Description: Drybrush is a painting technique in which a paint brush that is relatively dry, but still holds paint, is used. This technique provides a 'broken' color effect. It is often used in realism, portraiture and abstract art style, and it allows detailed composition with varied color range.

Title: Duane Michals
Description: Duane Michals is a renowned American photographer, known for his narrative, often dream-like sequences, and the use of text to accompany his images. He has greatly influenced conceptual and narrative photography. His work spans through various indoor and outdoor environments, making use of natural and artificial light sources.

Title: Dufaycolor Photograph
Description: Dufaycolor is an early British additive color photographic film process, introduced for motion picture use in 1932 and for still photography in 1935. The medium primarily delivers a realistic composition in full-color under natural lighting, often used in pictorialism and photojournalism.

Title: Duro Olowu
Description: Duro Olowu is a Nigerian-born British fashion designer, widely known for his elegant and modern art style. His medium mainly involves working with textiles, creating diverse, colorful designs that elicit an elegant mood. His work is often exhibited on fashion runways.

Title: Dustin Nguyen
Description: Dustin Nguyen is a comic artist known for his dramatic pseudo-realism art style. His primary medium is illustrated comics, which showcase a varied color palette and are often set in a variety of comic settings. His work is best exemplified in comics like 'Justice League of America' and 'Batman: Streets of Gotham'.

Title: Dziga Vertov
Description: Dziga Vertov is known for his unique art style in film where he used natural light to capture cinematic realism. He pioneered in the art of montage and composed the arrangement of his shots in a juxtaposition manner.

Title: Eadweard Muybridge
Description: Eadweard Muybridge is widely recognized for his photographic sequencing and motion photography works. He used outdoor lighting to shoot in monochrome and arranged his works in sequential order, capturing movement and life with high precision.

Title: Earl Norem
Description: Known for his realistic illustrations, Earl Norem's art style involved creating fantasy environments through painting. He often used vibrant colors to create a dramatic mood and focused on figurative compositions.

Title: Ebru
Description: Ebru is an art style originating from Turkey, known for its marbling technique combined with Islamic calligraphy. Artists use multicolored pigments on paper to create abstract compositions, representing one of the oldest forms of printmaking.

Title: Eclectic Architecture
Description: Eclectic Architecture represents a diverse art style combining elements from various historical architecture styles, such as Victorian, Gothic Revival, and Tudor. This urban architecture style is known for its variety and diversity in colors and compositions.

Title: Ecopunk
Description: The Ecopunk art style is characterized by its focus on ideas of ecological sustainability and a proactive approach to technology and environmentalism. Visual aesthetics often include futuristic, urban landscapes with bright, contrasting colors and artificial, neon lighting, reflecting an activist, hopeful mood.

Title: Ed Brubaker
Description: Ed Brubaker is a Comic Book writer known for his crime-noir art style. His stories are typically depicted frame-by-frame, using high contrast lighting and either monochromatic or highly contrasted color schemes. His Medium of choice is comic illustration.

Title: Ed Emshwiller
Description: Ed Emshwiller is an Illustrator and Filmmaker known for his work in speculative and science fiction art. His art style is known for its vibrant tones, airy colors, and compositions featuring imaginary concepts and futuristic elements.

Title: Ed Freeman
Description: Ed Freeman is a Photographer who practices fine art and photorealism. His style is characterized by the use of both natural and artificial light in his compositions, which are often carefully staged and intentional.

Title: Ed Mell
Description: Ed Mell is a modernist painter best known for his southwestern style. Featuring desert landscapes, his compositions often utilize vibrant, saturated colors and depict the environment through geometric forms and lines.

Title: Ed Paschke
Description: Ed Paschke was an American artist, considered a central figure in the Chicago Imagist school. His work is characterized by intense colors and complex, abstract compositions, often with Pop Art and Abstract Expressionism influences.

Title: Ed Piskor
Description: Ed Piskor is a comic book artist and writer known for his distinct cartoonish style and overall narrative compositions. His works are primarily in the genre of comic art.

Title: Ed Roth
Description: Ed 'Big Daddy' Roth was a celebrated artist and design visionary around the mid-to-late 1950s and 1960s. Roth's artwork embodied the spirit of Pop Art and California's 'Kustom Kulture'. He created a playful, character-focused composition.

Title: Ed Wood
Description: Ed Wood was an American filmmaker, often celebrated ironically as the worst director of all time. His low-budget, eccentric films have a cult following and are appreciated for their strange, imaginative flair.

Title: Eddie Campbell
Description: Eddie Campbell is a Scottish-born comic book artist, known largely for his collaborations with Alan Moore. His style is grounded in the domains of graphic novels and comic art, featuring narrative-driven, panelled compositions.

Title: Eddie Mendoza
Description: Eddie Mendoza is a popular digital artist, recognized for his distinct conceptual approach to digital art. His works often exhibit futuristic settings, characterized by vibrant color schemes and dynamic compositions. His style is similar to the works of artists such as Daniel Dociu and Thierry Doizon.

Title: Edgar Degas
Description: Edgar Degas was a renowned French artist known for his impressionistic paintings that often depicted urban, intimate scenes. His use of pastel color palettes and natural lighting further enhance the realism in his works. His style is closely related to other artists like Pierre-Auguste Renoir and John Singer Sargent.

Title: Edmonia Lewis
Description: Edmonia Lewis was a groundbreaking American sculptor associated with the Neoclassicism movement. Her sculptures typically exhibit eloquent moods, structured composition and are often monochrome in color. Similar artists include Harriet Hosmer and Mary Cassatt.

Title: Edmund Dulac
Description: Edmund Dulac was a French-born, British naturalized illustrator who specialized in art that captures dreamy fairy tale environments. His works, influenced by the Art Nouveau style, often present rich color palettes, fantastical lighting, and flowing compositions. Dulac's style mirrors that of fellow illustrators Arthur Rackham and Howard Pyle.

Title: Edmund Leighton
Description: Edmund Blair Leighton was an English painter known for his detailed and romantic depictions of historical scenes. His art style, a mix of Romanticism and the Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood, makes use of soft lighting and muted colors to convey a sense of timeless romance. Similar artists include John Everett Millais and Ford Madox Brown.

Title: Edouard Bisson
Description: Edouard Bisson was a French painter known for his association with the Academicism and Impressionism art styles. His artwork often showcased vibrant color palettes and figurative compositions, primarily executed through painting.

Title: Edouard Manet
Description: Edouard Manet was a prominent French painter whose influence on modern art was substantial. His art style was a combination of Impressionism and Modernism, with his paintings featuring a diverse color palette and realistic compositions.

Title: Édouard Manet
Description: Édouard Manet, spelt with an accent, was a significant figure in the transition from Realism to Impressionism and had a significant impact on the development of Modern art. His art style comprised a versatile color palette and realistic compositions.

Title: Edouard Vuillard
Description: Edouard Vuillard was a renowned French painter of the Post-Impressionist period, closely associated with the Nabis style. He specialized in intimate, domestic scenes with subdued color choices and favored the medium of painting.

Title: Eduardo Kobra
Description: Eduardo Kobra is a contemporary Brazilian street artist famed for his colorful and geometric mural paintings. His distinctive art style is characterized by the use of vibrant colors and large-scale geometric compositions, often crafted using spray paint.

Title: Edvard Munch
Description: Edvard Munch was a Norwegian painter, best known for his work 'The Scream'. As a prominent figure of expressionism and symbolism, Munch's style is characterized by his depiction of human emotion, particularly that of fear, and his use of color, form, and dramatic, sickly lines.

Title: Edward Burne-Jones
Description: Edward Burne-Jones was an English Aesthetic painter and one of the most important figures in the second phase of the Pre-Raphaelite movement. His art style is characterized by the use of mythical and medieval themes combined with intricate composition.

Title: Edward Burtynsky
Description: Edward Burtynsky is a Canadian photographer known for his large-format images of natural environments altered by industry. His style bridges the divide between art and documentary photography, with a prominent feature being his depiction of industrial landscapes.

Title: Edward Curtis
Description: Edward Curtis was an American photographer and ethnologist whose work focused on the American West and on Native American peoples. His style is characterized by the dignified and detailed portrayals of Native American tribes.

Title: Edward Gorey
Description: Edward Gorey was an American writer and artist noted for his illustrated books. His art style is characterized by intricately detailed, yet whimsical ink drawings, embodying a somewhat morbid, gothic humor.

Title: Edward Hopper
Description: Best known for his oil paintings, Edward Hopper was a prominent realist and modernist artist. His work predominantly features stark, urban scenes marked by isolated figures. Hopper brilliantly uses natural sunlight to cast deep shadows and often employs a muted color palette. His art often captures feelings of loneliness and introspection.

Title: Edward Kienholz
Description: Edward Kienholz was a ground-breaking installation and funk artist. He typically used mixed media to create thought-provoking installations within exhibition spaces. His compositions were often complex and raw, reflecting reality in a provocative way. The color and lighting in his works are dependent on the chosen materials and exhibition spaces.

Title: Edward Lear
Description: Edward Lear, known also as a writer, was an artist of the Romantic period, specializing in painting stunning, detailed landscapes with watercolors. His use of bright colors brought a fantastical mood to his works, while soft daylight produced gentle shadows in the depicted scenes. Lear became known for his whimsical style which often blurred the lines between reality and imagination.

Title: Edward Moran
Description: Edward Moran was an American artist associated with the Hudson River School and Luminism styles. He was known for his seascapes marked by detailed, vivid colors and luminous lighting which created tranquil atmospheres. His paintings are characterized by a strong sense of light and color, with a focus on the quiet moments of natural landscapes.

Title: Edward Robert Hughes
Description: Edward Robert Hughes was a noted Pre-Raphaelite and Aestheticism stylist. He painted detailed scenes filled with rich colors often set in woods and forests during twilight. His art style was mystical and dream-like, accentuated by the unique way he captured changing light and color. Hughes' works often teem with lyrical beauty and intricate symbolism.

Title: Edward Ruscha
Description: Edward Ruscha is a prominent artist known for his association with the Pop Art movement. His works often incorporate text and commonplace objects, making use of painting as a medium. Conceptual elements are often present in his art style.

Title: Edward S. Curtis
Description: Edward S. Curtis was a photographer who is best remembered for his work documenting Native American peoples. His photographic style leans toward Pictorialism, trying to create an aesthetic, artistic quality in his images.

Title: Edward Steichen
Description: Edward Steichen was an innovator in photography, known for his groundbreaking contributions to pictorialism and modernism. His work exudes a sense of elegance and aesthetic depth.

Title: Edward Tufte
Description: Edward Tufte is an expert in statistical graphics and data visualization. His work does not fit in a traditional art realm but holds aesthetic qualities within graphic design and infographics.

Title: Edward Weston
Description: Edward Weston, a photographer, is known for his modernist style. His works, often created with natural light, are noted for their outstanding clarity and subtle tonality.

Title: Edwardian Fashion
Description: Edwardian Fashion art style pertains to the elegance and detailed fashionable wear of the Edwardian era. Artists like Lucile Lady Duff-Gordon and Paul Poiret have influenced this style.

Title: Edwin Austin Abbey
Description: Edwin Austin Abbey was an American artist known for his Realist and Impressionist styles. His work often carried historic narratives and used vibrant color schemes in painting medium.

Title: Edwin Landseer
Description: Sir Edwin Landseer was a British artist recognized for his Romanticism and Realism styles. His paintings often portrayed animals with a meticulous attention to details and a naturalistic color palette.

Title: Eero Saarinen
Description: Eero Saarinen was a Finnish-American architect known for his Modernist style. His iconic designs are marked by sweeping forms, functional purposes and are generally featured in a monochromatic color scheme.

Title: Egon Schiele
Description: Egon Schiele was an Austrian artist famous for his Expressionist style. His painting medium favored earthy color schemes, carrying a melancholic mood and often featured distorted compositional structures.

Title: Eiichiro Oda
Description: Eiichiro Oda is a Japanese manga artist, known for his work on the highly popular series 'One Piece'. His art style combines elaborate fantasy environments with versatile and dynamic sequential compositions to create an adventurous mood. The color scheme in his work varies widely, reflecting the diverse settings and tones of the adventures in his storytelling.

Title: Eiko Ishioka
Description: Eiko Ishioka was an influential visual artist and graphic designer renowned for her eclectic and avant-garde costume designs in cinema, using bold colors and compositions that had a strong visual impact.

Title: Eileen Agar
Description: Eileen Agar was a reputed British painter and photographer associated with the Surrealist and Cubist movements. Her work is characterized by vibrant art pieces with abstract environments and eclectic compositions.

Title: El Anatsui
Description: El Anatsui is a celebrated Ghanaian sculptor known for his installation art and sculptures. He refashions found materials, especially metal, into varied colors, having strong connections to nature and transformation.

Title: El Greco
Description: El Greco, a Spanish Renaissance painter, suffered a unique style blending Byzantine and Western artistic traditions. His dramatic compositions, featuring warm colors and chiaroscuro lighting, often depicted religious themes, rendering a spiritual mood.

Title: El Lissitzky
Description: El Lissitzky was a Russian artist, designer, photographer, typographer, and architect. His art style is associated with Suprematism and Constructivism, showcasing dynamic compositions with geometric environments and a limited color scheme.

Title: Elaine De Kooning
Description: Elaine de Kooning was renowned for her abstract expressionism and figurative art, influenced heavily by her peers, Jackson Pollock, Mark Rothko, and her husband, Willem de Kooning.

Title: Elden Ring
Description: The Elden Ring game features a surreal, gothic mood presented in a medieval environment. It employs fantasy and digital art styles, renowned for its seemingly otherworldly designs.

Title: Eleanor Fortescue-Brickdale
Description: Eleanor Fortescue-Brickdale was famous for her Pre-Raphaelite and Romantic art styles, influenced greatly by artists such as John Byam Liston Shaw, and John Roddam Spencer Stanhope.

Title: Election Poster
Description: The Election Poster is a form of art emphasizing propaganda and poster art styles. It's typically bold and persuasive, using print as a medium.

Title: Electropunk
Description: Electropunk represents cyberpunk and graffiti art styles infused with vibrant colors and a rebellious mood, primarily set in an urban environment. The medium is primarily digital.

Title: Elfen Lied
Description: Elfen Lied, a popular anime series, features an art style that focuses on horror and psychological elements with a mix of supernatural and romantic tragedy. The art style is recognized for its dynamic composition and dark mood. The main artist associated with this style is Lynn Okamoto.

Title: Elie Saab
Description: Elie Saab, an acclaimed fashion designer, has an art style characterized by haute couture, pret-a-porter, and bridal styles. The art style is recognized for its sophisticated elegance, symmetrical composition, and earthy color palette. Elie Saab himself is the artist associated with this style.

Title: Elina Brotherus
Description: Elina Brotherus, a renowned photographer, is known for her distinctive art style that blends contemporary, self-portrait, and landscape photography. Recognized for her minimalist compositions, melancholic mood, and use of natural lighting, Brotherus herself is the primary artist associated with this style.

Title: Élisabeth Vigée Le Brun
Description: Élisabeth Vigée Le Brun, an iconic painter, is known for her art style that resonates with Rococo and Neoclassical portrait painting. Her artworks are recognized for their elegant mood, balanced composition, and rich color palettes. Vigée Le Brun herself is the artist associated with this style.

Title: Elisabetta Sirani
Description: Elisabetta Sirani, a famed painter, had an art style that is associated with the Baroque artistic movement. Her works are mainly portraits recognized for their dynamic compositions, dramatic moods, and vibrant colors. Sirani herself is the artist associated with this style.

Title: Elizabeth Catlett
Description: Elizabeth Catlett was a prominent African-American artist known for her figurative sculptures and printmaking. Working primarily in bronze, she created monochrome pieces with a particular emphasis on the female form.

Title: Elizabeth Gadd
Description: Elizabeth Gadd is a contemporary photographer whose work typically captures the interaction between humans and nature. Gadd's outdoor shots take advantage of natural lighting to accentuate the serene beauty found in isolated, human-nature interactions.

Title: Elizabeth Shippen Green
Description: Elizabeth Shippen Green was a pioneering female illustrator in the 'Golden Age of American illustration'. Her narrative watercolors often center around a scene, enabling the viewer to read the story even without text.

Title: Elizabeth Siddal
Description: Elizabeth Siddal was a key figure in the Pre-Raphaelite movement. Her sepia drawings often convey a melancholic mood through their figurative composition. She became one of the muses for the Romanticism movement, offering a unique perspective as both model and artist.

Title: Elizabethan Fashion
Description: Elizabethan Fashion reflects the opulence and detail-oriented design of the Elizabethan era. Fashion illustrations of that period typically feature vibrant color and intricate details, depicting the lavish material and exaggerated silhouettes that were popular during the Renaissance.

Title: Ellen Jewett
Description: Ellen Jewett's art style is primarily surreal and symbolic, characterized by intricate, nature-inspired sculptures. Her work portrays a mysterious mood, using vibrant shades in an imaginary environment. The composition of her work leans heavily on three-dimensional space, adding to the depth and allure.

Title: Ellen Von Unwerth
Description: Ellen von Unwerth's art style is made up of fashion photography and erotic art. Her photography, often monochrome, is known for its bold mood and dramatic lighting. She primarily shoots in a studio environment and employs a focused, crisp composition for her subjects.

Title: Elliott Erwitt
Description: Elliott Erwitt's art style is primarily documentary and street photography. His work, often in monochrome, captures a candid mood in urban environments with ambient lighting. The composition of his photographs is usually spontaneous, representing the unpredictability and dynamism of life.

Title: Elsa Beskow
Description: Elsa Beskow's art, known for children's illustration and Nordic folklore, is dominated by whimsical moods. Her use of pastel colors, often set in European landscapes, compliments her narrative composition. Her paintings carry the warmth of fantasy, making her a beloved illustrator.

Title: Elsa Bleda
Description: Drawing from photography and neon aesthetics, Elsa Bleda's art style captures urban decay in a melancholic mood. The use of heavily saturated colors under neon lighting gives an atmospheric quality to her nighttime urban environments. Her photographs often feature symmetrical compositions.

Title: Embossing
Description: Embossing is a technique in the art world that raises or indents designs against a background, creating a three-dimensional effect on the surface. It's commonly used in paper crafting, leatherwork, and even metalworking. The lighting and color scheme tend to be natural, but can vary depending on the artist. It's a tactile art form, encouraging viewers to touch and interact with the pieces.

Title: Embroided
Description: Embroided art style involves the use of needle and thread to create designs and pictures on fabric. Artists draw from a wide range of colors, and therefore, it is often vibrant and engaging. Embroidery reflects an array of patterns, from simple monochromes to complex multi-colored designs. Artists usually use light to bring out the textures in their works.

Title: Embroidery
Description: Embroidery is a two-dimensional or slight relief textile art form that uses needle and thread or yarn to create decorative designs on fabric or other materials. The color schemes are multi-colored due to the variety of threads available. The detail level and complexity of these designs can range from simple abstracts to intricate realistic scenes.

Title: Emek
Description: Emek is renowned for his unique and vibrant style of art, particularly in the world of poster art and gig posters. His technique employs bold colors and dramatic lighting, often showcasing surreal compositions. Emek's work has a strong psychedelic mood, reflecting the urban environment. Emek's pieces are predominantly prints.

Title: Emeric Pressburger
Description: Emeric Pressburger was a celebrated film director known for his distinguished style that predominantly reflected the genres of Film Noir and Realism. Utilizing the medium of film, Pressburger's works were typically characterized by high contrast lighting, monochromatic color schemes, and a dramatic mood. The compositions in his movies were largely story-driven, leading to a very cinematic environment.

Title: Emil Nolde
Description: Emil Nolde was a German-Danish painter and printmaker, known for his emotional and vivid use of color. He was an important proponent of the Expressionist movement, and his painting style is characterized by non-objective composition and strong, emotional subject matter.

Title: Emile Bernard
Description: Emile Bernard was a French post-Impressionist painter and writer, who had art styles of symbolism and post-impressionism. He used bold colors and deviated from the realistic representation, creating a narrative, figurative compositions, often interpreting religious and symbolic themes.

Title: Emilio Pucci
Description: Emilio Pucci was an Italian fashion designer and politician. He is recognized for his signature bold, abstract prints in high-color combinations, utilized primarily in women's clothing and accessories. His art in fashion design exuded an exuberant mood.

Title: Emily Carr
Description: Emily Carr was a Canadian artist and writer heavily inspired by the Indigenous cultures of the Pacific Northwest Coast. She was known for her landscapes and forest scenes, expressed in a post-impressionist and later, a modernist style, with earthy tones and spiritual mood.

Title: Emmanuel Lubezki
Description: Emmanuel Lubezki is a Mexican cinematographer known for his work with directors such as Alfonso Cuarón and Terrence Malick. He is famed for his use of natural lighting and extended, uninterrupted shots, which lend a realistic mood to the cinema environment.

Title: Emmanuel Shiu
Description: Emmanuel Shiu is a critically acclaimed concept artist known for his captivating digital and conceptual works. His art often navigates the realms of science fiction, offering detailed and futuristic environments brought to life via digital painting.

Title: Emmet Gowin
Description: Emmet Gowin is an esteemed American photographer. His work primarily delves into contemporary and fine art photography, with a strong focus on humanistic and environmental themes.

Title: Erin Hanson
Description: Erin Hanson is a modern American painter credited with developing the 'Open Impressionism' style. Her style deviates from traditional impressionism by using bolder and broader strokes to capture the beauty of nature in her works.

Title: Ernest Hamlin Baker
Description: Ernest Hamlin Baker, known for his distinct illustrative style, specialized in portrait art and employed a rich mix of media. His work is largely recognized by the powerfully illustrative manner in which it captures its subjects.

Title: Ernest Zacharevic
Description: Ernest Zacharevic is a contemporary visual artist specializing in street art and murals. His art is usually seen in urban areas and is vibrant and multicolored, displaying a striking blend of imagination and realism.

Title: Ernesto Neto
Description: Ernesto Neto is a Brazilian contemporary artist known for his large-scale, abstract sculptures. His works often exhibit a soft, organic nature, using neutral colors and are usually displayed indoors.

Title: Ernst Barlach
Description: Ernst Barlach was a German expressionist sculptor known for his figurative and monochromatic sculptures. His works reflect a sense of simplicity and spiritual aspiration.

Title: Ernst Fuchs
Description: Ernst Fuchs was an Austrian painter known for his works in surrealism and symbolism. His paintings typically featured vibrant colors, dramatic lighting, and fantastical compositions.

Title: Ernst Haas
Description: Ernst Haas was an influential Austrian-American photojournalist known for his pioneering use of color in photography. His compositions are dramatic, characteristically with a naturalistic lighting.

Title: Ernst Haeckel
Description: Ernst Haeckel was a renowned biologist and artist known for his detailed and vibrant natural illustrations. His work often represents the scientific and biological art style, emphasizing intricacies in natural forms.

Title: Ernst Ludwig Kirchner
Description: Ernst Ludwig Kirchner was an expressionist painter and one of the founders of the art group 'Die Brücke'. His works often depict dynamic, agitated scenes of urban life with bright, contrasting colors.

Title: Erwin Blumenfeld
Description: Erwin Blumenfeld was a celebrated fashion photographer, known for his experimental and surrealistic work. His ethereal, monochrome photographs, often captured in studio settings under dramatic lighting, significantly influenced the fashion industry.

Title: Erwin Olaf
Description: Erwin Olaf is a contemporary photographer known for his provocative and staged portraitures. His works often exhibit saturated colors, controlled environment and studio lighting, reflecting a distinctive staging technique.

Title: Erwin Wurm
Description: Erwin Wurm is a contemporary artist known for his humorous and abstract sculptures. His work frequently involves the viewer's participation, converting mundane actions into art and blurring the line between sculpture and performance art.

Title: Esao Andrews
Description: Esao Andrews is a contemporary painter widely known for his Surrealistic and Dark Art. His works are often identified as melancholic, blending realistic depictions with surreal elements. Influenced by artists like Audrey Kawasaki and Tara McPherson, Andrews's work often features muted color palettes and emotionally charged scenes.

Title: Esteban Cortazar
Description: Esteban Cortazar's artistic contribution lies in the realm of fashion design. His style embraces a modern, chic, and elegant aesthetic, heavily inspiring the world of high fashion. His work is preceded by the likes of Karl Lagerfeld and Gianni Versace, whom he draws influence from.

Title: Esteban Maroto
Description: Esteban Maroto's artistic prowess lies in comic art. He creates meticulous line art illustrations often set in dramatic, fantasy environments. His style is frequently lauded for capturing intricate details and has heavily influenced the comic industry. Maroto draws distinctive stylistic elements from fellow artists like Jose Gonzalez and Frank Frazetta.

Title: Esther Pissarro
Description: Esther Pissarro's paintings are a reflection of Impressionism, with a characteristic use of light colors and a soft approach to lighting. This style typically captures the natural world or ordinary life scenes, and it bears a relationship to the works of Paul Cézanne and Monet.

Title: Etching
Description: Etching is an exemplary style of printmaking, featuring intricate compositions crafted through lines and dots. This art is traditionally produced on a metal plate and is renowned for the rich details it can capture. Rembrandt and Giovanni Battista Piranesi are two significant artists associated with this technique.

Title: Etel Adnan
Description: Etel Adnan is known for her abstract expressionism and minimalist works, typically featuring bold, vibrant colors and geometric compositions. Her works strongly echo themes of landscapes, particularly of the Lebanese mountains and California seascapes.

Title: Etherealpunk
Description: The Etherealpunk art style is an amalgamation of gothic, surrealism, and cyberpunk styles. It's primarily a digital art style, featuring complex compositions and low-key lighting that creates a mystical mood.

Title: Etienne-Jules Marey
Description: Etienne-Jules Marey was a pioneer in photographic studies of motion and inventor of chronophotography. His works are steeped in photorealistic and humanistic themes with linear compositions and natural lighting, capturing minute details.

Title: Ettore Sottsass
Description: Ettore Sottsass led the postmodern Memphis design movement, known for its colourful, abstract furniture creations. His designs, often asymmetrical, employ a multitude of colors and are typically associated with urban environments.

Title: Eugène Delacroix
Description: Eugène Delacroix, a renowned Romantic painter, is known for his dramatic, intense paintings filled with action, and highly chromatic and vividly colored works, which were influential in shaping the aesthetic of the Romantic movement.

Title: Eugenio Recuenco
Description: Eugenio Recuenco is a renowned Spanish photographer known for his Surrealist and Conceptual art styles. His works, often monochromatic and filled with melancholia, are rich with symbolic elements, drawing comparisons with other influential photographers like Tim Walker and Annie Leibovitz.

Title: Eureka Seven
Description: Eureka Seven is a popular anime series known for its Mecha art style. Dynamic and adventurous, it features a vibrant Sci-fi environment brought to life through animation. The art style is credited to Tomoki Kyoda, Dai Sato,and Kenichi Yoshida.

Title: Evangelion
Description: Evangelion, a seminal anime series, showcases a striking Mecha art style. The vivid, dramatic, and complex compositions portray a dystopian world. The art style is largely attributed to Hideaki Anno, Yoshiyuki Sadamoto, and Kazuya Tsurumaki.

Title: Evelyn De Morgan
Description: Evelyn de Morgan, an eminent painter, worked primarily in the Pre-Raphaelite and Symbolist art styles. Her romantic and figurative compositions, rendered in rich colors, echo the work of artists such as Dante Gabriel Rossetti and John William Waterhouse.

Title: Expressionism
Description: Expressionism is an art style that emerged in the 20th century focused on representing raw, intense emotion. It manifests through distorted compositions and vivid colors in primarily painting medium. Artists notable for this style include Edvard Munch, Egon Schiele, and Wassily Kandinsky.

Title: Expressionist Architecture
Description: Expressionist Architecture, an art style belonging to the broader movment of expressionism, is known for its dynamic, organic forms and often designed with an urban landscape in mind. Key figures include Hans Poelzig, Bruno Taut, and Walter Gropius.

Title: Extreme Close-up Portrait
Description: Extreme close-up portraits, a subset of portrait photography and macro photography, focus on capturing minute details. Artists like Annie Leibovitz, David Bailey, and Irving Penn have contributed significantly in this style's growth. It is typically done with soft lighting and in full color.

Title: Extreme Wide Portrait
Description: Extreme wide portraits combine aspects of landscape and portrait photography to capture subjects in a broader context. The style is typically done outdoors, and artists such as Annie Leibovitz, Peter Lindbergh, and Steve McCurry have made remarkable contributions.

Title: Eyvind Earle
Description: Eyvind Earle, a painter known for his Surrealism and Abstract Expressionist styles. His works are characterized by their vibrant colors and geometric compositions. Earle is best known for his distinctive artistic contributions to Disney's animated features.

Title: Ezra Stoller
Description: Ezra Stoller is a renowned architectural photographer, remembered for his imagery that defines mid-century Modernism. Stoller's work often features geometrical composition and is taken within architectural spaces.

Title: F.W. Murnau
Description: F.W. Murnau was a highly influential film director, best known for his silent films. His style, characterized by gloomy moods, deep focus composition, and low-key lighting, is deeply rooted in German Expressionism and Film Noir.

Title: Fabian Perez
Description: Fabian Perez is an internationally renowned artist, widely recognized for his unique style that blends elements of Romanticism and Impressionism. His paintings are noted for their bold, dark colors, dramatic lighting, sensual mood, and high-contrast composition.

Title: FAILE
Description: FAILE is a Brooklyn-based artist collective known for their vibrant, collage-like murals. Rooted in Street Art and Pop Art, their pieces are typically set against urban environments and are recognized for their unique blend of typography, illustration, and comic imagery.

Title: Fairfield Porter
Description: Fairfield Porter was an American painter known for his intimate, sun-lit portraits of rural life. His style is characterized as Realist and Impressionist, with compositions that rely on natural lighting to evoke peaceful moods.

Title: Fairy Kei Fashion
Description: Fairy Kei is a pastel-themed fashion style that originated in Japan. It is a sub-style of Harajuku and Decora, known for its oversized clothing, excessively cute elements, and a color palette dominated by pastel shades.

Title: Fairypunk
Description: Fairypunk art style is a fascinating blend of fantasy, steampunk, and fairy art, often using natural motifs such as plants, animals, and fairy creatures. The style usually has an enchanted mood with earthy tones and often tends toward sculpture as the medium.

Title: Faith Ringgold
Description: Faith Ringgold's art style combines vibrant colors and the story quilts often narrate stories of societal issues. Her work is deeply influenced by African art and feminist art and serves as a form of protest.

Title: Fallout
Description: Fallout's art style is characterized by a retrofuturistic, post-apocalyptic aesthetic, often represented through grime and decay mood with desaturated colors. The game's environment revolves around derelicts and decaying structures.

Title: Family Portrait
Description: A family portrait art style often comes in either realism or impressionism form. The composition typically features a centered layout, with the mood ranging from formal to more casual. The lighting usually leans into natural light, and the medium is traditionally painting.

Title: Fan Ho
Description: Fan Ho's art style is characterized by monoColor (black & white) expressiveness combined with dramatic lighting effect. He is widely recognized for his street photography and modernism influence in his work, often utilizing geometric compositions.

Title: Fang Lijun
Description: Fang Lijun is a prominent Chinese contemporary artist best known for his pivotal role in the development of 'Cynical Realism', a Chinese contemporary art movement. His work, primarily done through painting, often portrays the contrast between urban and rural. His color schemes are usually vibrant and his compositions often depict the isolation of individuals, echoing the cynical mood he aims to depict.

Title: Fantasypunk
Description: Fantasypunk references a genre of art that combines elements of fantasy and often dystopian or alternate reality themes, inspired by art movements such as Speculative Fiction, Steampunk and Cyberpunk. Typically seen in illustration, this style includes futuristic environments, low lighting, and a muted color scheme that contributes to its mysterious mood. Artists often use elaborate world-building in their compositions.

Title: Farel Dalrymple
Description: Farel Dalrymple is an American artist known for his works in the field of comic art and pop surrealism. His comics are characterized by abstract environments and thought-provoking moods, often with a monochrome color scheme. His compositions are recognized for their dynamic panel arrangements and innovative page layouts.

Title: Fashion Illustration
Description: Fashion illustration is a genre of art consumed predominantly by the fashion industry. This art form uses styles such as Figurative Art, Minimalism and Pop Art as influences. The medium can vary, with drawing being most common. The style is often characterized by elegant moods, bright color schemes, an urban environment, and the central focus in the composition is laid on clothes depicting the latest fashion trends.

Title: Fashion Photography
Description: Fashion Photography is a genre of photography that's primarily focused on displaying clothing and other fashion items. It often involves a blend of styles such as Portrait and Conceptual Photography, executed usually in a controlled studio environment. With controlled lighting and varied color schemes, Fashion Photography compositions focus on fashion, styling and have a glamorous mood.

Title: Fashion Portrait
Description: Fashion portrait art style is a blend of portraiture and fashion. It often utilizes photography as a medium, with artificial lighting to achieve high-contrast or dramatic images. The environment mostly includes studios, and the portraits often exhibit an elegant mood with a centralized composition.

Title: Fashion Sketch
Description: The fashion sketch art style is a branch of illustration that specifically involves creating conceptual designs of clothing and fashion accessories. Generally, the medium for fashion sketches is drawing, often in a monochrome color scheme, with the compositions often being symmetrical.

Title: Fast Shutter Speed
Description: Fast shutter speed art style is a characteristic concept in photography, mainly featuring street, sports, and wildlife genres. It requires capturing photos in natural daylight for a clear view, providing a dynamic and exciting mood. The composition often follows the rule of thirds.

Title: Fate
Description: Fate art style revolves around visual interpretations of the concept of fate and destiny. It's rooted in art styles like surrealism, symbolism, and abstract where artists express concepts metaphorically. Medium often involves painting, and the mood is contemplative, with dark color schemes and often asymmetrical composition.

Title: Avant-garde Fashion
Description: Avant-garde fashion is a type of art style referring to designers who push the boundaries of fashion and challenge the norm. This style is distinguished by unconventional and radical designs, often blurring the lines between art and fashion. Though it varies in color and mood, it consistently maintains an innovative and provocative approach.

Title: Catherine Hyde
Description: Catherine Hyde's artworks often blend surrealistic and expressionistic styles. Her medium of choice is painting, with a central focus and a muted lighting. The environment of the subjective scenes is predominantly nature, with an earthy color palette which enhances the mystical mood of her works.

Title: Catherine Nolin
Description: Catherine Nolin's work features a realism style with elements of folk art. Her preferred medium is painting, with the scenes usually set in an indoor environment. Warm lighting and vibrant colors help create a balanced composition and a serene mood.

Title: Craola (Greg Simkins)
Description: Artist Greg Simkins, known as 'Craola', is recognized for his style influenced by Pop Surrealism and Storybook Illustration, delivered through Painting. His art presents a Whimsical mood with a Narrative composition and features Soft diffused lighting and a Saturated color scheme. Simkins' style is broadly connected to artists like Mark Ryden and Audrey Kawasaki.

Title: Diego Velázquez
Description: Diego Velázquez was a Spanish painter known for his significant contributions to the Baroque period. His work often depicts indoor environments with dramatic lighting to enhance the warmth and realism of his subjects. He is particularly renowned for his ability to capture the human nature in his portraits, which has influenced a great number of painters after him.

Title: Fate Zero
Description: Fate Zero embodies a notable anime and manga art style. This game leverages animation as a medium, often showcasing intense moods through its dynamic characters and scenarios. The robust use of contrast in its color scheme adds depth and enlivens the scenes.

Title: Fauvism
Description: Fauvism is an art style rooted in Post-Impressionism, characterized by bold, often non-naturalistic use of color. The medium is generally painting and uses a vivid color palette to express mood and emotion. The composition is simplified, focusing on color and form to express subjective emotions.

Title: Fay Godwin
Description: Fay Godwin is renowned for her black and white photography, depicting nature and landscapes with profound intensity. The art style primarily involves natural landscapes captured under natural light. Her work greatly influenced photographers like John Davies, Ravilious, Paul Hill, John Blakemore, and Tony Ray-Jones.

Title: Fayum Portrait
Description: Fayum portraits or mummy portraits, named after the Faiyum Oasis in Egypt, represent an art style from Roman Egypt. These portraits have a serious mood depicted in warm colors. The identifiable artists creating these paintings are largely unknown, however, this art greatly influenced the roman and egyptian art era.

Title: Federico Fellini
Description: Federico Fellini was an Italian film director renowned for his distinctive style of filmmaking. His movies often embodied a fantastical, surreal mood set in urban environments. He primarily created films in technicolor leading to a unique visual interpretation. His artistic style greatly influenced renowned filmmakers like Martin Scorsese, Terry Gilliam, David Lynch, Pedro Almodovar, and Guillermo del Toro.

Title: Felice Casorati
Description: Felice Casorati was prominent in the Magic Realism movement, known for his still life compositions and subtle use of cool colors. His work typically presented a melancholic mood. Notable contemporaries and influencers of his style included Georgio Morandi, Carlo Carra, Giorgio de Chirico, Mario Sironi, and Arturo Martini.

Title: Felicia Simion
Description: Felicia Simion is known for her ethereal style of photography, capturing the profound beauty of nature and portraits in a vivid color palette. Typically shot under natural light, her work presents an artistic characterization of the world. Artists influenced by her style include Bogdan Grigore, Lavinia Cernau, Matei Buta, Ioana Porav, and Alex Robciuc.

Title: Felicien Rops
Description: Felicien Rops is a Belgian artist renowned for his provocative symbolism and realism styles. He used etching as a medium for his artwork, typically set in outdoor environments with natural light. Rops's work is highly detailed and often has a provocative mood.

Title: Felipe Pantone
Description: Felipe Pantone is a contemporary artist known for his energetic graffiti and Op art styles. He leans toward bright, multicolour palette using geometric shapes in his compositions. His work is often set in vibrant, urban environments.

Title: Felt
Description: Felt is a textile-based form of craft, known for its soft texture. Artists like Joseph Beuys and Jorie Johnson have famously used felt in their works, showcasing the medium's versatility and textural possibilities.

Title: Felted
Description: Felted art style is a form of Fiber Art that uses texture and structure to create expressive pieces of artwork. Artists such as Elis Vermeulen and Marjolein Dallinga have popularized this art style, using it to create innovative and evocative designs.

Title: Fenghua Zhong
Description: Fenghua Zhong is a well-known artist who primarily works in the Realism art style. His paintings are known for their vibrant colours, detailed compositions and a soothing mood. He usually portrays natural environments under soft and calming light.

Title: Ferdinand Du Puigaudeau
Description: Ferdinand du Puigaudeau was a French Post-Impressionist painter known for his depictions of night landscapes. His work often comprises naturalistic outdoor scenes, displaying an Impressionistic and Symbolic art style. His paintings exhibit tranquil moods, characterized by glowing colors and night-inspired lighting.

Title: Ferdinand Ladera
Description: Ferdinand Ladera is a painter known for his Surrealistic art style. His work is characterized by vivid color schemes, often set in imaginative, dreamy, fantasy environments. His compositions display intricate detail and can often seem almost otherworldly.

Title: Fernand Khnopff
Description: Fernand Khnopff was a Belgian Symbolist painter whose work was known for its somber and isolated feel. His paintings, often set in interior environments, are characterized by a muted color scheme and depict lone figures that bring forth a sense of melancholy.

Title: Fernand Leger
Description: Fernand Leger was a renowned French painter who contributed significantly to the Cubist and Futuristic art movements. His works often show bright colors within abstract, geometric compositions, presenting a unique blend of machinery, figures, and landscapes that deliver a dynamic mood.

Title: Filip Dujardin
Description: Filip Dujardin is a Belgian photographer known for his surreal digital art. His photographs often showcase monochromatic urban environments with an architectural focus. His work is distinguished by its blend of reality and fantasy, resulting in unique compositions that are surreal and thought-provoking.

Title: Filippino Lippi
Description: Filippino Lippi was a prominent Italian painter during the Renaissance. His work often depicted vibrant, serene scenes with detailed composition. He is associated with other artists, such as Botticelli and Leonardo da Vinci.

Title: Final Fantasy
Description: The Final Fantasy series is renowned for its unique art style, combining elements of Anime, Manga, and Fantasy. The imaginative worlds, vibrant colors, and dynamic composition contribute to its adventurous mood. Artists such as Tetsuya Nomura and Yoshitaka Amano played crucial roles in designing this series.

Title: Final Fantasy Tactics
Description: Final Fantasy Tactics features an Anime, Manga, and Fantasy art style with a unique isometric composition. The game's strategic mood is complemented by an imaginary environment and muted color palette. Recognized artists like Akihiko Yoshida have contributed to this art style.

Title: Final Fantasy VII
Description: Final Fantasy VII's art is marked by Anime, Manga, and Steam Punk styles. It's set in a futuristic world, with a dynamic composition and diverse color palette, setting an epic mood. Artists Tetsuya Nomura and Yoshitaka Amano are renowned contributors.

Title: Fisheye Lens
Description: A fisheye lens is a piece of photography equipment that creates a dramatic, distorted style, often used in wide-angle composition. It tends to capture realistic colors under various environments and natural lighting. Noted photographers like Annie Leibovitz have used this lens for unique perspectives.

Title: Flat Design
Description: Flat Design is a minimalist art style that emphasizes simplicity, clarity, and efficiency. It uses vibrant and bold colors, simple shapes, and lacks textures, gradients, and complex details. Mostly implemented by big companies like Microsoft, Apple, and Google in their user interfaces. The design communicates effectively by stripping down to the most fundamental elements.

Title: FLCL
Description: FLCL is an anime series renowned for its diverse, energetic art style. Influenced by surrealism, the animation highlights vibrant colors and is set in a modern urban environment. The lighting in FLCL varies from scene to scene, supporting the changing moods and narratives of the series. Direction by Kazuya Tsurumaki, and the studios Gainax and Production I.G were instrumental in the creation of FLCL's unique look.

Title: Flemish Tapestry
Description: Flemish Tapestries are textile artwork originating from the Renaissance and Baroque periods. Known for their richness in color and intricate details, these pieces often depict historical or mythological scenes. Artist Pieter Coecke van Aelst and Jan Frans van Dael were renowned for their sublime masterpieces in this art form.

Title: Flora Borsi
Description: Flora Borsi is a renowned artist specializing in photography and image manipulation. Her style is rooted in surrealism and photorealism, using saturated colors, dramatic lighting, and provocative symbolism. Her work often involves manipulated compositions that challenge the viewer's perception of reality.

Title: Flowerpunk
Description: Flowerpunk is a form of contemporary art envisioned by Azuma Makoto. It fuses the traditional Ikebana (Japanese flower arrangement) with a bold and rebellious attitude, creating a sort of 'punk' style for flower arrangements. Using a variety of media, it often presents asymmetrical compositions and vibrant colors set in fantasy settings.

Title: Flyer
Description: Flyer art style is a type of graphic design that combines typography, imagery, and color to communicate a message. Designers like Milton Glaser and Paul Rand have been influential in this field. The medium is typically digital, and the color scheme can be multicolored to engage the viewer.

Title: Folk
Description: Folk art style, a subset of primitivism, often set in rural environments, where artists like Grandma Moses and Horace Pippin have become synonymous with it. It's characterized by a joyous mood, narrative composition, and vibrant color palette. The dominant medium of expression is painting.

Title: Fomapan 400
Description: Fomapan 400 art style is mainly associated with the practice of monochrome or black and white photography. The medium is photography, using the specific film 'Fomapan 400'. Artists like Ansel Adams and Robert Frank are well-known for producing high-contrast images.

Title: Forensic Photography
Description: Forensic Photography is a form of Documentary Photography. Used predominately in law enforcement, it presents a realistic and sombre mood portraying crime scenes or evidence. Notable practitioners include Alphonse Bertillon and Rodolphe A. Reiss. The lighting is typically artificial and the color scheme as realistic as possible.

Title: Found
Description: The Found art style, also known as 'Found object' or 'Ready-made', is a contribution of Dada and Surrealism. It involves the use of commonplace items in an assemblage to create provocative works. Artists synonymous with this style include Marcel Duchamp and Kurt Schwitters.

Title: Fra Angelico
Description: Fra Angelico, an early Renaissance painter, used vibrant colors to portray divine narratives mostly focused on Christian themes. His art style falls within frescoes and panel paintings, inspiring artists like Masaccio, Piero della Francesca, and Andrea del Castagno.

Title: Fractal
Description: Fractal art is a form of digital and abstract art, characterized by self-similar patterns that exhibit infinite complexity. The colors used are often multicolored with a transcendental mood. Artists like Benoit Mandelbrot, Jonathan Wolfe, and Carlos Ginzburg are notable for their contributions to this style.

Title: Francesca Woodman
Description: Francesca Woodman was a modern and surrealistic photographer, known for her black-and-white images often set in urban environment. Her work frequently features a melancholic mood with natural lighting and figurative compositions. Her work has resonance with artists like Diane Arbus, Cindy Sherman, and Nan Goldin.

Title: Francesco Francavilla
Description: Francesco Francavilla, a noted illustrator, is famed for his gothic comic art style, using a dark color palette to create dramatic narrative compositions. His style shares similarities with the works of artists like Mike Mignola, Bruce Timm, and Darwyn Cooke.

Title: Francis Bacon
Description: Francis Bacon was a renowned painter known for his bold, graphic and emotionally raw imagery. His art style merges expressionism and surrealism, often including gloomy moods and distorted human figures. He shares stylistic similarities with artists like Lucian Freud, David Hockney, and Edward Hopper.

Title: Francis Ford Coppola
Description: Francis Ford Coppola, a renowned film director, posses a unique art style marked by cinematography and film noir, often set in urban environments. His works usually convey a nostalgic mood and employ high contrast lighting with a symmetrical composition. Notable artists with similar influences include George Lucas, Martin Scorsese, and Steven Spielberg.

Title: Francis Picabia
Description: Francis Picabia, a painter known for his provocative works in the styles of Dada, Surrealism, and Cubism. His paintings, often multicolored, portray nonobjective compositions. Artists with similar influences include Marcel Duchamp, André Breton, and Salvador Dali.

Title: Francisco Goya
Description: Francisco Goya, celebrated for his Romantic and Realist art style, used Painting as a medium to display rural environments with dramatic lighting and earthy colors. His works are often somber with asymmetrical compositions. Notable artists with similar work include Edouard Manet, Eugene Delacroix, and Pablo Picasso.

Title: Francois Boucher
Description: Francois Boucher, a painter known for his Rococo style, frequently portrays light-hearted moods in indoor settings with soft lighting and pastel colors. His compositions are often organic. Influential artists with similar styles include Jean-Honoré Fragonard, Jean-Antoine Watteau, and Jacques-Louis David.

Title: François Schuiten
Description: François Schuiten is known for his engravings and surrealistic style seen in his drawings. His work often features imaginary environments depicted in monochrome, conveying a mystical mood with a detailed composition. Artists of similar influence include Moebius, Hergé, and Chris Ware.

Title: Frank Auerbach
Description: Frank Auerbach, a British artist, is known for his expressionistic style. Using a heavy impasto with earthy colors, Auerbach creates thick layers of paint, where every stroke is clearly visible. The resulting artworks are often abstract, yet they retain a sense of the figure or the identity of the original object.

Title: Frank Cho
Description: Frank Cho is an acclaimed comic book artist and writer, known for his distinct style. His art has a sense of motion and detail, and it's usually characterized by humor. Drawing dynamic figures with detailed comic art, he weaves incredible visual stories.

Title: Frank Frazetta
Description: Frank Frazetta, a renowned fantasy and science fiction artist, left a significant mark on world art. His style, marked by vibrant, dramatic compositions, influenced generations of artists. Drawing fantasy environments full of action, Frazetta captured his viewers' imaginations.

Title: Frank Gehry
Description: Frank Gehry is a famous architect whose unique style revolutionized the field of architecture. Known for his deconstructivist approach, Gehry designs buildings with a seemingly chaotic, asymmetrical look, often incorporating metallic colors and unexpected shapes.

Title: Frank Horvat
Description: Frank Horvat was a versatile photographer, adept in the art of fashion photography and photojournalism. Known for his honest and dynamic compositions, Horvat utilized natural light to create striking images that drove the narrative of his work.

Title: Frank Lloyd Wright
Description: Frank Lloyd Wright was an American architect who contributed significantly in the field of architectural design. His 'prairie school' designs incorporated natural colors and striking geometric structures, reflecting the landscape of the American Midwest.

Title: Frank Miller
Description: Frank Miller is known for his distinctive comic art style in graphic novels. He's recognized by a high contrasting monochrome scheme and dynamic compositions. Miller has influenced and is admired by many in the comic and graphic novel industry.

Title: Frank Quitely
Description: Frank Quitely is a renowned comic book artist known for his highly detailed and vibrant illustrations in graphic novels. His particular style has set a unique benchmark in comic artistry.

Title: Frank Stella
Description: Frank Stella is an American painter noted for his work in the areas of minimalism and post-painterly abstraction. Stella's geometric abstractions and multicolored works convey a sense of rhythmic and harmonious balance.

Title: Frank Thorne
Description: Frank Thorne is best recognized for his work in comic art, particularly in the genre of erotic art. His dynamic compositions, the variety of color use, coupled with dramatic lighting, have made him an influential figure in his field.

Title: Frans Hals
Description: Frans Hals was a Dutch Golden Age painter known primarily for his large-scale portraits. His art style, characterized by fluid brushwork and warm tones, was influential in the Baroque movement.

Title: Frans Lanting
Description: Frans Lanting is a renowned Dutch nature photographer whose work often demonstrates a photorealistic art style. He is known for his serene wildlife scenes captured under natural light.

Title: Franz Kline
Description: Franz Kline was an American painter primarily associated with the Abstract Expressionism movement. His signature style utilized intense, abstract shapes predominantly in black and white.

Title: Franz Marc
Description: Franz Marc was a German painter and one of the key figures of the Expressionist movement. His art style often depicted animal figures in vibrant colors and imbued them with symbolic, spiritual significance.

Title: Franz Sedlacek
Description: Franz Sedlacek was an Austrian artist associated with the New Objectivity and Magical Realism movements. He painted surreal cityscapes and scenes with a sense of melancholy, often in muted tones.

Title: Franz West
Description: Franz West was an Austrian artist who largely contributed to the Actionist and Contemporary art forms, known for abstract and whimsical sculptures.

Title: Franz Xaver Winterhalter
Description: Franz Xaver Winterhalter was a renowned 19th-century German painter, known for his refined painting style in the genre of realism and portrait art. His compositions feature accurate yet elegant portrayal of his subjects.

Title: Frederic Edwin Church
Description: Frederic Edwin Church, a central figure of the Hudson River School, worked in the Luminism style. He painted detailed and vibrant landscapes with natural light effects, generally rendering a serene mood.

Title: Frederic Leighton
Description: Lord Frederic Leighton was a British artist famous for his Victorian Classicism and Academic art styles. He focused on painting, creating works that combine idealized romanticism and dramatic compositions.

Title: Frederic Remington
Description: Frederic Remington was an American artist known for his Western art and Impressionistic style. He worked primarily in sculpture, creating dynamic compositions in earthy tones that depict the drama and action of the American West.

Title: Frederick Carl Frieseke
Description: Frederick Carl Frieseke was an American Impressionist painter known for his pastel-colored outdoor sceneries. His influences came from significant Impressionist painters like Claude Monet and Pierre-Auguste Renoir.

Title: Frederick McCubbin
Description: Frederick McCubbin was a prominent Australian Impressionist and Romanticist painter best known for his nostalgic and earthy-colored paintings of Australian landscape. He was part of the Heidelberg School, alongside artists like Tom Roberts and Charles Conder.

Title: Frederik Lord Leighton
Description: Frederik Lord Leighton was an English painter and sculptor, associated with Neoclassicism and Academic Art. His paintings often featured historical and heroic figures enunciated in a dramatic mood with vivid colors. His contemporaries included Thomas Couture and Jean-Léon Gérôme.

Title: Fresco
Description: Fresco is a technique of mural painting that has been widely used in Baroque, Byzantine, and Renaissance art. It is often found in religious sites such as churches, with scenes often depicting biblical stories. The technique is known for its use of natural lighting and vibrant colors. Notable artists known for their frescos include Michelangelo and Raphael.

Title: Frida Kahlo
Description: Frida Kahlo was a prominent Mexican painter known for her unique blend of Surrealism and Symbolism. Many of her works are self-portraits demonstrating emotional intensity. She often used intense colors for her personal narratives. Her husband Diego Rivera and Leonora Carrington were among her contemporaries.

Title: Friedensreich Hundertwasser
Description: Friedensreich Hundertwasser was an Austrian artist known for his expressive, vibrant, and surrealistic abstract art. His compositions were largely asymmetrical, aiming to introduce harmony in a chaotic world. He drew influence from fellow Austrian artists like Gustav Klimt and Egon Schiele.

Title: Frieke Janssens
Description: Frieke Janssens is a Belgian photographer known for her work in fine art and contemporary photography. Her images frequently use naturalistic light and carry a contemplative mood, focusing on evocative figurative subjects. Janssens' photography often captures the essence of human experience with natural tones.

Title: Frits Thaulow
Description: Frits Thaulow was a Norwegian painter, associated with the impressionist and realist styles. His paintings are mostly landscapes with earthy tones set in outdoor environments with diffused lighting. Thaulow's art usually induces a reflective mood, resonating with the works of artists like Claude Monet and Pierre-Auguste Renoir.

Title: Fritz Henle
Description: Fritz Henle was a renowned German photographer known for his pictorial and modernist photographic style. His works, often in monochrome, showcased portraits and landscapes under diffused lighting, creating a melancholic mood. Remarkably, Henle's proficiency lied in capturing every element in explicit detail.

Title: Fritz Lang
Description: Fritz Lang was a pioneering filmmaker known for his film noir and expressionist style. Often set in urban environments and shot under low-key lighting, his works predominantly used a monochrome color scheme, portraying a mysterious mood. Lang's film composition was dynamic, influencing other notable filmmakers such as Alfred Hitchcock and Orson Welles.

Title: Fritz Scholder
Description: Fritz Scholder was an American artist known for his Abstract expressionism and Pop art style. His works are characterized by vibrant coloration and expressionistic composition. He has notable influence from artists like Oscar Howe, Elaine de Kooning, and Robert Venturi.

Title: Fu Baoshi
Description: Fu Baoshi was a Chinese artist renowned for his traditional Chinese ink wash paintings, notably landscapes. His art style included a representational composition set in a natural environment. He took inspiration from artists like Qi Baishi, Huang Binhong, and Zhang Daqian.

Title: Fujichrome Provia 100F
Description: Fujichrome Provia 100F is a type of film used in photography, known for producing highly saturated colors and clear compositions. It's commonly used in photorealistic art styles. Notable photographers including Steve McCurry and Ansel Adams have utilized similar types of film.

Title: Fujicolor C200
Description: The Fujicolor C200 is a budget color film known for its ability to reproduce natural colors in photographic compositions. It is typically used in photorealism and color photography. Artists such as Henri Cartier-Bresson and Elliott Erwitt have utilized similar types of film in their works.

Title: Fujicolor Fujichrome Velvia 100
Description: The Fujicolor Fujichrome Velvia 100 is a professional film known for its vibrant colors and sharp compositions in photorealistic art style. Well-known photographers like Annie Leibovitz, Robert Capa, and Diane Arbus have worked with similar types of film.

Title: Fujicolor Pro 400H
Description: Fujicolor Pro 400H art style relates to photography that uses a specific film type, Fujicolor Pro 400H. It's renowned for its true-to-life, vibrant colors under daylight conditions. Artists belonging to this school include Wolfgang Tillmans and Nan Goldin.

Title: Fujicolor Superia X-TRA 400
Description: Fujicolor Superia X-TRA 400 art style is a photography style that involves the use of a specific film type, Fujicolor Superia X-TRA 400. This results in bold and vibrant colors with a high level of contrast. Prominent artists in this style include Cindy Sherman and Robert Frank.

Title: Fujifilm Neopan 100
Description: Fujifilm Neopan 100 art style pertains to a black and white photography technique that employs the use of a specific film type, Fujifilm Neopan 100. It yields high sharpness and fine grain images. Artists like Ansel Adams and Dorothea Lange are associated with this style.

Title: Full Body Height Portrait
Description: Full body height portrait art style refers to portraiture that includes the subject's entire body within the frame, whether in photography or painting. The compositions show balanced symmetry and the full figure of the person. Notable artists are Leonardo Da Vinci and Annie Leibovitz.

Title: Fullmetal Alchemist
Description: Fullmetal Alchemist's art style is emblematic of anime and manga, featuring dynamic action sequences and detailed backgrounds. The color-scheme ranges from bright to dark, reflecting the diverse moods of the storyline. Hiromu Arakawa is the main artist associated with this art style.

Title: Funk
Description: Funk art style originated in the 1960s as part of a reaction against the non-objectivity of abstract expressionism. Artists used mundane and absurd imagery, humor, and eroticism to create sculptures that demonstrated a preference for the tangible and real, in contrast with the serious and intellectual tendencies of previous movements. The style, characterized by its vivid color and non-traditional composition, has links with pop art, surrealism, and more.

Title: Fused Glass
Description: Fused glass art refers to the technique of joining glass pieces together by partly melting the glass at high temperature. The art style evolved from traditional glass-making methods and gained popularity in the modern art era. Notably, it's characterized by its multicolor scheme and layered composition.

Title: Futurepunk
Description: Futurepunk art style is a form of science fiction visual art that depicts futuristic dystopian worlds. The style is often characterized by complex compositions of futuristic cityscapes, neon lighting, and futuristic color palettes that may lean towards either extremely dark or bright, colorful atmospheres. The style has ties to other 'punk' art styles, including cyberpunk, steampunk, dieselpunk, and atompunk.

Title: Futurism
Description: Futurism was an artistic and social movement that originated in Italy in the early 20th century. It emphasized speed, technology, youth, and violence, and objects were represented as they were perceived in motion. The Futurism art style is characterized by dynamic compositions of industrial landscapes portrayed in bold colors and dramatic lighting, often conveying a sense of progressive mood.

Title: Gabriel Dawe
Description: Gabriel Dawe is renowned for his site-specific installations using colored thread to explore the connection between fashion and architecture. The Gabriel Dawe art style creates enormous, geometric, indoor rainbows that are elaborate three-dimensional structures composed of bright, multicolored thread. His work also often features natural lighting conditions that allow the colors to truly shine.

Title: Gabriel Metsu
Description: Gabriel Metsu was a Dutch painter known for his Baroque style characterized by a vivid and realistic portrayal of scenes. Detail-oriented compositions were integral to his work. He was contemporaneous with artist like Jan Vermeer, Pieter de Hooch and Nicolaes Maes.

Title: Gabriel Pacheco
Description: Gabriel Pacheco is a Mexican illustrator, known for his symbolist and surrealistic art style. His illustrations often invoke a sense of mystery and are characterized by muted color palettes and narrative-driven compositions. He shares artistic parallels with Remedios Varo, Leonora Carrington, and Giorgio de Chirico.

Title: Gabriele Munter
Description: Gabriele Münter was a German painter who contributed significantly to the Expressionist movement. Known for her bold, emotive style and bright color usage, Münter had a significant impact on early 20th-century art. She is often mentioned alongside artists such as Wassily Kandinsky, Franz Marc, and Alexei Jawlensky.

Title: Gabriele Viertel
Description: Contemporary photographer Gabriele Viertel is known for her ethereal and dynamic underwater photorealistic images which play with natural light. Often her images are compared to the water-themed work of artists like Barbara Cole, Howard Schatz, and Elena Kalis.

Title: Gaetano Pesce
Description: Gaetano Pesce is an Italian designer with a dynamic style straddling Modernist and Postmodernist art. He's celebrated for his innovative, multicolor, and fluid designs. His work draws comparisons with notable designers like Ettore Sottsass, Alessandro Mendini, and Andrea Branzi.

Title: Gail Potocki
Description: Gail Potocki is a Symbolist painter, celebrated for her ability to blend classicism with modern themes. Her paintings, often done in earth tones, portray strong, emotional scenes in a highly figurative composition. Artists like Gustav Klimt and Odilon Redon share similar art styles.

Title: Gainax
Description: Known for their energetic and dynamic art style, Gainax is an animation studio specializing in Mecha and Science Fiction anime. The animation is characterized by futuristic settings, vibrant color palettes, and dynamic action sequences. Notable artists include Hideaki Anno and Hiroyuki Imaishi.

Title: Gakuen Anime
Description: Gakuen Anime is a popular genre or art style of anime set primarily in school environments. These animations are often bright, light-hearted, slice-of-life stories or romantic comedies that follow an episodic composition. Artists like Akiyuki Shinbo and Yukihiro Miyamoto are known for this style.

Title: Galaxy Express 999
Description: Galaxy Express 999 is a widely known Space Opera Anime with a unique art style featuring outer space environments. The animation employs a dark color scheme with bright contrasts to mimic the cosmos. Its storytelling is adventurous with an underlying mood of melancholy. Leiji Matsumoto is a prominent artist behind this style.

Title: Gamerpunk
Description: Gamerpunk is a sub-genre of Cyberpunk focused on dystopian video game worlds. This digital art style, similar to Science Fiction, uses intense neon colors and is often described as dystopian. The composition is typically grid-based, depicting futuristic, tech-driven landscapes. Notable authors like William Gibson and Neal Stephenson explore topics related to this style.

Title: Gantz
Description: Gantz is an anime/manga with a dark, tense atmosphere set in an urban environment. The art style is both realistic and futuristic, showcasing Hiroya Oku's signature elements.

Title: GaoGaiGar
Description: GaoGaiGar is a mecha anime series with bright, vivid colors, and detailed composition. It creates a dynamic mood and is heavily set in urban environments, with Yoshitomo Yonetani as one of the key artists associated with this style.

Title: Gareth Pugh
Description: Gareth Pugh is known for his experimental and avant-garde fashion design. His work is often monochrome, featuring dramatic mood and geometric composition.

Title: Gari Melchers
Description: Gari Melchers was an American painter who balanced realism with elements of Impressionism. His works often depict serene moods and are set in natural, outdoor environments.

Title: Garry Trudeau
Description: Garry Trudeau is a renowned cartoonist known for his humor and depiction of modern society. His illustrations are narrative in composition and typically use bright colors.

Title: Garry Winogrand
Description: Garry Winogrand was a renowned American street photographer known for his depiction of American life in the mid-20th century. His art style is characterized by candid and spontaneous photographs taken in urban environments, often under natural lighting.

Title: Gary Bunt
Description: Gary Bunt is a British artist, known for his impressionist-style paintings. His works are often composed of vibrant colors and peaceful rural landscapes.

Title: Gary Larson
Description: Gary Larson is a retired American cartoonist, best known for 'The Far Side', a single-panel cartoon series. His art style is recognizable by its monochrome color scheme, comedic themes, and narrative composition.

Title: Gary Panter
Description: Gary Panter is an American illustrator and painter associated with the pop art and punk art movements. His works are known for their eccentric mood and dystopian themes, presented in vibrant colors.

Title: Gaston Bussiere
Description: Gaston Bussiere was a French painter and illustrator associated with the Symbolist movement. His art style was characterized by muted colors, mystical moods, and figurative compositions.

Title: Gaston Bussière
Description: Gaston Bussière was a French painter and illustrator, closely associated with the Symbolism and Art Nouveau movements. His works are known for their vibrant color schemes, fantasy-inspired compositions, and painting mediums. Related artists include Alphonse Mucha and Gustav Klimt.

Title: Gaston Lachaise
Description: Gaston Lachaise was a Franco-American sculptor who contributed significantly to Modernism with his figurative works. His primary medium was sculptures. Artists similar to Gaston Lachaise include Paul Manship and Jacob Epstein.

Title: Gatchaman
Description: Gatchaman is a Japanese anime featuring characteristic animation, set in a sci-fi environment. The art style is colorful, character-driven, and action-packed, reflecting typical anime styles. Relevant artists associated with Gatchaman's art style include Tatsuo Yoshida and Ippei Kuri.

Title: Gediminas Pranckevicius
Description: Gediminas Pranckevicius is a digital artist known for his Surrealism and Digital Art styles. His works are complex and typically exhibit a vivid color palette and a mystical mood. Salvador Dalí and René Magritte are artists who share related art styles.

Title: Gekiga Anime
Description: Gekiga is a specific art style within Anime and Manga that leans towards a more dramatic and realistic presentation. It often uses animation as a medium and tends to be narrative in composition. Artists related to this style include Osamu Tezuka and Tatsumi Yoshihiro.

Title: Gemma Correll
Description: Gemma Correll is a renowned illustrator known for her vibrant, humorous digital art and graphic design. Her style is appreciated for its simplicity, bright color schemes, and the use of clean lines.

Title: Gene Luen Yang
Description: Gene Luen Yang's artistic style is found within comic books and graphic novels, often utilizing a sequential medium to tell stories. His digital compositions undertake a diverse range of colors and generally carry serious undertones.

Title: Genndy Tartakovsky
Description: Genndy Tartakovsky's art style is definitive of the adventurous mood found within animation and cartoon genres. He uses dynamic digital compositions with a range of varying colors to create action-packed and visually engaging artworks.

Title: Genshin
Description: The Genshin art style presents an anime-influenced, fantasy aesthetic to set the tone for this role-playing game. It is characterized by detailed digital artwork, enriched with a fantastical mood and a colorful palette.

Title: Genshin Impact
Description: Genshin Impact uses an adventurous, anime-influenced, fantasy art style characterized by detailed digital artwork and vibrant colors, highlighting action-packed sequences within the realm of this Action Role-Playing Game.

Title: Geof Darrow
Description: Geof Darrow is renowned for his detailed comic book art style, featuring vibrant color schemes and intense moods. His work typically employs a panel composition in drawing medium.

Title: Geof Kern
Description: Geof Kern is a commercial and abstract photographer known for his art style which often highlights meticulously staged compositions in studio environments under artificial lighting.

Title: Geoff Johns
Description: Geoff Johns is an acclaimed comic book writer known for his vibrant and thrilling storylines. While his medium is writing, the visual interpretation of his work often takes the form of dynamic comic book panels.
