Description: Lewis Baltz was a visual artist and photographer known for his stark simplicity and minimalistic approach. His work often captures the transformed landscape, echoing the New Topographics and Minimalism art styles. His photographs, often black and white, present a serene mood. Baltz shares a similar approach with artists like Bernd and Hilla Becher.

Title: Lewis Hine
Description: Lewis Hine was an American sociologist and photographer, known for his works highlighting child labor and industrial conditions during the early 20th century. His sober photographs, mostly black and white, embody the art styles of Social Realism and Documentary Photography. Hine's work significantly influenced other photographers such as Dorothea Lange and Jacob Riis.

Title: Liam Wong
Description: Liam Wong is a celebrated photographer known for fusing cyberpunk and noir elements in his work. His photos often feature urban environments bathed in the bold neon lighting, creating mysterious, high contrast scenes. Inspired by the likes of Edward Hopper and Richard Tuschman, Wong utilizes the rule of thirds in his composition for engaging visual balance.

Title: Liar Game
Description: Liar Game, a board game turned manga and anime series, has an art style characterized by interior settings, harsh lighting conditions, and a monochromatic color scheme. The tense mood is conveyed through an array of wide shots in the series. The art style is much influenced by its creator, Shinobu Kaitani.

Title: Liar Game Anime
Description: The Liar Game Anime interpretation features an art style that leans heavily on vibrant colors to set a suspenseful mood. The Anime is mostly set indoors with stark lighting and a linear composition to focus on the main characters. The style of Shinobu Kaitani, the original artist of the series, deeply influences the Anime.

Title: Light Field Photography
Description: Light field photography is a contemporary art style that uses natural lighting to capture four-dimensional compositions. The style captures the intensity and direction of all the light rays in the scene. Ren Ng is famously associated with this photographic technique for his contribution to its development.

Title: Light Painting
Description: Light painting is an avant-garde photography style that uses artificial lights to paint a vibrant, dynamic scene captured using long-exposure. Originating from the 20th century, this art style includes moving light sources while the camera's shutter remains open. Notable artists within this genre include Man Ray and Barbara Morgan.

Title: Light Tracing
Description: Light tracing is a digital art technique that uses algorithms to mimic the natural behavior of light. It is often used to create highly detailed, photorealistic art or graphic designs. The lighting, mood, and composition of the artwork can vary greatly depending on the artist's intent.

Title: Lillian Bassman
Description: Lillian Bassman was a renowned photographer known for her distinctive style. Her work chiefly falls under the realm of fashion photography and fine art. Bassman’s work is noted for its high contrast, use of abstract compositions, and monochromatic color palette. Her contributions to art magazines, particularly Harper's Bazaar, have solidified her influence in the field.

Title: Lin Fengmian
Description: Lin Fengmian was a pivotal figure in modern Chinese painting, blending traditional Chinese techniques with western art movements like Impressionism and Cubism. He is known for his vibrant use of color, organic shapes, and natural context. His innovative approach to fusing east and west continues to be treasured in the annals of world art.

Title: Liniers
Description: Liniers, a renowned cartoonist, is appreciated for his illustrative art style manifested through his cartoons. Liniers' drawings are typically scene-based, depicting a moment or situation. His work is vivid, often utilizing a wide range of colors. He draws inspiration from several famous cartoonists like Quino and Bill Watterson.

Title: Linocut
Description: Linocut is a printmaking technique that emerged as an art style. It's closely tied to Expressionism and more broadly, printmaking. Artwork in this style is often monochrome, although color is sometimes used. The composition involves geometric shapes due to the carving method. Notable artists associated with this style include Picasso, Matisse, and Sybil Andrews.

Title: Lisa Frank
Description: Lisa Frank art style is known for its use of neon colors, resulting in a highly vibrant and cheerful aesthetic. It is often seen in her illustrations, with eclectic compositions involving playful themes found in a rainbow art style. The mostly remembered artist of this style is Lisa Frank herself.

Title: Lisette Model
Description: The Lisette Model art style is gritty and realistic, closely associated with street photography. Her works are often set in the urban environment featuring spontaneous compositions, utilizing natural lighting conditions. This style is primarily attributed to the photographer Lisette Model itself.

Title: Lisk Feng
Description: Lisk Feng's art style involves clean and geometric compositions often seen in vector art and digital illustrations. It stands out for its bright and pastel color scheme. The style is often attributed to Lisk Feng, a renowned illustrator in the digital art field.

Title: Lithography Print
Description: Lithography print art style is a part of the broader planographic printmaking discipline, characterized by multiple layers of detail. It's a printing technique invented by Alois Senefelder, and later applied by artists like Edvard Munch and Pablo Picasso.

Title: Little Witch Academia
Description: Little Witch Academia is notable for its vibrant colors and dynamic composition that emphasizes action and movement. As an anime, it represents the Japanese style of animation and features a heroic narrative structure commonly found in the medium, with a touch of fantasy elements.

Title: Liu Wei
Description: Liu Wei is known for his abstract and minimalist approaches in his works. His paintings often feature a monochromatic color scheme, and his non-objective compositions tend to focus on shapes and forms rather than representational figures.

Title: Liu Xiaodong
Description: Liu Xiaodong is famous for his realistic style, using painting as a medium. Often setting his works outdoors, he adopts a naturalistic color scheme and conveys stories through his narrative composition.

Title: Liu Ye
Description: Liu Ye is recognized for his surrealistic and pop art styles. His paintings utilize bright colors and symbolic compositions, often incorporating popular culture references and dreamlike settings.

Title: Lo-fi Photography
Description: Lo-fi Photography is a style which mimics a nostalgic, old-school aesthetic. It uses photography as a medium, often shot in low light for a more dramatic effect. The images generally have a desaturated color scheme, creating a nostalgic mood. The composition is mostly impromptu capturing raw, unedited moments.

Title: Logo
Description: Logo art style is the design approach used in creating distinct identities for businesses and brands. It utilizes different art styles like minimalist, abstract, illustrative, typographic, or 3D. The medium is often digital and the composition leans toward visual simplification. Prominent artists in this field include Rob Janoff, Paul Rand, Saul Bass, and Milton Glaser.

Title: Lois Van Baarle
Description: Lois van Baarle, also known as 'Loish', is a renowned digital artist. Her art style is characterized by the use of digital and conceptual elements. It embraces rich and vibrant colors to evoke a mood of fantasy. Her artworks typically feature figures in dramatic poses. Lois van Baarle's work has deeply influenced the genre of digital art.

Title: Loish
Description: Loish, a pseudonym for Lois van Baarle, represents a distinctive art style rooted in digital and conceptual elements. Her work is recognized for its rich, vibrant palette and fantasy-inspired moods. She uses dynamic forms in her composition and her digital designs have taken the art world by storm.

Title: Lomography
Description: Lomography is an art style within photography, marked by its use of analog, experimental, and abstract styles. This approach is characterized by 'lo-fi' lighting and highly saturated colors to induce a sense of nostalgia. The composition is unpredictable, capturing candid moments in the real world. Thse approach has been popularized by the Lomographic Society International.

Title: Lomography Color 100
Description: Lomography Color 100 refers to a type of film used in the Lomography art movement. The unique characteristics of the film contribute to the analog, experimental, and abstract styles of Lomography. It offers a normal lighting condition with vivid color reproduction, creating a nostalgic mood. The composition of the art is often spontaneous, reflecting unplanned moments from the real world. The Lomographic Society International has played a key role in this art concept.

Title: Lorenzo Quinn
Description: Lorenzo Quinn is a notable contemporary artist influential in the realm of sculpture. His art style can be linked with both Modern Sculpture and Contemporary Art. Quinn's sculptures often convey deep, emotional narratives, lending voice and form to abstract concepts. Notable for his usage of unique, dramatic mediums, his work shares stylistic similarities with artists like Antonio Canova, Auguste Rodin, and Alberto Giacometti.

Title: Lorna Simpson
Description: Lorna Simpson is famous within the fine art world, specifically focusing on Conceptual Art and Photography. Her work largely explores themes around identity, gender, race, and history, translating these broad topics into mind-provoking visual narratives. Her style shares characteristics with photographers Cindy Sherman, Barbara Kruger, and Carrie Mae Weems.

Title: Lotte Reiniger
Description: Lotte Reiniger, a pioneer of animation, introduced an enduring method of creating animations through Silhouette Animation. As a filmmaker, her unique style had an impact on the cinematic arts, creating a path that contemporaries like Walt Disney, Norman McLaren, and Windsor McCay would follow. Reiniger's stylistic narrative often drew from folklore and fairy-tales, bringing them to life with her distinctive techniques.

Title: Louis Kahn
Description: Louis Kahn was a renowned figure within the Modern Architecture and Brutalism movements. As an architect, his bold, monumental designs exuded a raw aesthetic, often making use of exposed concrete and brick. Kahn's style heavily influenced his peers and successors, including prominent architecture exponents like Frank Lloyd Wright, Le Corbusier, and Mies van der Rohe.

Title: Louis Sullivan
Description: Known famously as the 'father of skyscrapers', Louis Sullivan innovatively shaped the Modern Architecture movement, particularly the Skyscraper aesthetic. His iconic architectural designs popularized the use of steel frame constructions for tall buildings. His approach to functionalism and aestheticism, combined with his 'form follows function' principle, distinctively mark Sullivan's contributions, influencing contemporaries like Daniel Burnham, Frank Lloyd Wright, and Henry Hobson Richardson.

Title: Louis Wain
Description: Louis Wain, most popular for his anthropomorphized large-eyed cats and kittens, employed an art style that fell into the realms of Illustration and Surrealism. His medium was drawing, often using a multi-color scheme. The mood of his artwork is generally whimsical, composed mainly around a central figure.

Title: Louise Bourgeois
Description: Louise Bourgeois, a renowned artist known for her large-scale sculpture and installation art, often provoked thought and emotion with her works that spanned artistic styles like Modern Art, Surrealism, and Abstract Expressionism. Her art is characterised by a provocative mood and varies in composition.

Title: Low Angle
Description: The low angle art style is often employed in Realism, where the perspective is from below, looking upwards. This angle is often used to emphasize power or dominance.

Title: Low-poly
Description: The low-poly art style is a modern approach to art, usually in a digital medium, using simplified geometrical shapes. Often associated with minimalism and digital art, it has a futuristic mood and makes use of a vibrant multi-color palette.

Title: LSD
Description: The LSD-inspired art style is predominantly psychedelic, aligning with styles similar to Pop Art. The medium is mostly painting, emphasizing an array of colors to portray a surreal mood. The compositions are characteristically disorderly and chaotic, reflecting the altered state of consciousness.

Title: Luc Besson
Description: Luc Besson, a French film director, is known for his distinctive cinematic art style. His films, set in urban environments, are known for their dynamic composition, adventurous moods, and saturated color schemes often achieved through low-key lighting.

Title: Luc Schuiten
Description: Luc Schuiten is a Belgian architect whose drawings are known for their fantastical, organic compositions set in natural environments. His use of earth tones and architectural style makes his art both surreal and grounded in reality.

Title: Lucha Libre
Description: Lucha libre, a Mexican form of wrestling, is a performance art characterized by its vivid color schemes and energetic moods. The art style aligns with pop art, set usually in an arena with a dramatic composition.

Title: Lucian Freud
Description: Lucian Freud, a British painter, is known for his detailed, introspective depictions of human form. His art, characterized by its earthy colors and natural lighting, is often tied to Expressionism and Realism.

Title: Lucky Star
Description: Lucky Star, an anime series, is known for its distinct Moe anime art style. The series, set in a school environment, is characterized by simple compositions, bright colors, and joyful moods.

Title: Ludwig Bemelmans
Description: Ludwig Bemelmans's art is synonymous with vibrant color schemes and narration compositions that create a childlike mood. His style gravitates towards Children's Literature Illustrations and Impressionism.

Title: Ludwig Mies Van Der Rohe
Description: Ludwig Mies van der Rohe's architectural art reflects the Modernism and International Style, characterized by straightforward and symmetric compositions. He is particularly notable for his simplistic mood in his designs.

Title: Luis Royo
Description: Luis Royo's art style leans heavily on the Fantasy and Gothic art styles. His paintings typically exhibit gloomy lighting, dark color schemes, dynamic compositions, and a mysterious mood. Luis Royo is a prime artist in this genre.

Title: Luminogram
Description: The Luminogram art style is a form of Photography and Abstract Art characterized by low key lighting, black and white colors, unstructured composition, and an abstract mood. Michael Jackson is a renowned artist known for Luminogram art.

Title: Lupin the Third
Description: Lupin the Third is a Japanese manga and anime series created by Monkey Punch. Its visual style is characterized by a colorful and adventurous presentation, typically set in urban environments. The balanced lighting and action-packed composition contributes to its iconic style.

Title: Lynda Benglis
Description: Lynda Benglis is an American sculptor known for her work in minimalist and post-minimalist art. Her art style often involves three-dimensional sculptures, exhibiting both indoor and outdoor. The use of vibrant colors is noticeable. Her work is highly influential in feminist art.

Title: Lynsey Addario
Description: Lynsey Addario is a photojournalist known for her documentary photographs from war zones. Her style of photography relies heavily on natural lighting and capturing real-world scenarios, usually presenting the harsh realities of war and conflict.

Title: Lyubov Popova
Description: Lyubov Popova was an avant-garde artist who played a key role in the development of Cubist art in Russia. Her style of painting employed monochromatic coloring and geometric shapes, reflecting features of both Suprematism and Constructivism.

Title: M.C. Escher
Description: M.C. Escher was a Dutch graphic artist famous for his intricate and mind-bending designs. His surreal artwork usually involved impossible architectures, optical illusions, and infinite spaces, mostly created in black-and-white prints through lithography and woodcuts.

Title: M.F. Husain
Description: M.F. Husain was an Indian artist renowned for his Modern and Cubist inspired paintings. His works often featured a multicolored palette and had a unique, figurative composition. His work was influenced by artists like Pablo Picasso and Raja Ravi Varma.

Title: M.W. Kaluta
Description: M.W. Kaluta is a celebrated illustrator known for his comic art and realistic illustration style. His work often features a monochrome color scheme and has a narrative composition. His style was influenced by contemporaries like Bernie Wrightson and Neal Adams.

Title: Macrame
Description: Macrame is a form of textile art produced using knotting techniques rather than weaving or knitting. The art style is patterned with a special focus on the details of the knots. Renowned artists known for this style include Emily Katz and Sally England.

Title: Macross
Description: Macross is an anime and mecha art style known for its intense mood and multicolored scenes. It's characterized by asymmetrical composition, dynamic lighting, and a sci-fi environment setting. Notable artists involved include Haruhiko Mikimoto and Shoji Kawamori.

Title: Made In Abyss
Description: The 'Made in Abyss' art style derives from Japanese anime. It can be characterized by its detailed, vibrant illustrations set in expansive, fantastical cave systems, telling a tragic narrative of adventure. The concept artist is Akihito Tsukushi.

Title: Made of Felt
Description: Felt Art is a form of contemporary craft that employs the use of felt, a textile medium, to create textural and visually engaging pieces. Artistry involves either minimalist or highly detailed multicolor compositions. Some relevant artists include Lucy Sparrow, Shana Kohnstamm, and LeBrie Rich.

Title: Made of Iridescent Foil
Description: Iridescent Foil Art uses metal foil as its medium, typically involving abstract or pop art. The reflective properties of lighting on the iridescent colors give the art a unique palette. Artworks are often non-representational, focusing on the visual effects of color and light. Paul Jackson and Lisa Joukovski are known for this style.

Title: Made of Lace
Description: Lace Art, made predominantly in traditional or Victorian styles, utilizes lace as a textile medium. This art form is often monochromatic and showcases intricate composition. Artists like Cornelia Parker and Agnes Herczeg have used lace in their artwork.

Title: Madhubani Painting
Description: The 'Madhubani' art style is a form of traditional Indian folk art, often painted in earthy tones reflecting rural environments. This art is spiritual in nature, comprising figurative compositions. Known for their Madhubani art are artists like Bhaskar Kulkarni and Sita Devi.

Title: Madoka Magica
Description: The art style in 'Madoka Magica' can primarily be categorized under the anime and manga styles, using animation as the medium. The art portrays a dark mood housed within a vibrant and colorful, yet balanced composition in a fictional universe. Key artists associated with this series include Akiyuki Shinbo and Ume Aoki.

Title: Magazine
Description: The art style of magazines falls under commercial and graphic design. The medium is primarily print, with a composition focused on layout design. Colors vary widely based on the magazine's content and theme. Key artists in this field include Alexey Brodovitch and Herb Lubalin.

Title: Maggi Hambling
Description: Renowned for her provocative and abstract works, Maggi Hambling's art can be associated with the Expressionism and Contemporary art styles. She primarily uses painting as a medium and often focuses on outdoor environments with natural lighting and vibrant color schemes.

Title: Magic Realism
Description: Magic realism, an art style often associated with Surrealism and Symbolism, presents realistic objects in unreal contexts, creating an eerie mood. Commonly, the medium for Magic realism is painting. Notable artists within this style include Frida Kahlo and Salvador Dali.

Title: Magic the Gathering Card
Description: The art style seen in Magic the Gathering Cards is primarily fantasy and illustrative, expressed through digital art. The compositions depict characters and settings from the game, using rich color schemes to create an imaginative mood. Key artists related to this concept are Christopher Rush and Mark Tedin.

Title: Maia Flore
Description: Maia Flore, a French photographer, is known for her surrealistic and whimsical visual language. Her art dissects reality and transforms it into her imaginative world, often using vivid colors. She works in both indoor and outdoor settings, under natural or artificial light.

Title: Makoto Shinkai
Description: Makoto Shinkai, a Japanese director, is renowned for his distinctive animation style in the field of Anime. His detailed and photorealistic animation provides a unique exploration of life, relationships, and environment.

Title: Malcolm Teasdale
Description: Malcolm Teasdale, a British artist, is recognized for his Impressionistic and Social Realist style. Using a muted colour scheme, he portrayed the industrial urban scenes and people's lives. His art provides a narrative exploration of everyday life in his surroundings.

Title: Mali Empire Fashion
Description: Mali Empire Fashion refers to the distinctive artistic design of clothing and textiles in the Mali Empire, characterized by vibrant colors and intricate patterns. It mirrors the broader artistic heritage of West Africa.

Title: Malick Sidibe
Description: Malick Sidibe, an African photographer, is celebrated for his black and white and documentary-style photography. Working in the studio and outdoor, his compositions are candid and realistic, often encapsulating the spirit and culture of post-colonial Mali.

Title: Mamoru Oshii
Description: Mamoru Oshii is renowned for his striking visual style in the field of animation, transcending typical trends of anime. His creations often embed darker moods and relay a dystopian narrative, observed in prominent sub-genres including Mecha and Cyberpunk art styles.

Title: Man Ray
Description: Man Ray is best known for his unique art style, encompassing a blend of Dada, Surrealism, and Avant-Garde. His works primarily incorporate photography and offer abstract compositions that evoke a dreamy, contemplative mood.

Title: Mandala
Description: The Mandala art style is centered around creating symmetrical, geometric patterns, often seen in painting and rich, multifarious colors. With roots in spiritual practices, these artworks are serene, tranquil, and profoundly symbolic.

Title: Mandy Disher
Description: Mandy Disher is known for her signature approach to nature and macro photography. She typically captures close-ups in natural lighting and highlights their vibrant colors. Her art style can be classified as a blend of nature, macro, and contemporary.

Title: Manuscript
Description: The Manuscript art style refers to the integration of illustrative and calligraphic elements in medieval book design. Practically crafted in ink, manuscript artworks have a distinct monochromatic color scheme and a composition balance between text and illustration.

Title: Mao Hamaguchi
Description: Mao Hamaguchi is renowned for her unique style in the world of Manga art. Predominantly a digital artist, she beautifully blends her Manga with a traditional Japanese flavor. Her designs share commonalities with Takeshi Obata, Akira Toriyama, and Hiromu Arakawa.

Title: Map
Description: Map art style primarily includes cartographic and fantasy art. Mixed Media is often employed, focusing on geographical composition. Known artists of this art form include Edward Tufte, Matthew Cusick, and Ingrid Dabringer.

Title: Marbling
Description: Marbling is a form of abstract art, with paper marbling being particularly prominent. Utilizing paint as a medium, it is characterized by multicolored, fluid compositions. Notable artists include Anne Chambers, Ann Muir, and Regina St. John.

Title: Marc Chagall
Description: Marc Chagall is famous for his ethereal style, blending Surrealism with Symbolism. Commonly utilizing paint, his work emanates a dreamy mood set in low-lit dreamscapes, with vivid, asymmetrical compositions. Artists who share his artistic sensibilities include Picasso, Kandinsky, and Matisse.

Title: Marc Davis
Description: Marc Davis, a legend in character design and animation, primarily used sketch as his medium. His works often showcased a fantastical mood set within an animated world. Davis’ style resonates with the works of Ollie Johnston, Walt Disney, and Frank Thomas.

Title: Marc Jacobs
Description: Marc Jacobs is a prominent American fashion designer known for his unique style. His design philosophy encompasses a blend of high-end fashion with streetwear elements. His compositions often hold a balance with symmetrical designs.

Title: Marc Lagrange
Description: Marc Lagrange was a famed Belgian photographer well-known for his monochrome, fine art photography. His portraits often harbored a melancholic mood, shot under low-light conditions. The subjects of his photography, captured figuratively, were generally pictured in a studio environment.

Title: Marc Quinn
Description: Marc Quinn is a British contemporary artist, best known for his provocative sculptures and installations. His work typically pushes boundaries using abstract compositions, featuring a bold, multi-colored palette. His creations are often exhibited in art galleries.

Title: Marc Silvestri
Description: Marc Silvestri is an American comic book artist famous for his dynamic superhero and fantasy illustrations. His work typically features high contrast colors to create drama. He is among the prominent names in comic art alongside Jim Lee and Todd McFarlane.

Title: Marc Simonetti
Description: Marc Simonetti is a celebrated concept artist known for his vivid fantasy and sci-fi digital artwork. He is adroit in creating dramatic lighting and mysterious moods and is recognized for his ability to capture unique perspectives in his compositions.

Title: Marcel Breuer
Description: Marcel Breuer was a prominent modernist architect and designer. A member of the Bauhaus school, his works embodied the philosophies of the movement, characterized by functionality, simplicity, and the use of modern materials like steel and concrete. His style notably influenced modern architecture.

Title: Marcel Duchamp
Description: Marcel Duchamp was a radical and influential 20th-century artist who played key roles in the development of Dadaism and conceptual art. His works often challenge conventional notions of art, using sophisticated puns and plays on words, and often provoking the viewer's perceptions of art and aesthetics.

Title: Marcel Wanders
Description: Marcel Wanders is recognised for his prolific contributions to contemporary design, particularly in his creation of artistic and elaborate furniture and product designs. His works are characterized by a playful use of form and color, with intricate detailed patterns and vibrant color schemes.

Title: Marcin Sobas
Description: Marcin Sobas is a landscape photographer known for his unique and minimalistic approach to nature photography. His works display a strong sense of balance, often making striking use of natural light to highlight his subjects amidst the vast landscapes.

Title: Marco Mazzoni
Description: Marco Mazzoni is a surrealist artist known for his detailed and often haunting drawings. His works predominantly feature flora and fauna, rendered in a monochrome palette, often invoking surreal and unsettling narratives within the viewer.

Title: Margaret Bourke-White
Description: Margaret Bourke-White was an American photographer known for her extensive contributions to photojournalism. Her black and white photography style, often with clever use of both natural and artificial lighting, made her a pioneer in the area of documentary photography.

Title: Margaret Keane
Description: American artist Margaret Keane is known for her distinctive painting style, characterized by big-eyed figures. Her work is considered a blend of pop surrealism and lowbrow art. Keane's use of vibrant and contrasting colors, along with tragicomic mood, added a whole new dimension to subject portrayals.

Title: Margaret Olley
Description: Margaret Olley was an Australian painter known for her impressionist-style still life and interior paintings. Her work often showcased bright and pastel colors and provided tranquil moods. Her art mainly depicted her home's interior and still lifes.

Title: Margaret Preston
Description: Australian artist Margaret Preston is celebrated for her innovative approach to printmaking and painting. Her work is largely associated with strong forms, vivid colors, and optimistic moods. Preston's contribution to modernism and still life is significant in Australian art history.

Title: Maria Lassnig
Description: Austrian painter Maria Lassnig is recognized for her introspective and emotional art. Her style is a fusion of abstract expressionism and surrealism. Maria's work, known for its intense, dramatic colors and compositions focusing on body-awareness, seeks to express the reality of human sensation.

Title: Marianna Rothen
Description: Marianna Rothen is a professional photographer best known for her modern, conceptual art style mainly working in monochrome. Her works often utilise natural lighting and explore themes of femininity and domesticity.

Title: Marianne Breslauer
Description: Marianne Breslauer was a photographer known for her modern and documentary style photography. Her works are predominantly monochrome, featuring contrasty lighting and intimate, snapshot-like images of women and cityscapes.

Title: Marianne Stokes
Description: Marianne Stokes was a painter recognized for her pre-raphaelite and symbolist art style. Her romantic, dynamic compositions often featured natural environments and soft lighting. She predominantly used earth tone colors in her paintings.

Title: Marie Ellenrieder
Description: Marie Ellenrieder was a neoclassicist painter known for her serene yet symmetrical compositions depicting religious themes. Her art often used chiaroscuro lighting effects and a muted color palette.

Title: Marie Laurencin
Description: Marie Laurencin was a painter associated with the Cubist and Fauvist art styles. Her work is characterized by dreamy, non-geometric compositions in pastel colors and abstract environments.

Title: Marie Severin
Description: Marie Severin was a known American comics artist and colorist, mostly associated with the Marvel Comics. Her art style is predominantly categorized as 'Comic Art'. The medium primarily used is illustration, with rapid dynamism and vibrant colors. Her compositions primarily involve panels, framing particular scenes or actions.

Title: Marilyn Minter
Description: Marilyn Minter is a contemporary American artist known for her photorealist paintings, photographs, and video works. Her themes often include the contrasting ideas of beauty and decadence. She typically uses a metallic color palette, and her compositions usually include a close-up presentation of the subjects.

Title: Marina Abramovic
Description: Marina Abramovic is a Serbian performance artist. Her works often explore the relationship between performer and audience, the limits of the body, and the possibilities of the mind. Her style is classified as Performance and Conceptual Art, with an intense mood as she often challenges physical and psychological boundaries.

Title: Mario Bava
Description: Mario Bava was an Italian film director, known for his unique visual style heavily influenced by Gothic and Surrealism styles. His films often employ saturated colors, low light, and create a mysterious mood, transporting viewers into dream-like scenarios filled with eerie imagery.

Title: Mario Giacomelli
Description: Mario Giacomelli was an Italian photographer, recognized for his abstracted black and white landscapes and his graphic understanding of the human form. His style evokes elements of Documentary Photography and Abstract Expressionism. The compositions are often high contrast, implying a profound depth in his monochrome photographs.

Title: Mario Sanchez Nevado
Description: Mario Sanchez Nevado is known for his surrealistic and symbolic digital art. His works often display a mysterious mood portrayed through vivid colors and abstract compositions.

Title: Mario Testino
Description: Mario Testino is a fashion and portrait photographer known for his elegant style. He often uses natural lighting, bright colors, and staged compositions in his works.

Title: Marjane Satrapi
Description: Marjane Satrapi is a graphic novelist recognized for her provocative illustrated style. Her work is often presented in black-and-white with sequential composition.

Title: Marjorie Miller
Description: Marjorie Miller is known for her modernist painting style. Her art often represents tranquil moods through earthy colors, set in outdoor environments with a naturalistic composition.

Title: Mark Bradford
Description: Mark Bradford is admired for his abstract expressionistic style. His mixed media artwork often conveys an agitated mood through a multi-colored, layered composition.

Title: Mark Briscoe
Description: Mark Briscoe is known for his Impressionist oil paintings. His works are mostly set in rural landscapes, using vivid colors to create a calm, peaceful mood. His compositions typically use a landscape orientation, capturing the natural beauty of his surroundings.

Title: Mark Brooks
Description: Mark Brooks is a contemporary artist best known for his works featuring a realistic portrayal of superheros. His digital paintings use saturated colors and dramatic lighting. His compositions often incorporate multiple perspectives, reinforcing the dynamic nature of the scenes he illustrates.

Title: Mark Catesby
Description: Mark Catesby was a naturalist and painter renowned for his scientific illustrations. His works, primarily in watercolor, often portray wildlife in earthy tones. His compositions are systematic and scientific, capturing the natural world in minute detail.

Title: Mark Demsteader
Description: Mark Demsteader is celebrated for his realistic contemporary paintings, typically set in a studio environment. His works are often monochromatic in color, using chiaroscuro to create depth and shadow. His compositions are figurative and reflective, capturing the human form in a thoughtful and studied manner.

Title: Mark Gertler
Description: Mark Gertler was an Expressionist painter known for his portraiture. His paintings, often created in a studio environment, are characteristically rendered in warm colors with subdued lighting. They convey a mood of melancholy. His compositions focus on centralized forms, portraying subjects that often appear weighted with emotion.

Title: Mark Henson
Description: Mark Henson is a painter known for his psychedelic and visionary art style. His compositions are distinctive, known for vibrant colors and intricate, detail-oriented depictions.

Title: Mark Keathley
Description: Mark Keathley is a painter specializing in Realism and Landscape Art. His works often illustrate rural environments, emphasizing a peaceful mood, and are characterized by balanced composition.

Title: Mark Kostabi
Description: Mark Kostabi is noted for his contributions to Pop Art and Surrealism. His paintings often feature a monochrome color scheme and geometric compositions, inspired by society and culture.

Title: Mark Lague
Description: Mark Lague is an impressionist painter known for his Urban Art. His works often depict brightly colored urban environments, influenced by natural lighting and perspective-focused composition.

Title: Mark Rothko
Description: Mark Rothko was an influential figure in the Abstract Expressionism movement. His paintings are characterized by their non-objective compositions and muted color schemes, focusing more on emotion than representation.

Title: Mark Ryden
Description: Mark Ryden is a renowned artist known for his unique style of pop-surrealism. His art is characterized by vivid colors, and they often evoke a sense of mystery. His painting compositions are complex, often filled with symbolism and hidden messages.

Title: Mark Seliger
Description: Mark Seliger is famous as a noteworthy photographer proficient in portraiture and fashion photography. His work is characterized by high contrast lighting, giving depth to his photos. The compositions of his photographs are focused, presenting his subjects in their natural element.

Title: Mark Steinmetz
Description: Mark Steinmetz is a well-known name in the world of documentary and street photography. He primarily utilizes natural light for his captures and emphasizes the humanistic mood. The composition of his photos is highlighted by their simplicity, focusing on the subject.

Title: Mark Tobey
Description: Mark Tobey, associated with abstract expressionism and mysticism, created unique paintings, often with a reflective mood. His use of a usually monochromatic color scheme depicts a busy composition, crammed with fine intricate details that are signature to his style.

Title: Marker
Description: Marker art style relies on the usage of marker pens for creating vibrant artworks. It is often associated with styles such as doodling, illustration, and cartoon. The compositions are usually freeform, allowing artists to experiment with flows and lines, highlighting the use of multiple colors.

Title: Marker Drawing
Description: Marker drawing is a versatile art style where artists employ markers to express creativity on paper. The style can be multi-colored and utilizes a variety of compositions. It's commonly seen in cartooning, manga, doodling, and illustrations.

Title: Marko Manev
Description: Marko Manev is an artist known for his minimalist and pop art style. His digital compositions often embrace a monochrome color scheme and create surreal moods. The arrangement of his work is typically simplified, drawing focus to the central theme.

Title: Marlene Dumas
Description: Marlene Dumas is a noted painter for her figurative and abstract-expressionistic style. She predominantly works with oil paint and is known for her muted color palette. Her compositions, often distorted, evoke strong emotional responses.

Title: Marquetry
Description: Marquetry refers to an art style that involves the inlaying of different woods to create intricate patterns or pictures. Often geometric in composition, it is a form of wood art. Notable artists include André-Charles Boulle and Pierre Gole.

Title: Marta Bevacqua
Description: Marta Bevacqua is a prominent photographer known for her intimate portrait and fashion photography. Favoring natural environments and lighting, her work features soft tones and close-up compositions, creating a sense of naturalistic, intimate connection.

Title: Martha Rosler
Description: Martha Rosler is recognized for her works in conceptual art and feminist art, primarily using photography as the medium. Her style often encompasses elements of photomontage and performance art. It's noted for its political mood and the use of juxtaposition in composition.

Title: Martin Ansin
Description: Martin Ansin's art style can be categorized as Illustration combined with elements of Pop Culture Art and Graphic Design. He primarily uses digital art and is known for a vibrant color scheme.

Title: Martin Creed
Description: Martin Creed's art style revolves around minimalism and conceptual art. Known for using mixed media in his work, his pieces often exude an absurd mood with repetition as a common composition technique.

Title: Martin Deschambault
Description: Martin Deschambault is a concept artist specializing in Digital Art and Illustration. His pieces often exhibit a fantasy environment with a vivid color scheme.

Title: Martin Grelle
Description: Martin Grelle is a painter known for his artwork in Realism and Western Art. Set in nature, his paintings typically utilize natural light and project a nostalgic mood. His composition is marked by detailed portrayals.

Title: Martin Scorsese
Description: Martin Scorsese is an acclaimed director known for his distinctive style of crime and drama films, featuring complex narratives and dynamic framing. The low-key lighting and intense mood add to the atmospheric quality of his work. He often collaborates with artists like Robert De Niro and Harvey Keitel.

Title: Martin Stranka
Description: Martin Stranka is a photographer, whose work is noted for its surreal and emotive nature. Often shooting in outdoor environments, Stranka uses natural light, layered imagery and a monochromatic color scheme to create dreamlike images. His style is reminiscent of contemporary artists like Annie Leibovitz and David LaChapelle.

Title: Martin Whatson
Description: Martin Whatson is a renowned street artist known for his distinctive style that combines graffiti and stencil art. He often uses spray paint in urban environments and his work is characterized by its vivid colours and figurative compositions. Other artists in this field include Banksy and Shepard Fairey.

Title: Martin Wittfooth
Description: Martin Wittfooth is a painter specializing in surreal and fantasy art employing anthropomorphic animals as subjects in fantastical environments. His use of oil paints allows for rich color and intricate detail. His work is reminiscent of renowned surreal artists such as Salvador Dali and Rene Magritte.

Title: Martine Franck
Description: Martine Franck is noted for her documentary photography that highlights social issues around the world. Her style, characterized by natural lighting and candid compositions, captures the essence of her subjects. Franck's work is in line with other pioneers in photojournalism like Henri Cartier-Bresson and Eve Arnold.

Title: Martine Johanna
Description: Martine Johanna is known for her vivid surrealist and contemporary art style, often noted for her use of multicolor and melancholic mood. The composition of her works often focus on female figures.

Title: Martiros Saryan
Description: Martiros Saryan is celebrated for his distinctive style of modernism and impressionism. His art, often paintings, exhibits a harmonious mood brought about by his use of vibrant colors. Common themes in his compositions are landscapes and still life.

Title: Mary Blair
Description: Mary Blair is famed for her animation and concept art style with her joyfully illustrated compositions. Her art style is characterized by the use of bright colors and stylized childlike art.

Title: Mary Bradish Titcomb
Description: Known for her impressionistic realism, Mary Bradish Titcomb specialized in painting, often using a naturalistic color scheme. Her compositions are marked by peaceful depictions of American landscapes and scenes.

Title: Mary Cassatt
Description: Renowned for her intimate depictions of mother and child scenes, Mary Cassatt was a key figure in the Impressionist movement. Her paintings are marked by the use of pastel colors, creating an intimate mood.

Title: Mary Ellen Mark
Description: Mary Ellen Mark is renowned for her provocative documentary and portrait photography. Her work often represents naturalistic elements in a simplistic yet profound manner. Key artists within her field of work include Diane Arbus, Robert Frank, and Bruce Davidson.

Title: Mary Fedden
Description: Mary Fedden was a British artist known for her distinct take on modernism and still life painting. She adopted a flat composition using vivid colors which evokes a sense of solitude. Prominent artists who may have influenced her work include Pablo Picasso, Henri Matisse, and her husband Julian Trevelyan.

Title: Mary Heilmann
Description: Mary Heilmann, an influential painter recognized for her contribution to abstract expressionism and minimalism, often employs bright colors, geometric composition, expressing an energetic mood. Artists such as Willem de Kooning, Joan Mitchell, and Brice Marden relate to her artistry.

Title: Mary Jane Ansell
Description: Mary Jane Ansell uses a classical composition with soft lighting and monochrome palette to portray a melancholic mood in her realism portraits. The works of John Singer Sargent, Andrew Wyeth, and Gustave Courbet may draw parallels with hers.

Title: Mary Katrantzou
Description: Trademarks of Mary Katrantzou's fashion design include her play with print and bold compositions on textiles. Her multicolor palettes bring forth a joyful mood. Artists within her sphere of work include heavyweights like Alexander McQueen, Issey Miyake, and Vivienne Westwood.

Title: Masaaki Sasamoto
Description: Masaaki Sasamoto is a notable manga artist known for his vivid color choices and detailed compositions in his drawings, sharing stylistic similarities with artists like Katsuhiro Otomo and Hayao Miyazaki.

Title: Masaccio
Description: Masaccio, an influential painter during the Italian Renaissance, is renowned for his use of vibrant colors, linear perspective, and natural lighting in his predominantly religious paintings, resonating with works by Filippo Brunelleschi and Leon Battista Alberti.

Title: Masami Kurumada
Description: Masami Kurumada is a respected shōnen manga artist renowned for his bright and dynamic drawing compositions. His style exhibits similarities with works by Akira Toriyama and Eiichiro Oda.

Title: Masami Teraoka
Description: Masami Teraoka is distinguished for his colorful and narrative compositions seen in his Ukiyo-e style paintings, reflecting historical nuances. His artistic style exhibits parallels with Hokusai and Ando Hiroshige.

Title: Masamune Shirow
Description: Masamune Shirow is known for his complex and dark compositions in his cyberpunk manga drawings set in futuristic environments which resonates with styles depicted by Katsuhiro Otomo and Tsutomu Nihei.

Title: Matt Bors
Description: Matt Bors, a renowned cartoonist, is known for his satirical and often vibrant comic strip style of art. His work frequently employs panel-based compositions and is presented using illustration as medium.

Title: Matt Fraction
Description: Matt Fraction, an acclaimed comic book writer, is identified with a functional and sequential style of art. His work often displays varied colors within the medium of a comic, and his arrangement typically involves innovative page layouts.

Title: Matt Groening
Description: Matt Groening, a world-famous animator, is celebrated for his distinctive cartoon and simplified art. He presents works in the medium of animation, utilizing overlapping layers for composition. His creations are usually noted for their colorful appearances.

Title: Matt Molloy
Description: Matt Molloy's art style is a unique blend of photorealistic and 'Smeared Sky' styles, achieved through long exposure combinations in his photography. His work often showcases natural environments bathed in natural light, resulting in an art piece with rich color tones.

Title: Matt Wagner
Description: Matt Wagner, a famed comic book writer, applies a neo-noir and fantasy art style to his works, which are often marked by high contrast in colors. His arrangement typically includes dynamic, interchanging panels within the medium of a comic book.

Title: Matthew Barney
Description: Matthew Barney is a contemporary artist known for his multimedia approach. His work often involves film, sculpture, and performance art, pushing the limits of the body and material in his complex narrative structures.

Title: Matthias Jung
Description: Matthias Jung is known for his surreal and contemporary digital artwork. He often employs montage techniques to create fantastical architectures that defy reality, much like surrealist artists such as René Magritte and Salvador Dalí.

Title: Mattias Adolfsson
Description: Mattias Adolfsson is an illustrator who is renowned for his densely populated drawings filled with intricacies. His style is often compared to cartooning or comic art, and his typically vibrant use of color adds extravagance to his creations.

Title: Maurice De Vlaminck
Description: Maurice de Vlaminck was a key figure in the Fauvist movement. His vibrant and impassioned paintings are characterized by exaggerated colors and vigorous brushwork. He also dabbled in Cubism later in his career.

Title: Maurice Denis
Description: Maurice Denis was a French painter and writer associated with the Symbolist and Nabis movements. His artwork often features muted colors and symbolic compositions, primarily focusing on religious and mythological themes.

Title: Maurice Prendergast
Description: Maurice Prendergast was an American painter noted for his vibrant, loosely painted scenes of public life. His art style is largely associated with Post-Impressionism and Modernism, using a colorful palette.

Title: Maurice Sapiro
Description: Maurice Sapiro is a contemporary American painter known for his highly realistic, impressionistic landscapes. He uses natural lighting and employs a naturalistic color scheme in his artworks.

Title: Maurice Sendak
Description: Maurice Sendak was an American writer and illustrator, best known for his work in children's literature. His art style is recognised for its detailed illustrations and whimsical mood set in varied color schemes.

Title: Maurice Tabard
Description: Maurice Tabard was a French photographer noted for his surrealist montages and experimental use of light. His compositions often merge real and abstract environments.

Title: Maurice Utrillo
Description: Maurice Utrillo was a French painter who is associated with Naïve Art and Post-Impressionism. His works are characterised by their architectural compositions, warm color schemes, and urban environments.

Title: Maurits Cornelis Escher
Description: Maurits Cornelis Escher was a Dutch graphic artist whose innovative use of tessellations and geometrical distortions were significant in the development of the Math Art genre. His works are characterized by their intricate geometric patterns, metamorphosis, and mind-bending perspectives.

Title: Maurizio Cattelan
Description: Maurizio Cattelan is a renowned Italian artist known for his satirical and provocative techniques. His works often mock established symbols of power and authority through conceptual and figurative compositions, in a variety of mediums, but chiefly sculpture.

Title: Mawaru Penguindrum
Description: Mawaru Penguindrum is a Japanese anime series by Kunihiko Ikuhara, characterized by its unique narrative style, vibrant color scheme, and deep character development. It is known for its complex themes, mysterious mood, and strong visual storytelling.

Title: Max Dupain
Description: Max Dupain was an Australian modernist photographer noted for his expert use of natural light and emphasis on form and composition. His use of monochromatic schemes imparts a serene mood to his images, which often celebrates the ordinary moments of life.

Title: Max Ernst
Description: Max Ernst was a German artist, a prominent figure in the Dadaist and Surrealist movements. Most well-known for his dreamlike, fantasy paintings, he experimented with unconventional techniques to evoke unexpected visual effects and psychological responses.

Title: Mcbess
Description: Matthieu Bessudo, known as mcbess, is a French illustrator known for his distinctive monochromatic art style. Often, his work is digital illustration and it primarily includes figurative compositions.

Title: Mead Schaeffer
Description: Mead Schaeffer is an American artist known for his illustration and realistic art style. Primarily a painter, his works often carry figurative compositions and reflect his unique interpretation of realism.

Title: Mecha Anime
Description: Mecha Anime is a genre of Japanese animation that features robots or 'mecha'. The art style unique to this genre is manga or anime, often portrayed through animation. The compositional elements are generally futuristic.

Title: Medardo Rosso
Description: Medardo Rosso was an Italian sculptor and is seen as a key figure in linking Impressionism and Modernism. Known for his unique blend of these two styles, his sculptures are mostly figurative and represent realist human forms.

Title: Medieval
Description: Medieval art style, in its essence, includes two dominant art styles, namely Romanesque and Gothic. Primarily expressed in painting, this art style was mostly situated within religious institutions. The compositions are often hierarchical symbolizing the religious importance of figures.

Title: Medieval Architecture
Description: Medieval Architecture is characterized by grand structures prominent in the medieval period, with art styles such as Gothic, Romanesque, and Byzantine. The environment often consists of urban settings, and the mood is typically historic. The architecture is well-structured, often built for practical and defensive purposes.

Title: Medieval Fashion
Description: Medieval Fashion consists of the various ways people of the medieval times expressed themselves through clothing. The fashion was quite varied, tailored towards status and profession, from noble to peasant. The art styles associated with this concept include Gothic and Romanesque. The mood is usually historic and organized.

Title: Mega Man
Description: Mega Man is a video game known for its manga and Wanime art style. It's showcased in a vibrant, futuristic city environment with heroic moods. The prominent artist associated with Mega Man includes Keiji Inafune.

Title: Megastructure
Description: Megastructure involves the notion of extremely large artificial structures that are city-scale. The common art styles associated are Brutalist and Constructivist. The mood is futurist, displaying the potential of human achievement.

Title: Megastructure Architecture
Description: Megastructure Architecture is an art style that portrays large-scale structures dominating an urban landscape. The art styles associated are Modernist and Futurist. The composition of the structures is usually gigantic and overwhelming, depicting a sense of human achievement and dominance.

Title: Meiji Period Fashion
Description: The Meiji Period Fashion art style was prominent during the Meiji era in Japan (1868-1912), transitioning Japanese clothing from traditional kimono styles to Western fashion influences. Notable artists like Shibata Zeshin and Kawanabe Kyōsai captured these changes in their artwork.

Title: Melainotype Print
Description: The Melainotype print style is a type of early photography, produced by a process invented in the 19th century. It resulted in monochrome prints with a characteristic metallic finish. Noteworthy artists in this domain include Hamilton Smith and Luther Holman Hale.

Title: Melting Wax
Description: Melting wax as an art medium offers transformative compositions and symbolizes ephemerality. Artists like Janine Antoni and Pedro Reyes have widely used wax in their works, giving them a distinct visual element that changes over time.

Title: Meret Oppenheim
Description: Meret Oppenheim was a significant artist of the Surrealist movement known for her disturbing and abstract compositions. Her creative style, often feminist-driven, had considerable influence on her contemporaries, including Salvador Dalí and Man Ray.

Title: Meryl McMaster
Description: Meryl McMaster is known for her blend of photography and performance art. Her works often feature outdoor environments and vivid colors, reflecting her indigenous heritage. Her contemplative portraiture compositions have inspired artists like Rosie Simard and Rebecca Belmore.

Title: Metal Gear Solid
Description: The Metal Gear Solid art style is a blend of diverse genres, with Manga, Cyberpunk, and Pop Art influences. Its aesthetic features a futuristic military setting, often tense and immersive. Artists Yoji Shinkawa and Hideo Kojima have greatly contributed to this style.

Title: Metalhead Fashion
Description: The Metalhead Fashion art style takes inspiration from Punk, Goth, and Biker styles, with black being its predominant color, reflecting a rebellious spirit. Artists like Rob Halford and Ozzy Osbourne are often associated with the style.

Title: Mezzotint
Description: The Mezzotint art style is renowned for its detailed monochromatic prints. The style, often found in Rococo, Baroque, and Renaissance art, features a diffuse lighting effect. Artists such as Valentine Green and Richard Earlom have greatly contributed to this style.

Title: Mezzotint Print
Description: The Mezzotint print art style, associated with Rococo, Baroque, and Renaissance styles, provides a uniquely soft lighting effect in monochrome composition. Known for its balance, this printmaking medium has been used by artists like John Smith and James Macardell.

Title: Michael Bay
Description: Director Michael Bay is known for his unique art style seen in Action, Sci-fi, and Military films. His style is marked by high-contrast lighting within urban settings and has a dynamic mood with a fast-paced movement. Artists like Jerry Bruckheimer and Steven Spielberg are often associated with him.

Title: Michael Bierut
Description: Michael Bierut is influential in the graphic design realm, particularly with typography and digital design. He has a defined and balanced composition style. His work involves creating distinct brand identities, often for print and digital media.

Title: Michael DeForge
Description: Michael DeForge is a renowned artist in the field of Canadian comics. His work often ventures into the abstract and psychedelic art style associated with Underground Comix. His artwork predominantly features a dark, distorted composition and tends to be set in fantasy environments.

Title: Michael Graves
Description: Michael Graves is a pivotal figure in architectural design, particularly within the movements of Postmodern Architecture and New Urbanism. His designs often encompass buildings and product design, capitalising on natural light and often bearing a symmetrical composition.

Title: Michael Kaluta
Description: Michael Kaluta is a prominent artist in fantasy art and comics, renowned for his intricate illustrations. His work often evokes a mystical mood with vibrant colors, portraying highly detailed compositions set in fantasy environments.

Title: Michael Kenna
Description: Michael Kenna is a pivotal figure within the realm of fine art photography, particularly recognized for his black and white, landscape photographic style. His work cinematically captures serene moments within natural environments, favoring natural light, a monochrome color scheme, and a simplistic composition.

Title: Michael Kors
Description: Michael Kors is a world-renowned, award-winning designer of luxury accessories and ready-to-wear. His style is often considered to have a kind of upscale urban look that's also chic, minimalistic, and elegant. He typically favors neutral colors.

Title: Michael Parkes
Description: Michael Parkes is an American-born artist living in Spain who is best-known for work in the areas of fantasy art and magic realism. He uses a variety of mediums but is particularly noted for his painting. Parkes’ figurative, surreal compositions often convey complex and mystical dream worlds.

Title: Michael Shainblum
Description: Michael Shainblum is a celebrated photographer known for his stunning landscape, cityscape, and astrophotography. His style is defined by his use of wide-angle compositions, showcasing the breathtaking detail and scale of outdoor environments under natural lighting.

Title: Michael Vincent Manalo
Description: Michael Vincent Manalo is a digital artist specializing in photomanipulation and mixed media. His work often exudes an ethereal and surreal style that manipulates layered compositions to transcend ordinary images into dreamlike scenarios.

Title: Michael Wesely
Description: Michael Wesely is a German artist and photographer. He is best known for his long-exposure photography, creating images that capture the passage of time in a single frame. The lighting conditions in his photographs vary greatly due to the time-lapse nature of his compositions.

Title: Michael Whelan
Description: Michael Whelan's painting art style mostly integrates fantasy and science fiction themes with a rich color palette. It manifests a surreal mood through intricate and detail-oriented compositions. Artists like Larry Elmore, Boris Vallejo, and Chris Foss share a similar artistic approach.

Title: Michael Wolf
Description: Michael Wolf’s art style dwells within urban and documentary photography, capturing the crowded life in cities with natural lighting. His compositions often signify the congested essence of urban life. Andreas Gursky and Candida Höfer are two photographers with similar viewpoints.

Title: Michal Karcz
Description: With roots in digital art and surrealism, Michal Karcz's work largely flaunts a monochromatic color scheme with bizarre moods and absorbing compositions. Artists like Zdzisław Beksiński and Mattijn Franssen have a comparable artistic style.

Title: Michal Lisowski
Description: Michal Lisowski is renowned for his concept art and digital painting style, featuring dynamic compositions, vibrant colors, and imaginative moods. His art approach finds similarity with artists such as Sparth and Craig Mullins.

Title: Michel Gondry
Description: Michel Gondry's innovative film style embodies a whimsical mood and is often set in experimental environments. His inventive compositions distinguish him in the realm of experimental films and music videos. Artists like Charlie Kaufman and Spike Jonze stand on a parallel artistic rung.

Title: Michelangelo
Description: Michelangelo's artwork is characterized by the High Renaissance and Mannerism art styles. His main medium was sculpture, often using a monochromatic color scheme. The compositions were incredibly realistic, capturing the human form in its true essence. He is famously known for his statue of 'David' and the 'Sistine Chapel' ceiling.

Title: Michelangelo Pistoletto
Description: Michelangelo Pistoletto is often associated with the Arte Povera, Conceptual Art, and Minimalism styles. He uses mixed media in creating artworks, displaying a broad use of colors. His works are heralded for their abstract composition. Pistoletto is known for his mirror paintings and his Minus Objects.

Title: Mick Rock
Description: Mick Rock's photography takes on Photorealism and Pop Art influences. Using a multicolored palette on his pieces, he constructs a visual narrative that captures the essence of rock and roll. His captures of icons such as David Bowie, Iggy Pop, and Lou Reed defy the traditional norms and comprises his signature style.

Title: Mickalene Thomas
Description: Mickalene Thomas is a painter known for her Pop Art, Feminist Art, and Afrocentric art styles. Her works are colorful, often taking the form of collage compositions to address complexities of femininity, beauty, race, and gender. Notable works include 'Le Dejeuner sur l’herbe: Les Trois Femmes Noires'.

Title: Midcentury Fashion
Description: Midcentury Fashion art style converges at the intersection of Fashion Illustration and Pop Art. Using textile as the medium, the designers focused on monochromatic to highlight the sleek and sophisticated designs. Guided by a realistic composition, this style was championed by fashion figures such as Christian Dior and Coco Chanel.

Title: Middle Ages Fashion
Description: Middle Ages Fashion art style is characterized by its focus on clothing in the Middle Ages. Illustrative mediums are typically used, with works often depicted in earth tones. Dominant art styles include Gothic, Renaissance, and Byzantine styles. Prominent artists in this area include Hans Holbein the Younger, Jean Fouquet, and Lucas Cranach the Elder.

Title: Midjourney
Description: Midjourney art style refers to an art concept that captures moments or entities in the middle of a journey, often using photography. The style is often linked to Surrealism or Contemporary art, presenting scenes with vibrant colors, natural lighting, and a melancholic mood. Artists like Gregory Crewdson and Zhang Jia portray this theme effectively in their work.

Title: Miho Hirano
Description: Miho Hirano's art style is characterized by its contemporary take on Romanticism. She is a notable artist who primarily uses oil painting as a medium. Her works typically involve portraiture within an environment of idealized nature. The art pieces present a dreamy mood with soft lighting and a pastel color palette.

Title: Mike Allred
Description: Mike Allred's art style is synonymous with American New Wave and Pop Art. His work is most prominently seen in comic books, with a bold use of color and lighting. The mood conveyed in Allred's work is often dynamic, featuring fantasy environments. His skill lies in his ability to weave a story through sequential narratives.

Title: Mike Campau
Description: Mike Campau's art style is notable for its blend of photorealistic digital art and graphic design. His work often takes place in an urban environment, crafted with vibrant colors and artificial lighting. Campau's compositions often involve montage, prompting thought-provoking moods among viewers.

Title: Mike Dargas
Description: Mike Dargas is a contemporary artist specialized in hyper-realistic portraits using oil paints. His art is characterized by extraordinary details, capturing features and emotions with precision.

Title: Mike Deodato
Description: Mike Deodato is a renowned Brazilian comic book artist, known for his detailed and dramatic style in portraying superheroes.

Title: Mike Grell
Description: Mike Grell is a notable American comic book writer and artist known for his work on superhero characters and strong narrative style.

Title: Mike Judge
Description: Mike Judge is a film producer and animator known for his unique animation style in cult favorite TV shows like 'Beavis and Butt-Head', 'King of the Hill', and 'Silicon Valley'.

Title: Mike Kelley
Description: Mike Kelley was an American artist known for his eclectic style that made use of a wide range of media, including sculpture, drawing, performance, music, video, and writing.

Title: Mike Mayhew
Description: Mike Mayhew is a comic book artist known for his highly detailed, realistic style executed largely through digital art. His color use tends to be vivid and his composition graphic, often portraying superheroes in dynamic action scenes. He is known for his work on Star Wars, Vampirella, and The Amazing Spider-Man.

Title: Mike Mignola
Description: Mike Mignola is a comic book artist and writer, known for creating the comic book series Hellboy. His art style borrows from Gothic and Expressionism with a consistent use of heavy blacks, playing with shadows and contrasts. Primarily working in pen and ink, his work has a distinctive monochrome color palette, reflecting a dark and grim mood.

Title: Mike Ploog
Description: Mike Ploog is predominantly known as a comic book artist. His style is deeply anchored in the Fantasy and Horror genres, showcasing moody and dynamic scenes with twisted imagery. Working mostly in pencil and ink, Ploog utilizes a muted color palette, resulting intricate line work and distinctively darker mood.

Title: Mike Worrall
Description: Mike Worrall is an English painter known for his surrealistic art that often explores subconscious mysteries and fears. He executes this using oil painting that results in highly detailed compositions. Set in dreamlike environment with soft lighting and earth tones color scheme, his work often portrays an intriguing yet eerie mood.

Title: Mikhael Subotzky
Description: Mikhael Subotzky is a South African photographer known for his socio-political documentary-style photography. His work primarily captures urban environments, with a focus on natural lighting to depict reality as closely as possible. His candid compositions and use of vibrant colors bring out the raw, true beauty of the world around him, often highlighting the challenges of the socio-political landscape.

Title: Mikhail Larionov
Description: Mikhail Larionov was a pioneer in the Russian avant-garde. He developed a style called Rayonism, focusing on the representation of light and color in an abstract manner. He is also famous for his neo-primitive paintings.

Title: Mikhail Nesterov
Description: Mikhail Nesterov was a Russian artist associated with symbolism and realism. His work often includes a religious and spiritual theme, featuring structured compositions and a muted color palette.

Title: Mikhail Vrubel
Description: Mikhail Vrubel is a Russian symbolist artist known for his surreal and emotive invocations of mythology and fairy tales. His work is augmented with vibrant colors that emphasize the dream-like themes of his paintings.

Title: Miki Asai
Description: Miki Asai is a photographer known for her macro photography. She utilizes natural light to illuminate and draw attention to small details, creating beautiful, intimate scenes in natural colors.

Title: Mikko Lagerstedt
Description: Mikko Lagerstedt is a Finnish photographer recognized for his stunning landscape and night photography. His minimalist compositions accentuate natural beauty with cool tones, inviting viewers into mystical, low-lit scenes.

Title: Miles Aldridge
Description: Known for his vibrant and meticulously crafted frames, Miles Aldridge is a renowned photographer. His style can be eerie, often creating an underlying narrative. His works are notable for their emphasis on color and composition.

Title: Milica Golumbovic
Description: Serbian painter Milica Golumbovic's abstract art leans towards expressiveness. She employs a multitude of colors to portray her non-representational compositions, where form and color take precedence over realistic depiction.

Title: Millefiori Glass
Description: Millefiori, translating to 'thousand flowers', refers to a type of Murano glasswork, distinguished by its beautiful, flower-like patterns. This form of art is typically multi-colored and features intricate, geometric compositions.

Title: Millefleurs Tapestry
Description: Millefleurs (thousand flowers) is a style of medieval tapestry highlighted by its background densely covered with a multitude of small flowers. These pictorial works often depict an outdoor setting in a variety of colors.

Title: Milo Manara
Description: Italian cartoonist, Milo Manara, is renowned for his distinctive comic and erotic art. His works often present a sensual mood in fictional environments. The compositions often support a narrative, telling a story through his art.

Title: Minimalism
Description: Minimalism is a visual art style that emerged in the late 1950s as a reaction against the complexity of Abstract Expressionism. Focused on basic geometric shapes and monochromatic color schemes, it emphasizes simplicity, purity, and clarity of form.

Title: Minimalist Architecture
Description: Minimalist Architecture is a design style that emphasizes simplicity in form and function, devoid of ornate ornamentation. Characterized by simplicity, monochromatic color schemes, and the use of materials such as glass, steel, and concrete.

Title: Minoan Fashion
Description: Minoan Fashion art style comes from the Minoan Civilization on the island of Crete. This ancient style is characterized by vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and intricate designs as seen in sculptures, frescoes, and pottery.

Title: Miriam Schapiro
Description: Miriam Schapiro was a Canadian-born artist based in the US. Known for her role in the feminist art movement, Schapiro's style is characterized by the use of vibrant colors, collages, and patterns, often incorporating traditional 'women's work' like quilting.

Title: Miroslav Tichy
Description: Miroslav Tichy was a Czech photographer known for his impromptu and low-fi images taken with handmade cameras. His monochromatic photos, often of women in their daily routines, exhibit a melancholic mood and outsider perspective.

Title: Misha Gordin
Description: Misha Gordin's art style is rooted in Conceptual Photography. Employing the mediums of photography, he often employs monochrome color schemes. His compositions are complex and abstract, playing with perception and artifice.

Title: Miss Aniela
Description: Miss Aniela merges traditional art and photography to create dreamlike, Surrealist imagery. Her artistic style is distinguished by dramatic moods, layered compositions, and a unique blending of reality with the surreal.

Title: Miuccia Prada
Description: Miuccia Prada is renowned for her innovations in fashion design. Her designs, known for their innovative moods and futuristic compositions, redefine textile usage and blur the boundaries of fashion and art.

Title: MJ Niche
Description: The MJ Niche art style, an homage to musician Michael Jackson, is characterized by portraiture and depictions of dynamic dance movements in a bright, pop art style. Influenced by artists like Andy Warhol and Kadir Nelson, this style is often seen through mediums like painting in a colorful, figurative composition.

Title: Mob Psycho 100
Description: The Mob Psycho 100 art style pertains to the psychological thriller anime of the same name. The series displays dramatic, yet colorful artwork. Its anime and manga art style is characterized by figurative compositions with surreal imagery, brought to life through animation. Methods are in line with creators like ONE and Yuzuru Tachikawa.

Title: Mod Fashion
Description: Mod Fashion art style evolved during the 1960s, reflecting bold and minimalist aesthetics. Influenced by pop art, it often exhibits monochrome colors and geometric shapes on textile mediums. Designers who contributed to this style include Mary Quant and Pierre Cardin.

Title: Modern Architecture
Description: The Modern Architecture art style emphasizes functionalism, minimalism, and the smart use of building materials. It often presents geometric compositions within an urban environment, favoring neutral colors. Key influencers include Le Corbusier, Mies van der Rohe, and Frank Lloyd Wright.

Title: Modernism
Description: The Modernism art style incorporates various sub-styles including Impressionism, Surrealism, Cubism and more. The compositions are typically non-representational, often visually disruptive, and utilize varied color schemes. Notable artists associated with Modernism include Pablo Picasso, Salvador Dali, and Jackson Pollock.

Title: Modpunk
Description: Modpunk merges the styles of Mod (Modernist) and punk movements, exhibiting a rebellious spirit typically through vibrant, eclectic illustrations. Influential artists include Jamie Reid, Peter Blake, and David Hockney.

Title: Moe Anime
Description: Moe Anime is a category of anime that features characters in a style known as 'moe'. These characters are typically drawn in a cute and colorful style. Notable artists include Hayao Miyazaki, Akira Toriyama, and Osamu Tezuka.

Title: Moebius
Description: The term 'Moebius' refers both to the pseudonym of the French artist Jean Giraud and to the distinctive art style he developed, marked by surrealism and science fiction themes. His work is characterized by vivid, avant-garde compositions set in mystical, often futuristic environments.

Title: Moise Kisling
Description: Moise Kisling was a renowned Polish French painter known for his contributions to Cubism and Expressionism. His works often showed geometric compositions along with earthy color schemes, reflecting a pensive mood.

Title: Mokume-gane
Description: Mokume-gane is a traditional Japanese metalworking technique used to produce layered patterns, giving a wood grain or 'mokume' effect. The style reflects sophistication through metallic colors. Acknowledged artisans in the field include Denbei Shoami, Komada Ryōzan, and Sekibun.

Title: Mona Hatoum
Description: Mona Hatoum is an artist famous for her video, installation, and performance art. She employs minimalist and monochrome elements in her sculptural works. Common comparisons are made with the likes of Marina Abramovic and Ai Weiwei.

Title: Mongol Empire Fashion
Description: The artistic style of Mongol Empire Fashion represents historical and cultural art. This style, illustrated by diverse court artists of the empire, embodies the cultural diversity and historical richness of the Mongol period.

Title: Monia Merlo
Description: Monia Merlo is known for her fine art photography. Her work, often set in outdoor environments under natural lights, projects a romantic mood. The symmetrical composition and pastel color scheme are characteristics of her style. She is compared to photographers like Annie Leibovitz and Robert Mapplethorpe.

Title: Monkey Island
Description: Monkey Island is a video game distinguished by its pixel art and computer animation style. Implementing a fantasy world environment with 2D composition, this digital art style is known for its bright colors and humorous mood. Its artists include game developers like Ron Gilbert and Tim Schafer.

Title: Mononoke
Description: Mononoke embraces the anime and manga art styles. It is an animated movie characterized by its mystical mood, diverse lighting, and colorful palette set in a fantasy world. The 2D composition of this style is linked to Hayao Miyazaki and Isao Takahata, two of Japan's most established animators.

Title: Monotype
Description: Monotype is a type of printmaking where an image can only be produced once, unlike other forms of printmaking. It is often related to painting and offers a unique sense of spontaneity, involving colors transferred from a smooth surface onto paper.

Title: Monotype Print
Description: A Monotype print, a variation of the Monotype art style, involves transferring paint or ink from a smooth surface onto paper, producing a single unique impression. Artists like Paul Klee and Camille Pissarro have used this technique in their work.

Title: Moorish Architecture
Description: Moorish Architecture combines elements of Islamic, Gothic, and Renaissance design. The style is associated with the Moors, an Islamic group from North Africa. It is characterized by elaborate geometric patterns, arcades, and earthy colors in architectural structures.

Title: Mordecai Ardon
Description: Mordecai Ardon was an Israeli painter known for his surreal and symbolic artwork. Ardon's work often features vivid colors and mystical themes, with a style deeply influenced by Surrealism and Symbolism.

Title: Morris Hirshfield
Description: Morris Hirshfield was an American painter of the Naive art and Folk Art movement. His work is characterized by its simplistic, flat composition, and solid colors. His style is emblematic of self-taught art.

Title: Morris Louis
Description: Morris Louis was an influential American painter. He is closely linked with Abstract Expressionism and Color Field painting, using vivid and bright colors in his work.

Title: Mort Drucker
