Description: Mort Drucker was a renowned American caricaturist and cartoonist. His style reflects narrative compositions, often set within urban environments.

Title: Mosaic
Description: Mosaic is an art form using small pieces of tile, glass or stones, known as tesserae, arranged to create intricate images or patterns. The style originated in Ancient Greece and was notably used in Byzantine, Roman and Islamic art.

Title: Moses Soyer
Description: Moses Soyer was an American painter associated with Social Realism. His works often depicted urban scenes with a muted color palette.

Title: Moshe Safdie
Description: Moshe Safdie is a Canadian architect, most known for his works in Modernism and Postmodernism. His designs favor urban environments, emphasizing the play of natural light.

Title: Moto Hagio
Description: Moto Hagio is a Japanese manga artist, known for pioneering the genre of 'Shojo Manga'- comics primarily targeting young girls. Her distinctive art style is characterized by intricate storylines, poetic panelling, and a unique blend of the Manga, Comic Art, and Modern Art styles.

Title: Movie Poster
Description: The Movie Poster art style is a commercial art form primarily characterized by a mix of Commercial Art, Pop Art, and Graphic Design. The medium is Graphic Art with a vibrantly colorful and typographic composition, which is designed to promote films. Notable artists in this field include Saul Bass, Bob Peak, and Drew Struzan.

Title: Mudejar Architecture
Description: Mudejar Architecture is an art style prevalent in the Iberian Peninsula, characterized by the blending of Islamic Art, Gothic Art, and Romanesque Art. The medium is Architecture, with urban settings and geometric compositions. Notable structures in this style include Patio de los Leones, Torre del Oro, and Seville's Giralda.

Title: Mughal Architecture
Description: Mughal Architecture is an art style that emerged in the 16th century in the Indian subcontinent, under Mughal Empire. It's a beautiful blend of Islamic Art, Persian Art and Indian Architecture. Notable artists in this field include Ustad Ahmad Lahauri, responsible for the Taj Mahal, Mirak Mirza Ghiyas, and Ustad Isa.

Title: Mughal Empire Fashion
Description: The Mughal Empire Fashion can be traced back to the 16th to 19th centuries in the Indian subcontinent, marked by a distinctive Islamic Art style. This fashion era is known for its vibrantly colored textiles, regal mood, and courtly environment. Noteworthy patrons of Mughal Empire Fashion include emperors Akbar, Jehangir, and Shah Jahan.

Title: Mugshot
Description: Mugshot photography art style is a derivative of portrait photography and documentary styles. This genre of photography is characteristically monochrome, with a serious mood and harsh lighting. The photographs are usually taken in an indoor environment with a frontal composition.

Title: Mugshot Photography
Description: Mugshot Photography focuses on portraiture, often in black and white. They are a sub-genre of portrait photography, used primarily by law enforcement. The style is usually stark, with front-facing subject and uniform lighting.

Title: Muppet
Description: Muppet art style is a unique blend of caricature and cartoon with surrealism and pop art elements. Predominantly expressed in the medium of puppetry, the art style is characterized by its humorous mood and vibrant colors.

Title: Mural
Description: Mural art is a painting technique applied directly on a wall or ceiling. The art styles prevalent in murals are fresco, abstract, graffiti, and pop art. Murals are characteristically large-scale compositions, painted in vibrant colors, set in outdoor environments, and naturally lit.

Title: Mushishi
Description: Mushishi art style is part of the anime/manga genre, incorporating elements of traditional Japanese art, realism, and supernatural themes. It is marked by the use of earth tones with soft and dramatic lighting set in natural environments. The mood is typically mystical with spiritual compositions.

Title: Mushishi Anime
Description: Mushishi is an anime series based on the manga of the same name by Yuki Urushibara. The art style is influenced by contemporary animation and Shōnen elements, with balanced compositions and pastel color schemes that bring its supernatural, natural settings to life. The style leans on tranquillity and mystery, made possible by the use of soft lighting techniques.

Title: Muybridge Sequence
Description: Muybridge sequence is an art style primarily associated with photography. Brought to life by Eadweard Muybridge, this style captures an action in a sequence of shots in order to study motion. The compositions are sequential, each frame offering a different stage of the movement. Natural lighting is typically used to capture these images.

Title: My Hero Academia
Description: My Hero Academia is an anime series with a vibrant art style that incorporates elements from Shōnen manga. It creates a heroic mood in an urban environment through bright lighting and dynamic compositions. The animation is alive with saturated colors, reflecting the action-packed nature of the series. Its style is notably produced by Kōhei Horikoshi, Kenji Nagasaki, and Masahiro Mukai.

Title: My Neighbor Totoro
Description: My Neighbor Totoro has a characteristic Studio Ghibli style, focusing on soft color schemes, a rural environment, natural lighting, and whimsical animations. The result is a relaxed composition that sets a peaceful mood. The leading artist behind this movie is Hayao Miyazaki, known for his focus on whimsey and childhood innocence.

Title: Myles Birket Foster
Description: Myles Birket Foster was a Victorian-age English illustrator and painter known for his detailed rural scenes. His style is deeply associated with the use of watercolors, creating vivid, natural scenes. His mood is often peaceful and calm, portraying a serene vision of the Victorian English countryside.

Title: Nadar
Description: Nadar is a pseudonym for the French photographer, caricaturist, journalist, novelist and balloonist Gaspard-Félix Tournachon. He is known for his portraits of prominent figures in the mid-19th century and as a pioneer in aerial photography.

Title: Nadav Kander
Description: Nadav Kander is a London-based photographer, artist and director, known for his portraiture and landscapes. His work is marked by a hand-evoked, painterly darkness that rejects typical commercial glossiness.

Title: Naive
Description: Naive art refers to a style of artwork that is characterized by a simplistic, child-like perspective. The artwork often disregards the laws of perspective and features vibrant color schemes. Naive artists are usually self-taught, and their work is unaffected by the trends in the professional art world.

Title: Nam June Paik
Description: Nam June Paik was a Korean American artist who is considered the founder of video art. His works included a variety of mediums and were notable for their innovative use of technology and electronics. Paik’s practice highlights his engagement with mass media, technology and the arts of both Eastern and Western traditions.

Title: Nan Goldin
Description: Nan Goldin is an American photographer known for her deeply personal and candid portraiture. Goldin’s images document her own life and those of her friends and lovers, in raw and candid fashion, presenting an intimate view of their lives.

Title: Nanatsu No Taizai
Description: Nanatsu no Taizai is a popular Anime and Manga series known for its medieval fantasy setting and vibrant color palette. The art style presents an aura of adventure with its compositions featuring multiple characters.

Title: Naoki Urasawa
Description: Naoki Urasawa is a Manga artist known for his detailed imagery within his comics. Often compared to the influential Osamu Tezuka, Urasawa's work follows more realistic designs, with minimalistic background settings.

Title: Naoko Takeuchi
Description: Naoko Takeuchi is widely known as the creator of 'Sailor Moon'. Her art style, characterized by the Shōjo manga genre, comprises colorful illustrations, predominantly romantic moods, and compositions featuring female characters.

Title: Naomi Okubo
Description: Naomi Okubo's contemporary art style is characterized by calming and pastel-colored paintings. The artist typically focuses on still life compositions and interior spaces which are highly detailed and intricate.

Title: Naomi Tydeman
Description: Naomi Tydeman is known for her impressionist style of painting. The artist uses a muted color scheme and natural lighting to create an ambient mood. Her works primarily include landscapes, capturing the serene beauty of nature.

Title: Naoto Hattori
Description: Naoto Hattori, a Japanese artist, is notable for his surrealistic and abstract expressionistic style. He predominantly uses painting as his medium, creating mind-bending pieces involving multiple colors and hauntingly beautiful dreamlike environments.

Title: Napoleonic Fashion
Description: Napoleonic Fashion art style is characterized by its royal and realistic appeal, drawing inspiration from Neoclassicism. The designs manifest in the richest of tones, imbuing an atmosphere of regality and elegance. This style served as a key inspiration for innovators in the fashion industry like Vivienne Westwood and Karl Lagerfeld.

Title: Naruto
Description: The art style of 'Naruto', a popular manga series, is distinct to its genre - anime and manga. The animations are set in a vibrant and adventurous fantasy world, using iconic compositions that portray a sense of journey. The creator, Masashi Kishimoto, has greatly influenced this style.

Title: Natalia Drepina
Description: Natalia Drepina, a Russian photographer, is known for her unique finesse in fine art and conceptual photography. Her work often manifests as monochrome compositions utilizing subdued lighting, evoking a deeply melancholic mood.

Title: Natalie Shau
Description: Lithuanian artist Natalie Shau's work is characterized by a unique blend of surrealism and gothic inspirations, created in the medium of digital art. With pastel colors that contrast her often dark themes, Shau's art is set in a fantastical environment that carries a sense of mystery and intricate detailing.

Title: Nausicaä
Description: Nausicaä, a fictional character from Hayao Miyazaki's manga and anime exemplifies the visual art style of both the manga and anime medium. It focuses on fantastical elements, exaggeration, and high detail in character design.

Title: Necropunk
Description: Necropunk art style is a sub-genre of Cyberpunk, that combines Gothic and futuristic elements. Often set in a post-apocalyptic environment, it uses dark shades and is usually rendered in digital art. It projects a somber mood, using low lighting and combining organic and mechanical elements for its composition. Notable artists include H.R. Giger and Tim Burton.

Title: Needlepoint
Description: Needlepoint art style is a form of embroidery, often seen in Cross-stitch techniques, and is a type of textile art. It creates a peaceful atmosphere using intricate patterns. Notable artists in this style include Betsy Morgan and Carolyn Barrani.

Title: Neil Blevins
Description: Neil Blevins is an artist known for his conceptual and 3D style art, usually rendered in digital form. His art often features alien environments, with natural lighting conditions and a full spectrum of colors. His compositions are marked by a futuristic appeal.

Title: Neil Welliver
Description: Neil Welliver is an artist renowned for his Realism and Naturalism style paintings. His works often depict outdoor settings, under natural light, full of color. They evoke calm emotions and primarily portray landscapes.

Title: Nell Dorr
Description: Nell Dorr is a photographer known for her Pictorialism style of photography. Her works often use soft light and are usually in black and white. They primarily aim to depict portraits of people.

Title: Nelleke Pieters
Description: Nelleke Pieters is known for her fine art photography, which mainly captures the natural beauty of landscapes. The mood of her work is often ethereal, with a balanced composition and a variety of colors present. She often uses ambient light to bring a unique view to her photographs.

Title: Nene Thomas
Description: Nene Thomas is renowned for her fantasy art which is often set in imaginary worlds. Her paintings are detailed, with a variety of colors setting a mystical mood.

Title: Neo-romanticism
Description: The Neo-romanticism art style developed as a reaction to industrialization and emphasizes romantic and emotional themes, using deep shades and expressive compositions. Notable neo-romantic artists include Paul Nash, Graham Sutherland, and Henry Moore.

Title: Neoclassical Architecture
Description: Neoclassical Architecture is characterized by grandeur, simplicity and symmetrical composition. Notable architect includes Jacques-Germain Soufflot, Nicolas Ledoux, and Giuseppe Piermarini.

Title: Neoclassicism
Description: Neoclassicism is an art style influenced by the classical art of Greece and Rome. It is characterized by a formal mood, neutral colors, and balanced compositions. Notable artists include Jacques-Louis David, Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, and Angelica Kauffmann.

Title: Neofuturist Architecture
Description: Neofuturist Architecture is a late 20th to 21st-century architectural style influenced by high-tech architecture and futurism. The design aesthetics are often characterized by strong, sculptural shapes and monochrome colors in an urban environment. Artists like Zaha Hadid and Santiago Calatrava are key contributors to this style.

Title: Neolithic Fashion
Description: Neolithic Fashion refers to the clothing and style from the Neolithic era. These designs are characterized by their primitive and functional styles, using predominantly earthy colors reflecting rural environments in the new age of farming. The fashion of 'Otzi the Iceman' is one example of Neolithic fashion.

Title: Neon Genesis Evangelion
Description: Neon Genesis Evangelion is a Japanese mecha anime series with a distinctive art style. Renowned director Hideaki Anno and artist Yoshiyuki Sadamoto worked on the show, characterized by its vibrant use of color, dynamic compositions, melancholic mood, and sci-fi environment.

Title: Neri Oxman
Description: Neri Oxman is a designer known for her unique blend of bio-architecture and digital fabrication. Using 3D printing techniques, her work often simulates natural forms and structures. The color palette is usually neutral, and the designs are typically viewed in natural light to highlight their organic aesthetic.

Title: Nicholas Hely Hutchinson
Description: Nicholas Hely Hutchinson is a contemporary British artist known for his impressionistic style. His paintings, frequently set in natural, outdoor environments, are characterized by a warm, tranquil mood and feature a loose composition. The play of natural light is a key feature of his art style.

Title: Nicholas Hughes
Description: Nicholas Hughes, a prominent abstract and impressionist photographer, is known for his natural-themed photography. He often utilizes natural light and a monochrome color scheme to evoke a sense of serenity. His compositions, primarily featuring natural settings, tend to be balanced and harmonious.

Title: Nicholas Roerich
Description: Nicholas Roerich was a Russian painter closely associated with the Symbolism and Post-Impressionism art movements. His work frequently featured vibrant, dramatic, and spiritually imbued mountainous landscapes, painted in a panoramic style.

Title: Nick Alm
Description: Nick Alm is a painter who explores a blend of Realism and Impressionism in his work. His paintings often depict intimate, interior settings, with focused compositions lit through chiaroscuro techniques. He is known for using rich and warm colors.

Title: Nick Brandt
Description: Nick Brandt is a renowned wildlife photographer, celebrated for his photorealistic style. His work is characterized by symmetrical compositions, natural light, and a melancholic mood, which is typically presented in a monochrome color scheme.

Title: Nick Knight
Description: Nick Knight, a leading fashion photographer, is known for his unique blend of Modernism and Futurism. His images are characterized by bold compositions, vibrant colors, and dynamic moods, typically created under studio settings with artificial light.

Title: Nick Veasey
Description: Nick Veasey's art style is rooted in photorealism, often demonstrating a modernist aesthetic as well. His works are layered compositions with an intriguing mood, using photography as his primary medium. Other artists, like Diane Arbus, Richard Avedon, and Robert Mapplethorpe, share similar artistic approaches.

Title: Nick Walker
Description: Nick Walker’s art is characterized by street and graffiti art styles, with a provocative mood. His works are usually depicted as murals and often contain narrative compositions. He's thematically similar to artists like Banksy, Vhils, and David Choe.

Title: Nicola Samori
Description: Nicola Samori's art style, rooted in figurativism and neo-baroque aesthetics, is characterized by dark, semi-abstract compositions in his paintings. The stylistic facets of his art have parallels to the works of Guido Reni, Artemisia Gentileschi, and Caravaggio.

Title: Nicolaes Maes
Description: Nicolaes Maes was a Dutch Golden Age and Baroque painter known for his highly-detailed and peaceful art. His paintings share stylistic similarities with works from artists like Johannes Vermeer, Pieter de Hooch, and Jan Steen.

Title: Nicolaes Van Verendael
Description: Nicolaes van Verendael was a Flemish Baroque painter who excelled in intricate still life paintings. His work often evokes an elegant mood, using a symmetrical composition. He shares a stylistic lineage with Jan Brueghel the Elder, Frans Snyders, and Abraham Brueghel.

Title: Nicolas Poussin
Description: Nicolas Poussin was a French painter in the classical French Baroque style. His work often imbued with warm colors, intricate compositions, and dramatic moods. His style has influenced a multitude of artists, including Jean-Baptiste Greuze and Jacques Louis David.

Title: Nicoletta Ceccoli
Description: Nicoletta Ceccoli is a Sanmarinese illustrator known for her surrealistic, pastel-colored paintings. The compositions are mostly asymmetric, creating a sense of imbalance and mystery. Her style has similarities with artists like Mark Ryden and Audrey Kawasaki.

Title: Nier Automata
Description: Nier: Automata is an action role-playing game featuring an anime and minimalist art style. It has a melancholic aura with a monochrome color scheme and high contrasts between light and dark. The game's environment is post-apocalyptic and the designs have symmetry, resulting in some striking visuals.

Title: Nigo
Description: Nigo is a Japanese fashion designer known for his street and pop art influences. His designs often feature playful, vibrant color schemes and are set in an urban environment. The compositions showcase variety, reminiscent of the works of Pharrell Williams and KAWS.

Title: Ninjapunk
Description: Ninjapunk is a subgenre of art merging ninja-like characters and themes with a punk aesthetic, often seen in digital illustrations. The artwork frequently features an urban environment illuminated with neon colors. It's defined by its rebellious mood and dynamic composition, intertwining elements of cyberpunk, street art, and grunge styles.

Title: No Game No Life
Description: 'No Game No Life' is a popular anime and manga series known for its distinctive art style. The show is set in a colorful, fantasy world that matches its adventurous spirit. It's characterized by dramatic composition, bright and vibrant lighting conditions, and highly saturated color schemes. The creator, Yu Kamiya, has significantly influenced the style of this series.

Title: Nobuyoshi Araki
Description: Nobuyoshi Araki is a prolific Japanese photographer known for his provocative art style. His work often explores themes of eroticism and intimacy through both color and monochrome photography. Natural and studio lighting conditions contribute to the intimate mood of his pieces.

Title: Noma Bar
Description: Noma Bar is a renowned Israeli graphic designer whose artwork exemplifies the use of minimalism and negative space. His compositions often contain clever double entendre interpreted through bold, contrasting colors. The mood of his work is intelligent and thought-provoking.

Title: Norman Ackroyd
Description: Norman Ackroyd, a British painter, is best known for his monochrome landscape paintings. His art style is characterized by the natural environment and lighting, portraying a calming mood. His works mainly fall within the domain of Landscape Art and Impressionism with a realistic composition.

Title: Norman Foster
Description: Norman Foster is known for his high-tech architecture and structural expressionism. His work revolutionized the possibilities of architectural design, focusing on functionality, form, and usage of advanced materials.

Title: Norman Rockwell
Description: Norman Rockwell is an iconic American painter. His work captures everyday life in a realist yet idealized approach, characterized by narrative composition, vivid colors, and a feeling of nostalgia.

Title: Normcore Fashion
Description: The normcore fashion style is characterized by its adherence to simplicity, intentionally choosing plain and unpretentious clothing. It's often described as minimalist, and generally features neutral colors and a casual mood.

Title: Octavio Ocampo
Description: Octavio Ocampo is known for his surrealistic and metamorphic paintings where details fuse into a larger image. His style is characterized by multifaceted composition and a dreamy mood.

Title: Octopath Traveler
Description: The game 'Octopath Traveler' offers a unique mix of classic pixel art and HD-2D art. It's characterized by layered composition, vibrant colors, dramatic lighting, and an adventurous mood set in a virtual environment.

Title: Odd Nerdrum
Description: Odd Nerdrum's art style is characterized by figuration in a post-modern era with a personal style recognized as Kitsch. His works are often dark-toned, with a melancholic mood blending with narrative composition.

Title: Oddworld
Description: The Oddworld art style fuses surrealistic character design and game world creation. It features vivid colors and a bizarre mood set in fantasy worlds. The dynamic composition also showcases the artist’s visual interpretation.

Title: Odeith
Description: Odeith, a prominent figure in graffiti art, is known for anamorphic and realistic compositions. His art, set in an urban environment, is characterized by spray paint medium, and frequently exhibits a high contrast color scheme.

Title: Oil Paint
Description: Oil paint as a medium has been instrumental in various art styles, including Renaissance, Impressionism, and Expressionism. Known for its vibrant colors and ability to create layered compositions, it has been used by artists like Leonardo Da Vinci and Claude Monet.

Title: Oil Painting
Description: Oil painting as an art style known for its rich colors, ability to render details, and versatility in conveying various moods. Renaissance, Impressionism, and Expressionism are some art styles that significantly used oil paint as a medium.

Title: Okami
Description: Okami is known for its unique art style heavily influenced by Japanese Sumi-e (ink wash painting) techniques. It features a color-rich environment and landscapes designed in a woodblock printing style, demonstrating vibrant and animated visuals.

Title: Okuda San Miguel
Description: Okuda San Miguel, a Spanish street artist, is best known for his geometric structures and multicolored style. His work blends pop surrealism with street art, infusing geometric forms and organic shapes with a vibrant, multicolored palette.

Title: Olafur Eliasson
Description: Olafur Eliasson is best known for his large-scale installation artworks that employ elements like light, water, and air temperature. His work is highly immersive, encouraging viewer engagement and often reflecting environmental concerns.

Title: Oleg Oprisco
Description: Oleg Oprisco is well-known for his surreal and dream-like photography. His work primarily involves portraiture, often shot in outdoor settings with natural lighting. His compositions are foreground-centric, often creating visually striking narratives.

Title: Oleg Shuplyak
Description: Oleg Shuplyak is a Ukrainian painter known for his optical illusion portrait paintings that hide secondary images within the primary image. His work is characterized by acidic color palettes and the marrying of landscape and portraiture.

Title: Olive Cotton
Description: Olive Cotton was a renowned Australian modernist and pictorialist photographer. She's known for her distinctive art photography, particularly portraiture and objects. Her nuanced compositions and reflective mood make her photos instantly recognizable.

Title: Oliver Jeffers
Description: Oliver Jeffers is a globally recognized artist and children's book illustrator known for his playful and simple compositions. His vibrant color palette and joyful mood distinguish his style, making his work engaging for both children and adults.

Title: Olivia Locher
Description: Olivia Locher is a contemporary photographer whose work incorporates elements of pop art. Her photography is known for its humorous and stylized compositions, and features a colorful palette that draws the viewer's attention to her inventive scenarios.

Title: Olivier Rousteing
Description: Olivier Rousteing is an acclaimed French fashion designer known for his significant contributions to haute couture and ready-to-wear collections. His designs exude luxury with detailed embellishments and predominantly neutral color schemes, serving to underscore the brand's opulence.

Title: One-Punch Man
Description: One-Punch Man is a popular anime and manga series known for its bright color palette and heroic mood. The composition is primarily action-based and the lighting is variable, reinforcing the dramatic and often humorous exchanges. Artists Yusuke Murata and ONE have hugely contributed to its visual style.

Title: Otl Aicher
Description: Otl Aicher's art style is rooted in Modernism and Graphic Design. His visual language often uses bold color contrast adhering to a minimalist composition. As a graphic designer, Aicher’s influence is notable, inspiring other artists like Josef Müller-Brockmann and Wim Crouwel.

Title: Ottavio Missoni
Description: Italian fashion designer Ottavio Missoni was known for his distinctive art style in Fashion Design and Textile Art. His artistic approach commonly incorporated vibrant colors and focused on stripes and zigzag patterns in textile medium. Missoni's work has inspired contemporary fashion designers such as Elsa Schiaparelli and Mary Quant.

Title: Otto Dix
Description: Known as a remarkable figure in the Expressionism and New Objectivity movements, Otto Dix's art style was characterized by realistic compositions and harsh color contrasts, oftentimes portraying a disturbing mood. He primarily worked in a painting medium, leaving a legacy that influenced artists such as George Grosz and Christian Schad.

Title: Otto Piene
Description: Otto Piene was recognized for his unique art style in Kinetic Art and Op Art. He popularized the use of smoke and fire as mediums, creating compositions with geometric patterns. His work generally features monochromatic color palettes exploring themes of light and darkness, often producing a futuristic mood. He influenced other kinetic artists like Heinz Mack and Günther Uecker.

Title: Otto Wagner
Description: Otto Wagner is known for his pivotal role in Modern Architecture and Art Nouveau. His works often have a symmetrical composition, built primarily in urban environments. His color palette tends to be neutral.

Title: Ottoman Architecture
Description: Ottoman architecture is a fusion of Islamic and Byzantine architectural elements. The style is characterized by its grand scale, natural color, and geometrical compositions. It primarily exists within urban environments, and it's brought to life by artists such as Mimar Sinan and Sedefkar Mehmed Agha.

Title: Ottoman Empire Fashion
Description: Ottoman Empire fashion is characterized by its display of luxury and vibrant colors. The style is detail-oriented, using elaborate designs and high-quality materials, often reflecting imperial and Islamic influences. Mustafa III and Lady Mary Wortley Montagu were known proponents of this style.

Title: Ozamu Tezuka
Description: Ozamu Tezuka's style in manga and anime exhibits an adventurous mood with colorful and dynamic compositions. His works often contain natural lighting and are set in fantasy worlds. Hayao Miyazaki and Osamu Dezaki are similarly associated with this art style.

Title: Ozwald Boateng
Description: Ozwald Boateng's fashion style is characterized by the essence of bespoke tailoring. His designs carry a bold color palette and an elegant mood, with immaculately tailored compositions. His style is often compared to the work of Giorgio Armani and Tom Ford.

Title: Pablo Carpio
Description: Pablo Carpio is a noted illustrator known for his digital painting and conceptual art styles. His work often portrays mysterious and fantasy environments, marked by a detailed composition, vivid colors, and dynamic lighting.

Title: Pablo Picasso
Description: Pablo Picasso was a renowned painter who is often associated with Cubism, Surrealism, and Symbolism. His abstract paintings typically feature geometric compositions, vivid multi-colored palette, and unnaturally lighted environments.

Title: Pal Szinyei Merse
Description: Pal Szinyei Merse was a Hungarian painter heavily associated with Impressionism and Realism. His paintings are often serene, with a soft color scheme, natural lighting, and natural environment. His compositions are typically figurative.

Title: Palekh
Description: Palekh entails an intricate form of miniature painting in bright and contrasted colors, usually based on fairy tales and folk stories. This enchanting art style employs a detailed composition and metaphysical lighting.

Title: Paleolithic Fashion
Description: Paleolithic Fashion refers to the style of clothing in the Paleolithic era. This prehistoric, tribal-inspired fashion comprises primarily of rustic and primitive textiles. The usage of natural materials in the composition is emblematic of this style.

Title: Palette Knife Drawing
Description: Palette knife drawing is an art style predominantly seen in painting, and is characterized by applying paint to a surface using a palette knife. Styles like Impressionism, Abstract, and Expressionism often employ this technique. The artists employ bold strokes, giving the artwork an intense mood.

Title: Pamphlet
Description: Pamphlet art style refers to the design and illustration of printed material meant for mass distribution. It blends elements of graphic design, typography and illustration. The colour schemes are diverse, aiming to attract and inform the reader. The layout of a pamphlet often focuses on functionality.

Title: Panfuturism
Description: Panfuturism art style embraces a speculative vision of the future, blending elements of Futurism, Afrofuturism, and Cyber art. It often features futuristic settings and surreal lighting, using bold and vibrant colors to create an optimistic mood.

Title: Paolo Pellegrin
Description: Paolo Pellegrin is a contemporary photographer known for his photojournalism, documentary photography, and war photography. He captures his subjects in natural lighting, in documentary settings, aiming to depict a realistic mood.

Title: Paolo Roversi
Description: Paolo Roversi is a prominent photographer known for his distinctive style in fashion and portrait photography. His work is often set in studio environments, characterized by his usage of soft lighting to create an ethereal mood.

Title: Papercutting
Description: Papercutting is a form of art style involving the cutting of paper designs. The art form has wide geographic reach, embracing many cultures and traditions, primarily seen in Chinese art. It encompasses a variety of styles like Origami, Kirigami, Scherenschnitte, and more, typically involves monochromatic color schemes, and embodies complicated patterns.

Title: Paperquilling
Description: Paperquilling or quilling is an art form that involves rolling, shaping, and glueing thin strips of paper to create complex, dimensional designs. Its styles include Quilling shapes, 3D Quilling, and Abstract Quilling. The pieces can range in color and routinely consist of coiled or curved paper.

Title: Papier-mache
Description: Papier-mache is an art form involving the use of paper in combination with a binding agent to create three-dimensional objects. It can encompass styles from Recycled Art to 3D Art and even Impressionistic art with a variety of colors and generally layered paper composition.

Title: Park Chan Wook
Description: Park Chan Wook is a renowned film director known for his distinctive visual style, making him a significant figure in the Korean New Wave cinema. His works exhibit a strong sense of cinematic realism, deploying intricate wide shots and often embodying dark, suspenseful moods.

Title: Pascal Campion
Description: Pascal Campion is a digital artist known for his heartwarming and contemporary digital art style. His drawings often depict warm, comforting colors, soft, ambient lighting with everyday domestic environments. The compositions are simple, allowing viewers to feel an immediate emotional connection to the scenes portrayed.

Title: Pascale Campion
Description: Pascale Campion is an artist known for her vibrant digital paintings and illustrations. Often featuring scenic compositions and evoking joyful moods, her style displays a certain penchant for color and light.

Title: Pastel Drawing
Description: Pastel drawing art style is often employed in Impressionism and Realism, especially for portraiture and landscapes. It typically uses vibrant colors and serene moods, having a naturalistic lighting. Renowned artists such as Edgar Degas and Mary Cassatt achieved great masterpieces using this medium.

Title: Patachitra Painting
Description: Patachitra painting art style is a form of Folk art that typically uses a bright color palette to depict narrative scenes. Taking place in rural environments, the mood of this art style is often reverent. Notable artists practicing this style include Jagannath Mohapatra and Raghurajpur.

Title: Patchwork
Description: Patchwork is an art form where pieces of fabric are sewn together to create a larger design. The style can range from folk art to abstract art with colorful, geometric patterns. The composition portrays a homely mood and is often seen indoors. Faith Ringgold is a well-known artist in this domain.

Title: Pat Steir
Description: Pat Steir is an abstract expressionist who explores a meditative and freeform style. Her works, mostly in painting, display a variable color palette. Her contemporaries include the likes of Mark Rothko and Jackson Pollock.

Title: Patrice Murciano
Description: Patrice Murciano's art style blends elements of Pop Art and Surrealism. His paintings are recognized for their vibrant color schemes and expressionistic compositions. His contemporaries include artists like Andy Warhol and Rene Magritte.

Title: Patricia Piccinini
Description: Patricia Piccinini's art is marked by her contemporary style blended with surrealism. She creates realistic sculptures often portraying human-animal hybrids, with her art style drawing similarities to artists like Jeff Koons and Ron Mueck.

Title: Patrick Caulfield
Description: Patrick Caulfield is known for his pop art and modernist style. His paintings often feature urban environments with flat colors and simplistic compositions. His art style can be compared to contemporaries like Andy Warhol and David Hockney.

Title: Patrick Demarchelier
Description: Patrick Demarchelier's photography is recognized for its contemporary and fashion-focused style. His signature style involves studio lighting and portraiture. He shares a similar art style with photographers like Peter Lindbergh and Mario Testino.

Title: Patrick Dougherty
Description: Patrick Dougherty's art style can be described as environmental art and installation. His sculptures, often outdoor and composed of organic materials, display an art style comparable to other artists such as Andy Goldsworthy and James Turrell.

Title: Patrick Kelly
Description: Known for his flair for flamboyance and storytelling, Patrick Kelly's designs often feature distinctive body proportional models and full-spectrum color scheme. His works reflect the essence of high fashion and avant-garde.

Title: Patrick Nagel
Description: Patrick Nagel's art is a unique blend of Art Deco and Pop Art principles, which are evident in his signature minimalist and saturated paintings featuring flat 2D shapes.

Title: Patrick Woodroffe
Description: Patrick Woodroffe was a renowned illustrator characterized by an incredibly unique fantastical style. His works are primarily paintings that have a vibrant color scheme and intricate, story-driven compositions.

Title: Patty Maher
Description: Patty Maher is a conceptual photographer known for her surreal, contemporary, and figurative art style. Most of her work is set in nature, lit naturally, and portrays a somber mood.

Title: Paul Barson
Description: Paul Barson's work, characterized by a unique blend of fine art, portraiture, and impressionistic styles, often elicits a contemplative mood. His compositions are heavy on symbols, using high-key lighting.

Title: Paul Cadmus
Description: Paul Cadmus was an American painter notable for his modern and social realist style, often delving into the realm of magical realism. His provocative and figurative compositions portray the complexities of modern society.

Title: Paul Catherall
Description: Paul Catherall is a British printmaker known for his striking linocut prints. His art style is grounded in printmaking, with a rational mood and geometric compositions often portraying urban landscapes.

Title: Paul Cezanne
Description: Paul Cezanne was a French artist celebrated for his innovative approach to painting. Cezanne's art style, which can be described as Post-Impressionist and an early precursor to Cubism, used composition in a structural and analytical fashion.

Title: Paul Chabas
Description: French artist Paul Chabas is celebrated for his serene style, his work largely falls under the Impressionist movement. His compositions typically feature a figurative approach, portraying primarily women and girls in different stages of life.

Title: Paul Corfield
Description: Paul Corfield is a contemporary British artist known for his vibrant, surrealistic, and abstract art. Often painted using geometric shapes, his work is marked by brilliant color schemes, influenced by Salvador Dali, Pablo Picasso, and Vincent Van Gogh.

Title: Paul Delvaux
Description: Paul Delvaux, a Belgian painter, was part of the Surrealist movement. His iconic style is marked by dreamy, muted color palettes applied in a realistic composition. Artists like Rene Magritte and Giorgio de Chirico influenced his work.

Title: Paul Fusco
Description: Paul Fusco is an American photographer known for his documentary style. His work captures real-world events in a provocative manner, maintaining a natural color scheme in candid compositions. His work is influenced by photographers like Diane Arbus and Robert Capa.

Title: Paul Gauguin
Description: Paul Gauguin was a French post-Impressionist artist who developed a colorful, primitivist art style. His work radiates exotic moods, exhibiting vibrant colors applied in abstract compositions. Vincent Van Gogh and Edgar Degas influenced his work.

Title: Paul Klee
Description: Paul Klee was a Swiss-German artist known for his unique style that blends elements of expressionism and cubism. His whimsical and fantastical works exhibit geometric compositions in varied color schemes. He was influenced by artists such as Pablo Picasso and Wassily Kandinsky.

Title: Paul Laffoley
Description: Paul Laffoley is a recognized figure in visionary and conceptual art. His style often encompasses complex geometric shapes, imbued with a mystical mood. His paintings are infused with intellectual and philosophical concepts.

Title: Paul Lehr
Description: Paul Lehr was known for his science fiction and surreal art. His illustrative paintings often featured bold colors and abstract forms set against futuristic landscapes, reflecting his imaginative style.

Title: Paul McCarthy
Description: Paul McCarthy is an influential figure in performance art and installations, known for his provocative style. His work incorporates a multitude of media, often centering on deconstructed and abstract forms.

Title: Paul Nicklen
Description: Paul Nicklen is a prominent nature and wildlife photographer. His work showcases organic forms within natural environments utilizing natural lighting. Vibrant colors are a prominent feature of his captivating visual narratives.

Title: Paul Outerbridge
Description: Paul Outerbridge was a pioneer in surreal and commercial photography. His studio-based work often featured controlled lighting, focusing on still life composition. Typically shot in monochrome, his photographs blur the lines between reality and the surreal.

Title: Paul Pope
Description: Paul Pope is an American comic book artist, renowned for his distinct and dynamic graphic novel art style. His work often features a vibrant color scheme, and the compositions are detailed and energetic. Other artists in similar veins include Frank Miller, Robert Crumb, and Dave Gibbons.

Title: Paul Rand
Description: Paul Rand is a pioneering figure in American graphic design. Adopting a modernist approach, he created numerous iconic corporate identities with his distinct, simple, and effective designs. His work often features a minimal color palette. Milton Glaser, Saul Bass, and Massimo Vignelli are some other artists who work in a similar style.

Title: Paul Strand
Description: Paul Strand was an American photographer known for his work in the modernist and pictorialist art styles. His compositions often feature abstract concepts, and he majored in street photography using natural light. Alfred Stieglitz, Edward Weston, and Ansel Adams are other photographers with similar approaches.

Title: Paul Thomas Anderson
Description: Paul Thomas Anderson is an American film director known for his melancholic and postmodernist style. His films, often set in urban environments, feature deep focus compositions and make use of low-key lighting. Notable directors similar to Anderson include Quentin Tarantino, David Lynch, and Martin Scorsese.

Title: Paul Verhoeven
Description: Paul Verhoeven is a Dutch film director known for his provocative, satirical and science fiction inspired films. He employs high contrast lighting and wide shots, usually set in futuristic cityscapes. Other directors with similar styles include Ridley Scott, Stanley Kubrick, and Tim Burton.

Title: Paul Zizka
Description: Paul Zizka is an acclaimed nature photographer. His visual style is characterized by dramatic natural environments, shot under vibrant natural lighting. He often plays with color in his images, using them to convey different moods. The composition of his works is usually balanced and carefully thought out.

Title: Paula Modersohn-Becker
Description: Paula Modersohn-Becker is an important figure in the Expressionist movement. Using bold strokes and vivid colors in her paintings, she evokes emotional depth. Her art style encapsulates the rawness and emotional power of expressionism.

Title: Paula Rego
Description: Paula Rego, a renowned painter, is known for her figurative art style. Her paintings often explore thought-provoking narratives, told through her unique creative voice. Her composition is centered around weaving stories through her artwork.

Title: Paula Scher
Description: Paula Scher is a prominent figure in graphic design, known particularly for her innovative use of typography. Her art style is characterized by compelling visuals and dynamic compositions that create a powerful impact.

Title: Pebble
Description: Pebble is often associated with the minimalist art style, especially within the realm of sculpture. Artists like Noguchi Isamu have used pebbles in their work to emphasize on natural stone colors and maintain a simplistic composition aligning with the minimalist aesthetic approach.

Title: Pedro Almodovar
Description: Pedro Almodovar's movies strongly represent the Cinema of Spain art style and are especially known for their dramatic mood. His work is compared to filmmakers like Carlos Saura and Luis Buñuel.

Title: Pedro Américo
Description: Pedro Américo was a Brazilian painter whose work spanned Neoclassical, Romantic, and Academic art styles. His paintings, known for their realistic color scheme and lighting, often depict rural and urban environments.

Title: Pen and Ink
Description: Pen and Ink refers to an art style involving drawing with a pen onto paper. The style is often used in fine arts, illustrations, and graphics design, featuring a monochrome color scheme and detailed composition.

Title: Pencil Drawing
Description: Pencil drawing is an art style where an artist uses pencils to create an image on paper. It comes in various forms, from realism to sketching and doodling, typically uses a grayscale color scheme, and varies widely in composition.

Title: Pendleton Ward
Description: Pendleton Ward is renowned for his distinct cartoonish and surrealistic animation style. His work often uses a colorful palette and is done primarily in 2D. Other artists with a similar style include Rebecca Sugar and J.G. Quintel.

Title: Pentti Sammallahti
Description: Pentti Sammallahti is known for his black-and-white photography focusing on nature. His work often features symmetrical compositions and takes advantage of natural lighting. The work of Henri Cartier-Bresson and André Kertész exhibits similarities to Sammallahti's style.

Title: Perfect Blue
Description: Perfect Blue is an anime film that employs a psychological storytelling style. Its style is characterized by dark color schemes, sinister moods, and 2D compositions, set primarily in urban environments. It was directed by Satoshi Kon.

Title: Perfect Blue Anime
Description: The anime film Perfect Blue features a psychological style, characterized by dark color schemes and a sinister mood. Its 2D compositions are primarily set in urban environments. The movie was directed by Satoshi Kon.

Title: Persian Empire Fashion
Description: The fashion of the Persian Empire was noted for its richness and complex patterns. The medium used was primarily textiles. Historical and traditional styles prevailed in this era. A relevant artist of this style includes Esfandiyar Batmanghelidj.

Title: Persona 5 Strikers
Description: Persona 5 Strikers art style is reminiscent of Japanese anime and manga, characterized by the dynamic and saturated color palette. The medium is primarily digital art, with a linear composition representing the progressive storyline of the game. Key artists include Shigenori Soejima and the game developer Atlus.

Title: Pete Lloyd
Description: Pete Lloyd's art style is predominantly grounded in digital and abstract mediums. His compositions, often vivid and geometric, create an otherworldly mood. Pete Lloyd himself is a renowned artist associated with this style.

Title: Pete Souza
Description: Pete Souza's art style falls under Documentary and Portrait Photography. His works, taken in natural light, capture real life settings through the medium of photography. His compositions are typically horizontal, lending to his documentary style. Pete Souza himself is a celebrated photographer.

Title: Philippe Halsman
Description: Philippe Halsman's art style lies within the realm of Portrait and Surrealist Photography. His medium is photography, predominantly monochrome, which aids in creating an intense mood. His compositions are typically vertical, contributing to the surrealistic feel of his work.

Title: Philippe Starck
Description: Philippe Starck is a renowned designer known for his modern and postmodern design styles. His primary medium is architecture and industrial design, characterized by functional compositions and innovative moods. Philippe Starck himself is the key artist associated with this style.

Title: Phoebe Philo
Description: Phoebe Philo, a revered fashion designer, is known for her minimalist, modern, and elegant style that screams sophistication. Her compositions often feature clean lines, establishing her as a leading voice in the fashion world.

Title: Photogram
Description: Photogram art style is an abstract, in-camera style characterized by the creation of images using objects in contact with 'photo-sensitive' paper, lit directly with light. Applied light and monochrome color schemes preponderate, with notable artists such as Man Ray and László Moholy-Nagy.

Title: Photogravure
Description: Photogravure is a intaglio printmaking process undertaken to create a photo-mechanical print with unique tonalities. It often employs natural light and has a sepia-toned color scheme. Notable artists in this style include Stieglitz Alfred and Karl Klic.

Title: Pichwai Painting
Description: Pichwai painting is a traditional Indian narrative art style often recognized for its spiritual environment. This style, characterized by vibrant colors and a devotional mood, centers around painting on fabric or walls behind the deity of Shrinathji.

Title: Pictorialism
Description: Pictorialism is an art style where the photographer manipulates what might be a straightforward photographic image to create an 'artistic' image, akin to the style of impressionism in painting. Main features include soft focus, a romantic mood, and a sophisticated arrangement. Key artists include Henry Peach Robinson and Peter Henry Emerson.

Title: Pictorialism Photography
Description: Pictorialism is a photography art style that emphasizes beauty, tonality, and composition rather than the documentation of reality. Artists often use soft lighting to create an ethereal mood and planned compositions. Julia Margaret Cameron and Edward Steichen are important artists of this style.

Title: Piero Della Francesca
Description: Piero della Francesca was an Italian painter of the Early Renaissance. Known for his keen sense of observation and realism, his art often utilized a naturalistic color palette and linear perspective to create peaceful and harmonious scenes. Masaccio, Leonardo da Vinci, and Michelangelo are artists who also practiced this style.

Title: Pierre Balmain
Description: Pierre Balmain was a renowned French fashion designer known for his sophisticated elegance and haute couture style. His designs were tailored, with vibrant colors, creating an elegant mood. Christian Dior and Coco Chanel are also notable designers in this domain.

Title: Pierre Bonnard
Description: Pierre Bonnard was a French painter and printmaker known for his use of bright colors and his intricate, decorative style that had elements of Post-Impressionism and Symbolism. His works often depict interior scenes with a joyful mood and perspective distortion. Maurice Denis and Édouard Vuillard also practiced this style.

Title: Pierre Cardin
Description: Pierre Cardin was a French fashion designer known for his avant-garde, futuristic style. His designs often feature bold colors, innovative ideas, and geometric forms. Paco Rabanne and André Courrèges are also notable designers in this field.

Title: Pierre-Joseph Redoute
Description: Pierre-Joseph Redoute is renowned for the Botanical art style which is characterized by Realism and Botanical Illustration. The art is typically done using watercolor and set in a natural environment. The lighting and colors are often reflective of reality and the mood is typically peaceful.

Title: Piet Hein Eek
Description: Piet Hein Eek is a renowned Dutch designer known for his innovative and practical approach to design. He tends to explore the limits of materials and conventional wisdom, resulting in a unique take on contemporary furniture design.

Title: Piet Mondrian
Description: Piet Mondrian was a Dutch artist who became a pioneer of 20th-century abstract art. He is best known for developing the De Stijl art movement, characterised by strict geometry of horizontal and vertical lines and use of primary colors.

Title: Pieter Bruegel the Elder
Description: Pieter Bruegel the Elder was an influential artist in the Flemish Renaissance. He gained renown for his landscapes and peasant scenes, making detailed narrative compositions that often exhibited a profound sympathy for the common folk.

Title: Pinhole Lens
Description: The Pinhole lens is a simple, hole-based optical lens used to capture images in a surreal and abstract style. Often utilized in Photography, this technique creates natural lighting, and a wide variety of compositions, resulting in unique and creative images.

Title: Pinhole Photography
Description: Pinhole photography is a type of photography where a pinhole, not a lens, is used as a means to take a picture. This results in images that can be rich in depth and detail, exclusively utilizing natural light, and is often characterized by its experimental and abstract style.

Title: Pino Daeni
Description: Pino Daeni was an Italian-American artist known for his style that blended both Realism and Romanticism. His works often feature strong or sensuous women depicted in warm color palettes using painting medium. The figures in his works are composed in a way that brings out a sense of realism and romanticism, similar to artists like Bouguereau, Piombo, and Rembrandt.

Title: Piper Thibodeau
Description: Piper Thibodeau is a popular digital artist known for her cartoonistic art style set in fantasy environments. She uses vibrant color palettes to bring her character-based compositions to life. Her work can be compared to other artists like Scott C, Brendon Schumacker, and Loish, who also excel in digital arts.

Title: Pixel
Description: Pixel art style, developed in the context of computer graphics, involves creating artwork in low-resolution, where individual pixels serve as building blocks for images. This grid-based composition allows for a wide range of colors and styles. Pixel art is often associated with 8-Bit art style and has been embraced by digital artists like Eboy, Paul Robertson, and Jenn Ravenna.

Title: Pixel Drawing
Description: Pixel drawing is a type of digital art where artists design images pixel by pixel, typically using a limited color palette. Commonly found in computer graphics and iconography, its grid-based compositions allow artists to create intricate details despite the low resolutions. Recognition-worthy artists of this style are Paul Veer, Valenberg, and Mark Ferrari.

Title: Plaster
Description: Plaster art style involves the use of plaster—a medium known for its versatility and ease to work with—in creating three-dimensional works of art such as sculptures and reliefs. It often comes in an off-white color, adding to its aesthetic appeal. Artists like Auguste Rodin, Donatello, and Michelangelo have famously experimented with plaster to create stunning art pieces.

Title: Plasticine
Description: The art concept of Plasticine pertains to a moldable material used in sculpture, modeling, and stop-motion animation. It was famously employed by artists like William Harbutt and Nick Park and lends itself to a tactile, three-dimensional art style.

Title: Platon
Description: Platon's art style, named after Platon Antoniou, predominantly involves portrait photography. Known for his high-contrast photos and close-up compositions, Platon's signature style provides an intimate perspective of his subjects.

Title: Pointillism
Description: Pointillism is a painting art style associated with Impressionism and Neo-Impressionism, where artists use small, distinct dots of color to create an image. Georges Seurat and Paul Signac were among the key proponents of this vibrant, meticulous art style.

Title: Pokemon
Description: The Pokemon art style, rooted in anime, manga, and kawaii aesthetics provides a colorful, fantastical visual treat. Notable artists such as Ken Sugimori and Satoshi Tajiri have been instrumental in developing this vibrant game art style.

Title: Polaroid
Description: The Polaroid art style revolves around instant photography, characterized by its saturated colors and nostalgic mood. Renowned artists like Andy Warhol and Lucas Samaras are known to have explored this medium significantly.

Title: Polaroid Photography
Description: Polaroid Photography art style, a subgenre of Instant Photography, emphasizes aspects of nostalgia with its realistic color schemes and natural lighting. The often asymmetrical composition provides a raw and naturalistic feel. Notable artists include Andy Warhol and David Hockney.

Title: Pom Poko
Description: The Pom Poko art style is characterized by its anime roots, specifically the styles of Studio Ghibli. The medium is animation, with detailed compositions set in a saturated, adventurous rural Japan environment. The movie was directed by Isao Takahata.

Title: Ponyo
Description: The Ponyo art style features detailed compositions with a vibrant color palette, set in a fantastical seaside environment. It demonstrates the trademark anime style of Studio Ghibli films, with the movie being directed by Hayao Miyazaki.

Title: Pop
Description: The Pop art style is a subcategory of Modern and American Art. Characterized by bright colors and bold compositions, it often takes form in playful paintings set in urban environments. Notable artists in this style include Roy Lichtenstein and Andy Warhol.

Title: Pop-up Book
Description: The Pop-up Book art style showcases elements of Paper Engineering and Illustration. The medium is paper, and the colorful pieces in this style are usually joyful and three dimensional. Notable artists include Robert Sabuda and Matthew Reinhart.

Title: Porco Rosso
Description: The Porco Rosso art style is iconic of Studio Ghibli and the director Hayao Miyazaki's vision. It's a blend of anime, manga, and cartoon styles, with the usage of vivid colors and natural lighting. The art is usually set in the air, reflecting the adventurous mood of the animation. The compositions are character-centric, focusing on the protagonist, Porco Rosso.

Title: Portrait Shot Over the Shoulder
Description: A portrait shot over the shoulder features an intimate and situational art style highlighting the subject's context. Famed photographers such as Annie Leibovitz, Richard Avedon, and Steve McCurry have utilized this technique. These shots favor soft studio lighting and often display a neutral color palette.

Title: Portrait Shot With Back Lighting
Description: Back lighting in portraiture creates a very dramatic and cinematic effect, emphasizing contrast in the image. Frequent in photography, this style uses stark yet beautiful backlit subjects. Famed artists like Annie Leibovitz, Yousuf Karsh, and Peter Lindbergh commonly incorporate this technique in their works.

Title: Portrait Shot With Bottom Lighting
Description: Bottom lighting in portrait photography presents a high contrast and somewhat eerie mood. This lighting technique dramatically lights the subject from the below, creating unique shadows. Renowned artists like Eugene Smith, Irving Penn, and David Bailey have effectively used this technique.

Title: Portrait Shot With Contrasty Lighting
Description: Portraits with contrasty lighting are characterized by dramatic, high contrast illumination, yielding cinematic, photorealistic results. Renowned artists like Annie Leibovitz, Yousuf Karsh, and Richard Avedon often employ this technique to emphasize the dramatic nature of their subjects.

Title: Portrait Shot With Hard Lighting
Description: Hard Lighting Portrait art is a photographic style where the artist uses strong, direct light to create sharp contrasts and vivid highlights. This creates intense shadows, adding depth and drama to the image. Notable artists include Annie Leibovitz and Richard Avedon.

Title: Portrait Shot With Light and Shadow from Window Blinds
Description: The Chiaroscuro Portrait style uses window blinds to create a pattern of light and shadow over the subject. This mesmerizing contrast is common in Film Noir photography, and prominent artists using this style include Cindy Sherman and Edward Steichen.

Title: Portrait Shot With Neon Lighting
Description: In Neon Lighting Portrait art, photographers like Brandon Woelfel and Kate Siobhan Mulligan use vibrant neon lights to draw focus to the subject. This style is often employed in night and urban photography to create eye-catching portraits.

Title: Portrait Shot With Peach and Cyan Lighting
Description: Peach Cyan Lighting Portrait art style makes use of a unique peach and cyan color scheme. The surreal yet aesthetic tone created by this lighting combination adds depth and personality to the portrait. Artists like Marta Bevacqua and Brooke Shaden are known for using this style.

Title: Portrait Shot With Red Light
Description: The Red Light Portrait art style uses intense red light to create strong, emotional photographic portrait. Noted for its drama and intensity, the red light imparts an intriguing mood to the art piece. Artists like Platon and Eamonn Doyle have famously used this style.

Title: Portrait Shot With Side Lighting
Description: The portrait shot with side lighting art style is associated mainly with photography, in which the subject is lit from the side. This technique renders a dramatic effect as it usually creates strong shadows on the face, making the features stand out. The art style is widely used in both photorealism and stylized realism. Notable artists include George Hurrell and Annie Leibovitz.

Title: Portrait Shot With Soft Lighting
Description: The portrait shot with soft lighting art style refers to a photography technique where the subject is lit with soft, diffused light to create gentle shadows and a natural, pleasing image. This art style, most common in photorealism and stylized realism, reduces harsh shadow lines and softens textures. Renowned artists pertaining to this style are Richard Avedon and Dorothea Lange.

Title: Portrait Shot With Sunlight
Description: The portrait shot with sunlight art style involves the technique of using natural sunlight as the primary light source in a photograph. This style is often used in photorealism and stylized realism to offer natural color tones and spectacular contrasts. Artists known for employing this technique include Ansel Adams and Steve McCurry.

Title: Portrait Shot With Top Lighting
Description: The portrait shot with top lighting art style refers to photography where the source of light is directly above the subject. This can create dramatic shadows and highlights, often used in photorealism and stylized realism. Renowned artists using top lighting include Cindy Sherman and Irving Penn.

Title: Post-impressionism
Description: Post-impressionism is an art style that emerged as a reaction against Impressionism in the late 19th century. It's characterized by a desire to convey deeper emotional content, structural composition, and symbolic meanings. This style is often exhibited in painting with varied color schemes and a non-linear composition, presenting subjective moods. Notable artists include Vincent van Gogh, Paul Cézanne, Paul Gauguin, Georges Seurat, and Henri Rousseau.

Title: Post-Modern Architecture
Description: Post-Modern Architecture art style grew as a response to modernist architecural principles. It is characterized by the use of asymmetrical structures, deconstructivism, and often considers the building's context.

Title: Postage Stamp
Description: Postage Stamp art style refers to the illustration style used on postage stamps. It has evolved to include a variety of styles from Realism to Abstract, often using a compact and detailed composition.

Title: Postcard
Description: Postcard art style typically uses images that are focused and visually striking. Styles may vary from realism to abstract, and the medium often involves high-quality printing.

Title: Poster
Description: Poster art style is a form of visual communication capitalizing on bold colors and striking compositions. Highly stylized, it includes Art Nouveau, Bauhaus, and Pop Art styles.

Title: Postminimalism
Description: Postminimalism art style emerges as a reaction to minimalism, evolving towards a more complex and expressive approach. It embraces a range of media and often involves thought-provoking installations and sculptures.

Title: Postmodern Architecture
Description: Postmodern architecture is a style and movement which emerged in the 1960s as a reaction against the austerity, formality, and lack of variety of modern architecture. It is characterized by the use of non-sequential, non-traditional, and sometimes contradictory, elements to create an eclectic look.

Title: Potassium Dichromate
Description: Potassium Dichromate is often used in the art field for photographic processes, most notably in the 19th-century 'photographic drawings.' Sepia tones or a range from deep red to orange colors can be introduced to the photographs using this chemical.

Title: Pre-columbian Fashion
Description: The artistic style of pre-Columbian fashion pertains to the textiles produced in the Americas before the arrival of Columbus. It involves vibrant natural colors, and traditional designs often incorporate cultural symbols and figures.

Title: Pre-Raphaelitism
Description: Pre-Raphaelitism was an English artistic movement of the mid-19th century inspired by the close observation of nature, idealized beauty, and detailed vibrant color composition. The style also embraces natural lighting and features intricate detail, often with a dramatic narrative.

Title: Prehistoric Fashion
Description: The style of prehistoric fashion draws inspiration from the types of clothing worn in the ancient eras such as the Paleolithic, Mesolithic, and Neolithic periods. It is characterized by functional designs made from animal skins and natural fibers, often bearing basic or primitive patterns.

Title: Procedural
Description: Procedural art style involves works created with autonomous systems and based on self-governed processes. This art style primarily features inside the digital art spectrum, widely hinging on algorithms and set rules for creation.

Title: Profile View
Description: In the Profile view art style, objects or figures are drawn or painted facing sideways, a technique prominently used in ancient Egyptian art and portraiture for signifying importance. The composition is predominantly linear.

Title: Propaganda
Description: Propaganda art is typically a means to influence public opinion, often associated with political and social themes. The medium is usually print, specifically posters. The art style is provocative, intended to stir emotions.

Title: Propoganda Poster
Description: The Propaganda Poster art style is marked for its bold graphics, dramatic composition, and provocative narrative. Artists use this style to advocate specific political or social messages through a bold color palette.

Title: Psychedelic
Description: Psychedelic art is characterized by its vibrant colors, abstract imagery and complex patterns. The composition and color scheme aims to evoke a trippy, mystical mood, usually via painting. Key artists in this style include Peter Max and Victor Moscoso.

Title: Psycho-Pass
Description: The artistic style of Psycho-Pass is grounded in Cyberpunk and Anime influences. It relies on animation and is set in a futuristic cityscape. With a dark color scheme, this art creates a mood of suspense. The composition is centered around spatial elements. Prominent artists include Kazunori Iwakura, Kou Yoshinari, and Masaaki Endou.

Title: Psychobilly Fashion
Description: Psychobilly Fashion art style is characterized by its bright colored appearance with influences from Gothabilly, Rockabilly, and Punkabilly styles. The medium is commonly textile with a rebellious mood portrayed. The composition is anachronistic, mixing latest and past fashion trends. Known designers in this art style include Vivienne Westwood, John Galliano, and Jean Paul Gaultier.

Title: Psychonauts
Description: Psychonauts utilizes an art style that blends surrealism and cartoon elements that helps portray its digital worlds. The art uses sharp lighting and surreal environments to create a vivid and mystical ambience. The composition is eccentric, characterized by dreamlike landscapes and strange juxtapositions. Artists such as Peter Chan, Scott Campbell, and Erik Robson have significantly contributed to this art style.

Title: Pulp
Description: The Pulp art style, specifically Pulp Noir, is exemplified by its dramatic illustrations set in urban environments. Its composition is often low-lit, resulting in warm color tones that add depth to the scenes. The style often employs a figurative composition, focusing on characters within their environments. Artists significant to this style include Margaret Brundage, Frank R. Paul, and Norman Saunders.

Title: Pulp Novel
Description: Pulp Novel art style is linked to Pulp Noir style with its monochromatic color scheme and tense mood. This style often employs narrative composition, with attention to conveying plot through visual elements. The medium of expression is typically print, set in urban environments. Artists like Frank Frazetta, Robert McGinnis, and George Rozen are known for their work in this style.

Title: Punk Fashion
Description: Punk fashion is an art style associated with the punk subculture. It often includes brightly colored hair, ripped jeans, band t-shirts, leather jackets, and accessories like safety pins or studs. The style is rebellious, asymmetric, and often associated with street art, graffiti, and Dadaism, an early form of punk art. Major contributors to Punk fashion include Vivienne Westwood, John Lydon, and Malcolm McLaren.

Title: Pyotr Konchalovsky
Description: Pyotr Konchalovsky was a Russian painter credited for his impressionistic and post-impressionistic styles. His artworks were extremely vibrant and expressive, influenced by artists like Paul Cezanne and Vincent Van Gogh. Konchalovsky's paintings mostly consisted of portraits, landscapes, and still life.

Title: Pyrography
Description: Pyrography, also known as wood burning, is an art style where artists use heated tools to burn designs onto wood. This style is predominantly in Realism, often featuring detailed natural scenes or objects. Notable pyrography artists include Otis A. Ingram, Julie Bender, and Daniel Wright. It is typically an indoor art technique due to the controlled environment required.

Title: Pyrogravure
Description: Pyrogravure, another name for pyrography or wood burning, requires heated tools to create intricate designs on wood. Known for its realistic style, artists create high detail representations of natural scenes or objects. Renowned pyrogravure artists include Sue Walters, Woodburn King, and Stephen A. Poole. Consistent with pyrography, it's an indoor art due to the needed controlled environment.

Title: Pyropunk
Description: Pyropunk is a term that blends elements of fire and punk aesthetics. It is similar to art styles such as cyberpunk and steampunk, being visualized in digital media, with intricate compositions to evoke a sense of fantasy. The environments often feature dynamic lighting and warm colors. Artists that may portray this style include Casey Cripe, Vladimir Tsesler, and Syd Mead.

Title: Pysanky
Description: Pysanky art style is a form of Folk art that typically uses a vibrant multicolored palette to create patterned egg ornamentations. The artstyle is qualitatively symbolic and celebratory with geometric compositions dominating. No specific artists are renowned for this work as it is widely practiced as a tradition.

Title: Qajar
Description: Qajar art style, evidenced in the Persian Miniature style, uses oil painting to depict Courtly settings in a monarchical mood. The color palettes used are rich with a dramatic lighting condition. It employs portraiture compositions and artists such as Kamal ol Molk and Mirza Baba are associated with it.

Title: Qi Baishi
Description: Qi Baishi, acclaimed as an artistic genius, painted in a free flowing, spontaneous style often using Chinese ink wash technique. His art is generally monochrome, highlighting intricate details and asymmetrical compositions. Typically portraying serene, humble subjects, his work reflects his continuous pursuits of unique artistic styles.

Title: Qing Dynasty Fashion
Description: The Qing Dynasty Fashion art style is a vibrant interpretation of traditional Chinese attire. It is known for its richly colored textile arts, complex embroidery, and sumptuous silks. The dress design usually complies with a symmetric composition, and the art form overall plays a significant role in the history of Chinese fashion and culture.

Title: Quentin Blake
Description: Quentin Blake's illustrations, known for their exuberant humor and loose, energetic style, bring joy and whimsy. His art is often characterized by brightly colored, cartoon-like figures drawn with ink and watercolor. Blake's compositions are bursting with energy, augmenting the humor and emotional depth in children's literature.

Title: Quentin Tarantino
Description: Quentin Tarantino's cinematic style is an energetic blend of high-contrast lighting, vibrant colors, and intense emotional arcs. His films usually situate in urban environments, characterized by non-linear narratives and an underlying sense of tension. Tarantino's work has considerably influenced modern cinema and elevates storytelling to an art form.

Title: Quilt
Description: Quilting as an art form is immensely dynamic, spanning from elaborate narrative tapestries to minimal geometric compositions. Crafted with fabrics, these creations feature a diverse range of colors and patterns, in styles such as papplique and patchwork. Artists like Faith Ringgold and Lucy Mingo have significantly contributed to the diversification of the Quilt art style.

Title: Quilted
Description: The Quilted art style is a type of Folk and Craft Art where textiles are stitched together in a grid-like composition. Artists such as Faith Ringgold and Lucy Mingo are known for employing this style.

Title: Quint Buchholz
Description: Quint Buchholz is a painter known for his unique style of surrealism, characterized by a dreamlike environment, muted color scheme, and a melancholic mood. The simplicity in his composition further enhances the surrealistic elements of his work.

Title: Quranic
Description: The Quranic art style, closely related with Islamic Art and Calligraphy, mainly uses ink as its medium. Artists like Mohamed Zakariya and Haji Noor Deen are associated with this form of art. Geometric patterns are a common feature in the composition of Quranic art.

Title: R. Kenton Nelson
Description: R. Kenton Nelson is a painter celebrated for his Regionalism art style. His work often showcases urban environments, bright color schemes, and a melancholic mood. The overall composition in his pieces is balanced, embodying elements of his signature style.

Title: Rachel Maclean
Description: Rachel Maclean is a Digital and Video Artist known for her virtual environments, vibrant color schemes, and satirical mood. The composition of Maclean's work often follows a montage format, fusing together disjointed elements for dramatic, critical commentary.

Title: Rachel Morrison
Description: Rachel Morrison is a renowned cinematographer recognized for her contemporary and realistic art style. Her work often utilizes naturalistic lighting and an intense mood alongside wide shots. Her style has influenced film aesthetically, raising the bar for fellow cinematographers like Reed Morano and Hoyte van Hoytema.

Title: Rachel Ruysch
Description: Rachel Ruysch was a Dutch painter of the Baroque era known for her detail-oriented still life paintings. Her work, bathed in pastel colors and a serene mood, contributes significantly to the Dutch Golden Age art. Ruysch's influence can be seen in the works of artists like Maria van Oosterwijck and Jan Davidsz. de Heem.

Title: Rachel Whiteread
Description: Rachel Whiteread is an English artist noted for her contemporary, minimalist sculptures. Her work often portrays a monumental mood with a unique three-dimensional composition. She has marked her influence on fellow artists like Tracey Emin and Damien Hirst.

Title: Raf Simons
Description: Belgian fashion designer Raf Simons showcases a distinctive modernist and minimalist fashion art style with a post-punk edge. His designs emphasize structural composition, a subtle color palette, and a rebellious mood. Simons' artistry has influenced fellow fashion designers like Hedi Slimane and Miuccia Prada.

Title: Rafael Albuquerque
Description: Rafael Albuquerque is known for his pulp noir and goth-inspired art style in the medium of comic book art. His work is often high contrast, featuring dark moods, and highly dynamic compositions. Artists such as Greg Capullo, Jock, and Mike Mignola show a distinct influence from Albuquerque's stylistic elements.

Title: Rafael Lozano-Hemmer
Description: The art style of Rafael Lozano-Hemmer is most commonly associated with electronic and interactive art. His works often utilize light and shadows, often displayed in public spaces. The mood of his artworks is contemplative, provoking thought in his audiences. His compositions involve geometric intricacy and often relate to viewer's interaction.

Title: Ragnar Kjartansson
Description: Ragnar Kjartansson expresses his artistry through performance and contemporary art, often using video as his medium. His works are usually saturated with a melancholic mood, reflecting a sense of emotion and empathy.

Title: RahXephon
Description: The art style of RahXephon, a popular game and anime series, falls predominantly within the Anime and Mecha genres. Its medium is animation, featuring vibrant color schemes and science-fiction landscapes. Key artists associated with this style include Yutaka Izubuchi and Nobuteru Yuki.

Title: Raimonds Staprans
Description: A noted painter, Raimonds Staprans often incorporates the abstract expressionist and still life genres in his art. Most of his works are monochromatic paintings that capture the essence of simplicity and minimalistic aesthetics. Artists such as Mark Rothko and Edward Hopper have influenced his art style.

Title: Raimundo De Madrazo Y Garreta
Description: Raimundo de Madrazo y Garreta's art style gravitated around Realism and Portraiture. As a painter, he was known for his mastery in employing enhanced naturalism in lighting, capturing the subtleties of different textures, colors, and tones. His compositions often followed the traditional rules of classic portraiture. Artists such as Jean-Léon Gérôme and John Singer Sargent are closely associated with this style.

Title: Ralph Gibson
