There's a focus on harmony and balance, using primarily natural materials for a color scheme of natural wood and stone.

Title: Hanok Architecture
Description: Hanok Architecture represents traditional Korean houses, characterized by their signature curved roofs. This style focuses on the positioning of the house regarding its surroundings, and prioritizes the balance of the house's structure with nature. Natural wood and paper are the predominant materials used.

Title: Vintage Art
Description: Vintage art style is characterized by warm colors and soft lighting, often with a nostalgic mood. It is usually set in an urban environment and has a structured composition. Notable artists include Pablo Picasso and Andy Warhol.

Title: Punk Art
Description: Punk art style is associated with vibrant colors, harsh lighting, and a rebellious mood. It is often set in an urban environment, usually characterized by a chaotic composition. Notable artists include Banksy and Shepard Fairey.

Title: Yasuhiro Nightow
Description: Yasuhiro Nightow is a renowned Manga artist known for his dynamic compositions generating excitement. He primarily uses drawing as his medium, with art styles between Anime and Manga. He allows flexibility in color, lighting, primarily leaning towards Urban or Fantasy environments.

Title: Japanese Modern Art
Description: Japanese modern art style is a balanced and harmonious fusion of traditional and contemporary styles like Yōga and Manga. Artists like Yayoi Kusama and Takashi Murakami are associated with this art style, often creating serene moods in urban environments.

Title: Chinese Brush Painting
Description: Chinese brush painting art style revolves around the use of brush, ink, and often remaining minimalist in color. Known for its asymmetrical layout, this art style often embodies a transcendent mood set in natural environments. Important artists include Qi Baishi and Zhang Daqian.

Title: Nihonga
Description: Nihonga is a traditional Japanese painting style that often features natural landscapes, scenes from traditional literature and everyday life, using vivid and rich colors. It is characterized by the use of traditional painting methods established during the Edo and Meiji periods. The style is detailed, and can portray both indoor and outdoor environments.

Title: Traditional Japanese Art
Description: Traditional Japanese Art encompasses a wide range of art styles and media, including ancient pottery, sculpture, ink painting and calligraphy. It often includes elements of the natural landscape, scenes of the sea, mountains, flowers, and birds. It's often full of details, simple yet vibrant in terms of color, and can depict both indoor and outdoor environments.

Title: Woodblock Printing
Description: Woodblock printing is a technique that involves carving an image into a wooden block, which is then inked and used to print onto paper or fabric. This art style is most commonly associated with the ukiyo-e genre of Japanese art, and offers a wide range of color possibilities. It showcases a layered composition due to the printing process.

Title: Marine Photography
Description: Marine photography captures undersea life and underwater landscapes often utilizing the natural lighting conditions under the water. The dominant color in this style of photography is Blue, reflecting the color of the sea. This type of art often brings a serene mood to viewers and the photographers generally use a wide-angle composition to capture vast underwater scenes.

Title: Caravaggisti
Description: Caravaggisti were the followers of the late 16th-century Italian artist Caravaggio. Their work, like his, was characterized by the dramatic use of lighting, often using a technique known as chiaroscuro, and had intensely realistic depictions of physical and emotional states. Most of their work is indoor setting, usually with a focused composition, and a dark but intense color palette.

Title: Lace-making
Description: The lace-making art style is a subset of decorative and textile art made using thread. It is characterized by intricate, symmetrical patterns woven by hand or machine. Artists like John Heathcoat and Johann Conrad Sigmund are known for their lace-making.

Title: Black British Art
Description: The Black British Art style encompasses the work of Black British artists throughout the 20th and 21st century. Representing a wide range of styles from modern and abstract to conceptual art, these artists utilized expressive and dynamic color palettes. Notably, Chris Ofili, Yinka Shonibare, Sonia Boyce, Steve McQueen, and Lubaina Himid have had significant influence in this genre.

Title: Folk Architecture
Description: The art style of Folk Architecture is grounded in the Vernacular and Rustic styles. This style is characterized by the use of local materials, and is primarily found in rural environments. The architecture is often composed in a pragmatic manner, based on local traditions, materials, and skills.

Title: Traditional Architecture
Description: Traditional Architecture art style encompasses design principles from Classical, Gothic, and Romanesque architecture. Often composed symmetrically employing stone as a primary building medium, this style can be seen both in urban and rural environments. It reflects the cultural, historical, and societal values of a given period.

Title: Regional Architecture
Description: Regional Architecture art style is an adaptation of Vernacular and Modernist architecture. It incorporates locally sourced materials and is designed to be in harmony with its specific physical and cultural environment, whether urban or rural. The composition of regional architecture is often contextual, reflecting and responding to the local climate, landscape, and culture.

Title: Gothic Revival
Description: Gothic Revival is a style of art that harks back to the Gothic era, characterized by its grand buildings of towering spires, pointed arches, and elaborate details. The style was popular during the Victorian era and was used extensively in the design of churches and cathedrals.

Title: Queen Anne
Description: The Queen Anne style is a refined artistic style that was prominent during the reign of Queen Anne in England, known for its elegance, symmetry, and complexity. It often employs intricate details, decorative embellishments, and a vibrant color scheme.

Title: Second Empire
Description: The Second Empire style, named after the French Second Empire, is an eclectic art style that combines elements of Baroque, Rococo, and Neo-Renaissance. It's prominently used in architecture, featuring grand structures with detailed decorations, and a sophisticated, urban appeal.

Title: Norse
Description: Norse art style, originating from the ancient Norse people, includes a rich heritage of designs from the Scandinavian roots. Common features include interlaced patterns, animal figures, and symbolic motifs, often seen in metalwork and wood carving, reflecting a deep connection with the ancient cults and deities.

Title: Sustainability
Description: Sustainability art style, often known as eco-art, revolves around the principle of maintaining ecological balance. It includes the use of recycled materials, and organic compositions, often provoking thoughts on environmental conservation. The art style manifests as installations, sculptures, and land art, emphasizing harmony with nature.

Title: Historical Fiction
Description: The Historical Fiction art style generally captures real-life historical events or periods, blending facts with imagination. Artists might employ styles like Realism, Romanticism, or Impressionism, capturing the mood of the era through vivid colors, feelings of nostalgia, and typically figurative compositions. Works are often done via painting.

Title: Book Illustration
Description: Book Illustration style involves creating artwork that supplements text in books. The artwork usually depicts the environment and characters within the stories. Styles used may include Graphic, Realism, or Caricature. The coloring varies depending on the narrative; the composition aims to enhance the story.

Title: Enamel Painting
Description: Enamel painting is a unique style that uses powdered glass applied to a surface, which is then fired until it melts. The resulting artwork is known for its vibrant colors and high durability. It has been used in various art styles, including Realism, Miniaturism, and Portraiture, typically featuring detailed compositions.

Title: Metaphorical Art
Description: Metaphorical art style uses symbolic figures, actions or symbolic representation to express a deeper philosophical or political message. Its nature makes it closely associated with styles like Abstract, Surrealism and Symbolism. It often has a thought-provoking mood due to its profound symbolic composition.

Title: Animated TV Series
Description: The art style of Animated TV Series is quite diverse, incorporating anime, modernism, pop art or minimalism. The medium is typically digital art, with environments often set in fantasy worlds. The lighting, color, and mood vary depending on the narrative of the series, while compositions tend to be dynamic and engaging.

Title: Voodoo
Description: Voodoo art style is characterized by elements that take inspiration from the mystical and spiritual aspects of the Voodoo religion. Predominantly seen in sculpture forms, it often uses earth tones and is set in a ritual environment. Its symbolism and mystical mood plays a significant role in its primitive and outsider art style.

Title: Whimsical Illustration
Description: Whimsical Illustration is an art style full of fun and fancy, often seen in children's books and fantasy-genre art. It uses vibrant, whimsical colors to draw and tell stories in a narrative composition. The joyful mood and unusual characters are significant features of this art style.

Title: Mechanical Contraptions
Description: Mechanical Contraptions art style is all about the creation of intricate, moving or static, machine-like structures. Using a metallic color scheme, artists present geometric compositions in an industrial environment. This art style is linked with Steampunk and Kinetic art.

Title: Pulp Fiction Art
Description: Pulp Fiction Art encompasses the commercial and pop art styles that appeared on mid-20th century pulp magazine covers. This art style utilizes high-contrast lighting and vibrant, saturated colors to portray dramatic, often urban-set vignettes, in a highly illustrative medium.

Title: American Landscape
Description: American Landscape art style is characterized by its detailed and vibrant portrayal of outdoor/nature environments. Noted for its realism and often panoramic composition, use of natural light, this style creates a tranquil mood. It's closely linked with the Romanticism style, Plein Air painting and the Hudson River School.

Title: Unknown Warli Artists
Description: The art concept of the 'Unknown Warli Artists' revolves around the Warli Art, a folk and tribal art style indigenous to Maharashtra, India. This style mainly consists of monochromic paintings, often done in white on mud walls. The composition is largely geometric, using simple forms like circles, triangles and squares.

Title: Indigenous
Description: Indigenous art style encapsulates the works indigenous to particular regions, such as Aboriginal Art, Native American Art, and Maori Art. The artwork often carries symbolic representations of cultural stories, typically using carving mediums, rendered in natural color palettes.

Title: Non-Objective
Description: The non-objective art style refers to artworks that do not represent or depict a being, a place or a thing in the natural world. Notable styles include Abstract and Conceptual Art. These artworks often involve painting mediums, in a range of colors, and a composition that does not aim to represent an accurate depiction of visual reality.

Title: Creature Design
Description: Creature Design art style is a subset of character design that focuses on the creation of alien or mythical creatures. This style often uses digital art as a medium, set in fantastical environments with compositions limited only by the artist's imagination. Notable artists include Terryl Whitlatch and Carlos Huante.

Title: Western
Description: The Western art style often refers to the style prevalent in the western world, characterized by art movements like Realism, Impressionism, and Renaissance Art. This style often utilizes painting mediums, set in rural environments, narrates a story through the artwork, and predominantly uses earthy color tones creating a sombre mood.

Title: Frontier Fashion
Description: Frontier Fashion art style refers to the clothing style inspired by the American Frontier period. It is marked by practical and hardy clothing often seen in rural environments. The color scheme is natural, reflecting the environment. Notable figures include Annie Oakley and Davy Crockett.

Title: Pioneering Photography
Description: Pioneering Photography art style refers to the early period of photography, often characterized by candid compositions and natural lighting. The style played a crucial role in documentary and photojournalism. Key contributors include Louis Daguerre and Henry Fox Talbot.

Title: Beat Generation
Description: Beat Generation art style is linked to the cultural and literary movement of the mid-20th century identified with rebellious sentiments. Amazonia art style in visual arts is often associated with abstract expressionism. Key figures include Jack Kerouac and Allen Ginsberg.

Title: Natural Color Palette
Description: Natural Color Palette art style describes the use of colors observed in nature. It is associated with art styles such as realism, impressionism, and landscape art. Artists known to extensively apply this kind of color palette are Claude Monet and John Constable.

Title: Realistic Depiction of Landscapes
Description: Realistic Depiction of Landscapes art style signifies artworks representing landscapes with natural colors and balanced composition. It aligns with Realism and Landscape art, and is characteristic of the Hudson River School. Notable artists of this style include Albert Bierstadt and Thomas Cole.

Title: Modern Sculpture
Description: Modern Sculpture represents a broad period from the late 19th to the mid-20th century. It is characterized by a break from traditional subjects and styles, with artists favoring abstraction, minimalist forms, and innovative construction methods, including casting, carving, and welding. Key artists include Henry Moore and Constantin Brâncuși.

Title: Various Digital Artists
Description: Various Digital Artists represent an amalgam of modern artists who use digital mediums to create a wide array of art styles like pixel art, virtual reality, algorithmic, net art, and digital painting. These artists utilize digital software or hardware to craft their artworks, pushing the boundaries of normalcy and blurring the lines between traditional and modern digital art forms.

Title: Soviet Nonconformist Art
Description: Soviet Nonconformist Art was a movement that officially began in the mid-20th century and included artists who refused to conform to the state's rigid artistic laws. The artists boldly explored various art styles, from surrealism to conceptual art. Important features of this style include its reflection on social realities, utilitarian urbanscape, and its diversion from socialist realism.

Title: Hong Kong New Wave
Description: Hong Kong New Wave refers to a movement in cinema that emerged in the 1980s. These directors pushed boundaries with their creative storytelling approaches, often reflecting socio-political realities of Hong Kong. Aesthetically, they introduced a more complex narrative structure, dramatic moods, and visually captivating scenes, often set in urban environments.

Title: Wood
Description: Wood as an artistic medium has had a long and diversified history in the art world. Artists use techniques such as carving, turning, marquetry, pyrography, and fretwork to create complex forms and patterns. Wood art serves as a testament to human creativity and the beauty of nature’s materials, leading to unique sculptural and functional pieces.

Title: Printing Technique
Description: The Printing Technique is an art style that primarily involves creating an image on a matrix using carving and printing processes. A prominent style within this concept is Moku Hanga or Japanese woodblock printing, emphasizing layered compositions. Renowned artists like Hiroshi Yoshida and Andō Hiroshige have significantly contributed to this art style's development.

Title: MMORPG
Description: MMORPG art style incorporates immersive open-world layouts, often utilizing a digital art or concept art style. Taking place in a high fantasy setting, it utilizes a full spectrum of colors with contrastive lighting. Mood in MMORPG games art is typically adventurous, reflecting the spirit of the gameplay. Prominent artists like Yoshitaka Amano, Akihiko Yoshida or Tetsuya Nomura have contributed significantly to this style.

Title: High Fantasy
Description: High Fantasy art style is characterized by dynamic imaging, strong contrast lighting, and a full spectrum of colors to depict an epic sense of adventure. The medium used is often digital, with styles varying from illustrations to concept art. The art resonates within a fantasy world environment created by renowned artists like Frazetta, Alan Lee, and J.R.R. Tolkien.

Title: Japanese Anime
Description: The Japanese Anime art style is known for its unique 2D representation, featuring vibrant colors with urban and natural environments. The lighting setup is often contrastive, and the mood is diverse, depending on the story. The style is exemplified in works by notable artists such as Hayao Miyazaki, Mamoru Oshii, and Osamu Tezuka.

Title: Action-packed
Description: Action-packed art style is seen in anime, manga, and graphic novels, reflecting a dynamic, tense environment. Vivid colors, harsh lighting, and fragmented composition often symbolize the overlapping chaos and intensity.

Title: Formal
Description: The formal art style reflects a sense of balance, meticulous staging, subdued colors, and seriousness. Its application is commonly seen in realism, impressionism, and classicism techniques of painting.

Title: Intimate
Description: The intimate art style is characterized by warm colors, soft lighting, and close-up compositions, encapsulating private environments. This style is often seen in impressionism, expressionism, and portraiture.

Title: Cynical Realism
Description: Cynical Realism art style, prevalent in contemporary and modern art, portrays a distorted, unsettling urban environment and a gloomy color scheme that reflect a cynical mood.

Title: Environmental
Description: Environmental art is a genre that encompasses various styles and techniques, focusing on the use of natural, sustainable materials to create installations. It's often outdoors and uses an organic composition, bringing tranquility through its natural color palette. Notable practitioners include Andy Goldsworthy and Richard Long.

Title: Glamorous
Description: Glamorous art refers to a style that encompasses sophistication, elegance, and style. It is often visualized in bold color schemes and dramatic lighting, offering a stylized composition. The genre captivates the viewer with high adornment and sophistication, epitomized by artists like George Hurrell and Tamara de Lempicka.

Title: Visually Stunning
Description: The 'Visually Stunning' art concept focuses on creating a visually dynamic, energetic mood with its complex compositions and vibrant color palette. It's often dynamically lit and can be found in styles such as Surrealism, Impressionism, and Abstract Expressionism. Notable artists include Salvador Dali and Claude Monet.

Title: Parametricism
Description: Parametricism is a style within contemporary avant-garde architecture, focusing on the use of digital design and algorithmic composition to create works. Influential in the fields of digital architecture and design, it has a futuristic mood, and often uses a monochromatic color scheme.  Zaha Hadid and Patrik Schumacher are key practitioners.

Title: Activist
Description: Activist art refers to artwork meant to bring awareness or advocate for a cause. Utilizing often provocative imagery and a saturation of diverse colors, it's expressed through various styles like political and protest art. The composition is mostly figurative, focused on communicating a clear message. Notable artists include Ai Weiwei and Banksy.

Title: Fantastic Art
Description: Fantastic Art is a genre that uses visual designs to stimulate a strong emotional response from the viewer. It often presents surreal and imaginary landscapes, often painted with vibrant and bright colors. Notable artists include H. R. Giger, Roger Dean and John Martin.

Title: Ink Wash Painting
Description: Ink Wash Painting, also known as East Asian ink brush painting, focuses on the beauty of each stroke created by the artist's brush. Color mainly varies in grayscale, with black ink wash being most common. It is associated with a peaceful mood and minimalistic composition. Notable artists include Wang Xizhi, Qi Baishi, and Mi Fu.

Title: Steampunk Engineer
Description: Steampunk Engineer art style encompassing elements of steampunk and fantasy with an intriguing mood. Often depicted in sculptures, it features an asymmetrical composition and monochromatic color scheme. Notable artists include H.R. Giger, Katsuhiro Otomo, and Hayao Miyazaki.

Title: Split Light Batman
Description: Split Light Batman art style, a blend of comic and pop art, features distinct split lighting set in an urban environment. It provides a mysterious mood with its symmetrical composition and black and white color scheme. Known artists include Frank Miller, Jim Lee, and Greg Capullo.

Title: Naive Art Helicopter
Description: The Naive Art Helicopter art style, drawn from naive and folk art, typically appears in paintings and portrays a joyful mood. It uses a simplified composition, vibrant colors, and is often set against a sky backdrop. Artists such as Henri Rousseau, Alfred Wallis, and Niko Pirosmani have been instrumental in this style.

Title: Double Exposure Cowboy
Description: Double Exposure Cowboy art style merges photographic art and double exposure techniques, using natural desert lighting for a nostalgic mood. It utilizes a layered, dichromatic composition, often interpreted through photography. Represented artists involve Annie Leibovitz, Robert Frank, and Ansel Adams.

Title: Flat Icon Panda
Description: The Flat Icon Panda art style involves icon and flat designs using digital art mediums. The artwork depicts a playful mood, often in monochromatic color. Represented by a flat composition, noted artists include Susan Kare, Aaron Draplin, and Paul Rand.

Title: Fire Department Knolling
Description: Fire Department Knolling art is a form of Photography and Still Life. The art style involves carefully arranging and photographing fire department tools and equipment. The setting is typically indoors, featuring artificial light, and a multicolored scheme. Known artists for this concept include Tom Sachs and Todd McLellan.

Title: Cyberpunk City Nightlife
Description: Cyberpunk City Nightlife art is a sub-genre of Digital Art and Futurism, often showcasing urban scenes during the night, accentuated by neon lights. It creates a gritty atmosphere, with complex compositions, and is characterized by dark colors illuminated by glowing neon hues. Notable artists include Syd Mead and Yoshiyuki Takani.

Title: Close-Up Raindrop
Description: Close-Up Raindrop art is a form of Macro Photography that captures raindrops in detail, often reflecting the surrounding environment. This vibrant style is characterized for its close-framed compositions in natural settings, using the natural light. Renowned artists in the field include Andrew Osokin and Steve Wall.

Title: Future City by Sid Mead
Description: The Future City by Sid Mead art style falls under Futurism. Mead's work consists of detailed future urban cityscapes, using artificial lighting and a palette of cool colors. The mood set is imaginative, with dynamic compositions. Syd Mead is the most notable artist of this style.

Title: Futuristic Skyscraper Design
Description: Futuristic Skyscraper Design is an art style under Modernism and Futurism, primarily expressed in architecture. These designs often feature vertical emphasis and are set in urban environments. The color scheme tends to be neutral. Zaha Hadid and Norman Foster are key architects associated with this style.

Title: Hyperdrive Concept Sheet
Description: The Hyperdrive Concept Sheet art style primarily features concept art of futuristic and sci-fi themes. The medium used is digital art, set in a space environment. It tends to exhibit fluorescent lighting, a vibrant color scheme, and a detailed composition, creating an inquisitive mood. Notable artists include Ralph McQuarrie, Syd Mead, and Doug Chiang.

Title: Stained Glass Steamboat
Description: The Stained Glass Steamboat art style combines the use of stained glass elements with nautical and vintage themes. The medium is glass, often depicted in waterfront settings. The lighting is usually translucent, with a multicolored scheme and geometric compositions giving a nostalgic mood. Noteworthy artists in this style include Louis Comfort Tiffany, John La Farge, and Marc Chagall.

Title: Dreamcore Tractor
Description: The Dreamcore Tractor art style blends the dreamcore genre with rural and abstract elements. The medium is digital art, set against quiet countryside landscapes. It observes surreal lighting, a pastel color scheme, and a minimalist composition, inducing a dreamy mood. Renowned artists in this style include Salvador Dalí, René Magritte, and Max Ernst.

Title: Mars Rocket by Kurzgesagt
Description: The Mars Rocket by Kurzgesagt art style is characterized by minimalist, futuristic, and sci-fi themes. Rendered in digital art, the context is space with contrasting lighting and a vibrant palette. The composition is simplistic, creating an inspiring atmosphere. The Kurzgesagt team is notably associated with this visual style.

Title: Maximalist Flea Market
Description: The Maximalist Flea Market art style incorporates maximalist, eclectic, and vintage elements using mixed media in indoor environments. The lighting is usually artificial, with a colorful scheme, and a cluttered composition exuding a joyous mood. Prominent artists include Kaffe Fassett, Nick Cave, and Phil Hansen.

Title: Gear Mandalla
Description: Gear Mandalla art style refers to a creative expression that uses abstract and symbolic elements in a circular symmetric composition. It often uses a metallic color scheme and is predominantly seen in paintings. Artists like M.C. Escher and Leonardo da Vinci have often used similar techniques.

Title: Isometric Submarine
Description: The Isometric Submarine art style uses digital techniques to create 3D objects in two dimensions, often with an industrial and futuristic feel, set in an ocean environment. The art style is geometric in composition with a dominance of the color blue. Artists such as Chris Spooner and Tim Reynolds have notably used isometric techniques.

Title: Blacklight Hamster
Description: In the Blacklight Hamster art style, normally found in digital art, the use of neon colors and blacklight lighting condition creates a playful mood. This style is similar to Neon Art or Pop Art. Artists like Kenny Scharf and Murakami Takashi have often experimented with similar styles.
